34/*
35 * before the END for the subprogram is generated, check how/where
36 * adjustable & assumed shape arrays were declared.
37 *
38 * An assumed shape array may be declared before its ENTRY, in which
39 * case its assumed shape attribute needs to be set.
40 *
41 * The entry's assumed size, adjustable, or assumed shape flags are set
42 * if there are corresponding array arguments.
43 */
44

79/*
80 * semant-created temporaries which are re-used across statements.
81 */
82
83static int temps_ctr[3];
84#define TEMPS_CTR(n) (temps_ctr[n]++)
85#define TEMPS_STK(n) ((sem.doif_depth << 10) + temps_ctr[n]++)
86
87void
88chk_adjarr(void)
89{
90 int entsym;
91 int *dscptr, cnt, arg;
92 LOGICAL is_first;
93 int stype;
94
95 // An RU_PROG can contain adjustable arrays in blocks.
96 if (gbl.rutype != RU_FUNC && gbl.rutype != RU_SUBR && gbl.rutype != RU_PROG)
97 return;
98 if (gbl.currsub <= NOSYM)
99 return;
100 is_first = TRUE;
101 /* scan all entries. NOTE: gbl.entries not yet set */
102 for (entsym = gbl.currsub; entsym != NOSYM; entsym = SYMLKG(entsym)) {
103 ADDRESSP(entsym, 0);
104 dscptr = aux.dpdsc_base + DPDSCG(entsym);
105 for (cnt = PARAMCTG(entsym); cnt > 0; cnt--) {
106 arg = *dscptr++;
107 if (arg == 0)
108 continue;
109 stype = STYPEG(arg);
110 /*
111 * continue processing if
112 * ST_ARRAY | (ST_DERIVED && TY_ARRAY)
113 */
114 if (stype != ST_ARRAY)
115 continue;
116 if (ALLOCG(arg) && !ALLOCATTRG(arg)) {
117 to_assumed_shape(arg);
118 }
119 if (ASSUMSHPG(arg))
120 ASSUMSHPP(entsym, 1);
121 if (ASUMSZG(arg))
122 ASUMSZP(entsym, 1);
123 if (ADJARRG(arg) || RUNTIMEG(arg)) {
124 ADJARRP(entsym, 1); /* tell expand adj. arrays in entry */
125 if (!is_first || AFTENTG(arg))
126 AFTENTP(entsym, 1); /* tell expand adj. code generated */
127 }
128 }
129 /*
130 * repeat for any adjustable arrays which are pointers-based
131 * objects.
132 */
133 for (arg = gbl.p_adjarr; arg > NOSYM; arg = SYMLKG(arg)) {
134 if (SCG(arg) == SC_BASED && (ADJARRG(arg) || RUNTIMEG(arg))) {
135 ADJARRP(entsym, 1); /* tell expand adj. arrays in entry */
136 if (!is_first || AFTENTG(arg))
137 AFTENTP(entsym, 1); /* tell expand adj. code generated */
138 }
139 }
140 is_first = FALSE;
141 }
142}
143
144static void
145to_assumed_shape(int arg)
146{
147 ADSC *ad;
148 int ndim;
149 int i;
150
151 AFTENTP(arg, 1);
152 ASSUMSHPP(arg, 1);
153 if (!XBIT(54, 2) && !XBIT(58, 0x400000))
154 SDSCS1P(arg, 1);
155 ALLOCP(arg, 0);
156 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(arg));
157 AD_ASSUMSHP(ad) = 1;
158 /* change the lower bound if one was not specifier. */
159 ndim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
160 for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++)
161 if (AD_LWBD(ad, i) == AD_LWAST(ad, i) && !XBIT(54, 2) &&
162 !XBIT(58, 0x400000))
163 AD_LWBD(ad, i) = astb.bnd.one;
164}

166/** \brief Return TRUE if the expression at 'ast' is composed of constants
167 and the special symbol 'hpf_np$'. In this case, even though the
168 bound is not a literal constant, it is a runtime constant.
169 */
170int
171runtime_array(int ast)
172{
173 int sym;
174#if DEBUG
175 if (DBGBIT(3, 32))
176 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "runtime_array(ast=%d)\n", ast);
177#endif
178 if (!ast)
179 return TRUE;
180 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
181 case A_ID:
182 /* check for named parameter, or hpf_np$ */
183 sym = A_SPTRG(ast);
184 if (sym == gbl.sym_nproc) {
185 return TRUE;
186 }
187 if (STYPEG(sym) == ST_CONST || STYPEG(sym) == ST_PARAM) {
188 return TRUE;
189 }
190 break;
191 case A_CNST:
192 return TRUE;
193 case A_BINOP:
194 if (runtime_array(A_LOPG(ast)) && runtime_array(A_ROPG(ast))) {
195 return TRUE;
196 }
197 break;
198 case A_UNOP:
199 case A_PAREN:
200 if (runtime_array(A_LOPG(ast))) {
201 return TRUE;
202 }
203 break;
204 } /* switch */
205#if DEBUG
206 if (DBGBIT(3, 32))
207 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "runtime_array(ast=%d): NO\n", ast);
208#endif
209 return FALSE;
210} /* runtime_array */
211
212/* Checks to see if array bound ast is an expression that uses a type parameter.
213 * This function is mirrored in lowersym.c
214 */
215static int
216valid_kind_parm_expr(int ast)
217{
218 int sptr, rslt, i;
219
220 if (!ast)
221 return 0;
222
223 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
224 case A_INTR:
225 switch (A_OPTYPEG(ast)) {
226 case I_INT1:
227 case I_INT2:
228 case I_INT4:
229 case I_INT8:
230 case I_INT:
231 i = A_ARGSG(ast);
232 return valid_kind_parm_expr(ARGT_ARG(i, 0));
233 }
234 break;
235 case A_CNST:
236 return 1;
237 case A_MEM:
238 sptr = memsym_of_ast(ast);
239 if (KINDG(sptr))
240 return 1;
241 return 0;
242 case A_ID:
243 sptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
244 if (KINDG(sptr))
245 return 1;
246 return 0;
247 case A_CONV:
248 case A_UNOP:
249 return valid_kind_parm_expr(A_LOPG(ast));
250 case A_BINOP:
251 rslt = valid_kind_parm_expr(A_LOPG(ast));
252 if (!rslt)
253 return 0;
254 rslt = valid_kind_parm_expr(A_ROPG(ast));
255 if (!rslt)
256 return 0;
257 return 1;
258 }
259 return 0;
260}

262/*----------------------------------------------------------------------
263 * _mk_arrdsc:
264 * A dimension list has been parsed and all bounds information has been
265 * deposited into a few semant global data structures. From this
266 * information, create an array record along with the array's array
267 * descriptor, and return the pointer to the array data record.
268 * The contents of the array record are as follows:
269 *
270 * Deferred / assumed-shape arrays:
271 * --------------------------------
272 * AD_LWBD == AD_LWAST, and AD_UPBD == AD_UPAST:
273 * = AST of compiler-generated temp vars, *except*:
274 * -- in a module they're undefined;
275 * -- if the lower bound is explicit (assumed shape array),
276 * AD_LWBD = AST of lower bound = sem.bounds[i].lwast,
277 * and the others are as above.
278 *
279 * Explicit-shape arrays:
280 * ----------------------
281 * AD_LWBD / AD_UPBD:
282 * = sem.bounds[i].lwast / upast
283 * = AST of lower / upper bound as it appears in the program.
284 * AD_LWBD = NULL for default lower bound.
285 * AD_UPBD = NULL for '*' (assumed size).
286 *
287 * AD_LWAST / AD_UPAST:
288 * = AST of lower / upper bound, *except*:
289 * -- if the bound is non-constant and we're not in a module,
290 * it's the AST of a compiler-generated temp var;
291 * -- AD_UPAST = NULL for '*' (assumed size).
292 */
293static DTYPE
294_mk_arrdsc(int start_of_base)
295{
296 DTYPE dtype;
297 ISZ_T last_mp, last_lb, last_ub, zbase;
298 LOGICAL last_mp_const, last_lb_const, last_ub_const, zbase_const;
299 ADSC *ad;
300 int i;
301 int adjarr, runtime;
302 int ast;
303 LOGICAL need_temps, struct_base_dim;
304
305 need_temps = TRUE;
306 /*
307 * don't create any bounds temps if in a module specification or
308 * if within an interface block in the module specification
309 */
310 if (IN_MODULE_SPEC || (IN_MODULE && sem.interface &&
311 sem.interf_base[sem.interface - 1].currsub == 0))
312 need_temps = FALSE;
313
314 /* adjustable array for interface we need temp */
315 if (need_temps == FALSE && sem.interface)
316 need_temps = TRUE;
317
318 dtype = get_array_dtype(sem.arrdim.ndim, DT_NONE);
319 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
320
321 /* these inits shut lint up */
322 last_lb_const = last_ub_const = 0;
323 last_lb = last_ub = 0;
324
325 if (sem.arrdim.ndefer) {
326 /* A deferred or assumed-shape array.
327 * sem.bounds[i] is defined as follows:
328 *
329 * bounds lowtype lowb lwast uptype upb upast
330 * ----------------------------------------------------------
331 * ( : ) S_NULL -- -- -- -- --
332 * (<e>: ) S_EXPR -- <ast> -- -- --
333 * ----------------------------------------------------------
334 */
335 if (sem.arrdim.ndefer != sem.arrdim.ndim) {
336 errsev(152);
337 sem.arrdim.ndefer = 0;
338 }
339 if (need_temps) {
340 /* Create temporaries for the lower and upper bounds,
341 * the multipliers, and the zero base offset.
342 */
343 for (i = 0;; i++) {
344 int lowtype;
345 if (i == 0)
346 last_mp = astb.bnd.one;
347 else
348 last_mp = mk_bnd_ast();
349 AD_MLPYR(ad, i) = last_mp;
350
351 if (i == sem.arrdim.ndim)
352 break; /* -- loop exit point-- */
353
354 lowtype = sem.bounds[i].lowtype;
355 if (i < start_of_base) { /* normal case */
356 if (lowtype != S_EXPR) {
357 AD_LWBD(ad, i) = AD_LWAST(ad, i) = mk_bnd_ast();
358 } else {
359 AD_LWBD(ad, i) = sem.bounds[i].lwast;
360 AD_LWAST(ad, i) = mk_bnd_ast();
361 AD_ASSUMSHP(ad) = 1;
362 }
363 AD_UPBD(ad, i) = AD_UPAST(ad, i) = mk_bnd_ast();
364 } else { /* in a structure base */
365 AD_LWBD(ad, i) = sem.bounds[i].lowb;
366 AD_LWAST(ad, i) = sem.bounds[i].lwast;
367 AD_UPBD(ad, i) = sem.bounds[i].upb;
368 AD_UPAST(ad, i) = sem.bounds[i].upast;
369 if (lowtype == S_EXPR)
370 AD_ASSUMSHP(ad) = 1;
371 }
372 last_lb = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
373 last_ub = AD_UPAST(ad, i);
374 }
375 AD_ZBASE(ad) = mk_bnd_ast();
376 } else {
377 /* temps aren't created for the bounds; just propagate any
378 * assumed-shape lower bounds.
379 */
380 for (i = 0; i < sem.arrdim.ndim; i++) {
381 if (sem.bounds[i].lowtype == S_EXPR) {
382 AD_LWBD(ad, i) = sem.bounds[i].lwast;
383 AD_ASSUMSHP(ad) = 1;
384 }
385 }
386 }
387 for (i = 0; i < sem.arrdim.ndim; i++) {
388 AD_EXTNTAST(ad, i) =
389 mk_shared_extent(AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_UPAST(ad, i), i);
390 }
391 AD_NOBOUNDS(ad) = AD_DEFER(ad) = 1;
392 return dtype;
393 }
394
395 adjarr = runtime = 0;
396 for (i = 0; i < sem.arrdim.ndim; i++) {
397 if (sem.bounds[i].lowtype == S_EXPR) {
398 if (chk_len_parm_expr(sem.bounds[i].lwast, sem.stag_dtype, 1) ||
399 chk_kind_parm_expr(sem.bounds[i].lwast, sem.stag_dtype, 1, 0)) {
400 need_temps = FALSE;
401 }
402 if (!adjarr && runtime_array(sem.bounds[i].lwast))
403 ++runtime;
404 else
405 ++adjarr;
406 }
407 if (sem.bounds[i].uptype == S_EXPR) {
408 if (chk_len_parm_expr(sem.bounds[i].upast, sem.stag_dtype, 1) ||
409 chk_kind_parm_expr(sem.bounds[i].upast, sem.stag_dtype, 1, 0)) {
410 need_temps = FALSE;
411 }
412 if (!adjarr && runtime_array(sem.bounds[i].upast))
413 ++runtime;
414 else
415 ++adjarr;
416 }
417 }
418 if (adjarr)
419 AD_ADJARR(ad) = 1;
420
421 zbase_const = TRUE;
422 zbase = 0;
423 for (i = 0;; i++) {
424 /* compute multiplier for this dimension: */
425
426 if (i == 0) {
427 last_mp = 1;
428 AD_MLPYR(ad, 0) = astb.bnd.one;
429 last_mp_const = TRUE;
430 } else if (last_mp_const && last_lb_const && last_ub_const) {
431 last_mp = last_mp * (last_ub - last_lb + 1);
432 AD_MLPYR(ad, i) = mk_isz_cval(last_mp, astb.bnd.dtype);
433 } else if (!last_ub_const && last_ub == 0)
434 AD_MLPYR(ad, i) = 0;
435 else {
436 /* don't generate an expression, use a temporary */
437 if (AD_LWAST(ad, i - 1) == astb.bnd.one &&
438 AD_MLPYR(ad, i - 1) == astb.bnd.one && last_ub) {
439 last_mp = last_ub;
440 last_mp_const = last_ub_const;
441 } else {
442 ast = mk_mlpyr_expr(AD_LWAST(ad, i - 1), AD_UPAST(ad, i - 1),
443 AD_MLPYR(ad, i - 1));
444 last_mp = mk_shared_bnd_ast(ast);
445 last_mp_const = FALSE;
446 }
447 AD_MLPYR(ad, i) = last_mp;
448 }
449 if (i == sem.arrdim.ndim)
450 break; /* ----- loop exit point ----- */
451
452 /* Process lower bound for this dimension.
453 * sem.bounds[i] is defined as follows:
454 *
455 * lower-bound lowtype lowb lwast
456 * --------------------------------------------------------------
457 * <NULL> S_CONST 1 0 (!)
458 * <literal or named const> S_CONST <const-val> <ast>
459 * <non const expr> S_EXPR 1 (!) <ast>
460 * --------------------------------------------------------------
461 */
462
463 struct_base_dim = (i >= start_of_base);
464 last_lb = sem.bounds[i].lowb;
465 last_lb_const = (sem.bounds[i].lowtype != S_EXPR);
466
467 AD_LWBD(ad, i) = struct_base_dim ? sem.bounds[i].lowb : sem.bounds[i].lwast;
468
469 switch (sem.bounds[i].lowtype) {
470 case S_EXPR:
471 if (need_temps)
472 /* create a temp for this bound */
473 if (A_TYPEG(sem.bounds[i].lwast) == A_CONV &&
474 valid_kind_parm_expr(sem.bounds[i].lwast)) {
475 AD_LWAST(ad, i) = last_lb =
476 struct_base_dim ? A_LOPG(sem.bounds[i].lwast)
477 : mk_shared_bnd_ast(sem.bounds[i].lwast);
478 } else
479 AD_LWAST(ad, i) = last_lb =
480 struct_base_dim ? mk_bnd_int(sem.bounds[i].lwast)
481 : mk_shared_bnd_ast(sem.bounds[i].lwast);
482 else {
483 /* don't create a temp; the bound is what was declared */
484 if (A_TYPEG(sem.bounds[i].lwast) == A_CONV &&
485 valid_kind_parm_expr(sem.bounds[i].lwast)) {
486 AD_LWAST(ad, i) = A_LOPG(sem.bounds[i].lwast);
487 } else
488 AD_LWAST(ad, i) = mk_bnd_int(sem.bounds[i].lwast);
489 last_lb = astb.bnd.one;
490 }
491 break;
492 default:
493 /* S_CONST: this lower bound is a constant. */
494 AD_LWAST(ad, i) = (sem.bounds[i].lowb == 1)
495 ? astb.bnd.one
496 : mk_bnd_int(sem.bounds[i].lwast);
497 break;
498 }
499
500 if (zbase_const && last_lb_const && last_mp_const)
501 zbase = zbase + sem.bounds[i].lowb * last_mp;
502 else
503 zbase_const = FALSE;
504
505 /* Process upper bound for this dimension.
506 * sem.bounds[i] is defined as follows:
507 *
508 * upper-bound uptype upb upast
509 * --------------------------------------------------------------
510 * * S_STAR 0 0
511 * <literal or named const> S_CONST <const-val> <ast>
512 * <non const expr> S_EXPR 1 (!) <ast>
513 * --------------------------------------------------------------
514 */
515 last_ub = sem.bounds[i].upb;
516 last_ub_const = (sem.bounds[i].uptype == S_CONST);
517
518 AD_UPBD(ad, i) = struct_base_dim ? sem.bounds[i].upb
519 : sem.bounds[i].upast; /* 0 for '*'*/
520 switch (sem.bounds[i].uptype) {
521 case S_EXPR:
522 if (need_temps)
523 /* create a temp for this bound */
524 if (A_TYPEG(sem.bounds[i].upast) == A_CONV &&
525 valid_kind_parm_expr(sem.bounds[i].upast)) {
526 AD_UPAST(ad, i) = last_ub =
527 struct_base_dim ? A_LOPG(sem.bounds[i].upast)
528 : mk_shared_bnd_ast(sem.bounds[i].upast);
529 } else
530 AD_UPAST(ad, i) = last_ub =
531 struct_base_dim ? mk_bnd_int(sem.bounds[i].upast)
532 : mk_shared_bnd_ast(sem.bounds[i].upast);
533 else {
534 /* don't create a temp; the bound is what was declared */
535 if (A_TYPEG(sem.bounds[i].upast) == A_CONV &&
536 valid_kind_parm_expr(sem.bounds[i].upast)) {
537 AD_UPAST(ad, i) = A_LOPG(sem.bounds[i].upast);
538 } else
539 AD_UPAST(ad, i) = mk_bnd_int(sem.bounds[i].upast);
540 last_ub = astb.bnd.one;
541 }
542 break;
543 case S_CONST:
544 /* this upper bound is a constant. */
545 AD_UPAST(ad, i) = mk_bnd_int(sem.bounds[i].upast);
546 break;
547 default:
548 /* S_STAR: "*" was specified for this upper bound. */
549 if (i + 1 != sem.arrdim.ndim && !is_parameter_context())
550 error(48, 3, gbl.lineno, CNULL, CNULL);
551 AD_UPAST(ad, i) = sem.bounds[i].upast; /* == NULL */
552 AD_ASSUMSZ(ad) = 1;
553 break;
554 }
555
556 AD_EXTNTAST(ad, i) = mk_shared_extent(AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_UPAST(ad, i), i);
557 } /* end of for loop */
558
559 if (!need_temps && (adjarr || runtime) && sem.interface) {
560 AD_NUMELM(ad) = 0;
561 }
562
563 if (zbase_const)
564 AD_ZBASE(ad) = mk_isz_cval(zbase, astb.bnd.dtype);
565 else {
566 ast = mk_zbase_expr(ad);
567 AD_ZBASE(ad) = mk_shared_bnd_ast(ast);
568 }
569 return dtype;
570}
571
572DTYPE
573mk_arrdsc(void)
574{
575 return _mk_arrdsc(99);
576}

578static void
579save_dim_specs(SEM_DIM_SPECS *aa)
580{
581 if (sem.in_dim) {
582 BCOPY(aa, &sem.bounds[0], struct _sem_bounds, MAXDIMS);
583 aa->arrdim = sem.arrdim;
584 }
585}
586
587static void
588restore_dim_specs(SEM_DIM_SPECS *aa)
589{
590 if (sem.in_dim) {
591 BCOPY(&sem.bounds[0], aa, struct _sem_bounds, MAXDIMS);
592 sem.arrdim = aa->arrdim;
593 }
594}
595
596/** \brief Process an explicit shape list has been parsed and all bounds
597 information has been deposited into a few semant global data
598 structures.
599 \param sptr sptr of the deferred array
600 \param astparent ast of the parent pointer
601 \param savedelete ?
602
603 From this collection of information:
604 + Generate assignments which define the lower and upper bounds for the
605 deferred array; where the bounds are stored (asts) are located in the
606 array descriptor.
607 + Create a subscript AST which is used to represent the explicit shape;
608 the bounds for the explicit shape use the bounds asts which are the
609 destinations of the generated assignments; note that each subscript
610 is represented as a triple.
611 */
612int
613gen_defer_shape(int sptr, int astparent, int savedelete)
614{
615 int dt;
616 int numdim;
617 int subs[MAXDIMS];
618 int i;
619 int ast, std;
620 int src, lb, ub;
621 int extent;
622 ITEM *itemp;
623
624 dt = DTYPEG(sptr);
625 numdim = ADD_NUMDIM(dt);
626 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++) {
627 if (sem.bounds[i].lwast)
628 src = sem.bounds[i].lwast;
629 else
630 src = astb.bnd.one;
631 if (ADD_DEFER(dt)) {
632
633 lb = ADD_LWBD(dt, i);
634 } else {
635 lb = ADD_LWAST(dt, i);
636 }
637 if (lb && A_TYPEG(lb) != A_CNST) {
638 ast = mk_assn_stmt(check_member(astparent, lb), src, astb.bnd.dtype);
639 std = add_stmt(ast);
640 ASSNP(sym_of_ast(lb), 1);
641 if (savedelete) {
642 itemp = (ITEM *)getitem(1, sizeof(ITEM));
643 itemp->ast = mk_id(sptr);
644 itemp->t.ilm = std;
645 itemp->next = sem.p_dealloc_delete;
646 sem.p_dealloc_delete = itemp;
647 }
648 }
649
650 if (ADD_DEFER(dt)) {
651 ub = ADD_UPBD(dt, i);
652 } else {
653 ub = ADD_UPAST(dt, i);
654 }
655 if (ub && A_TYPEG(ub) != A_CNST) {
656 int ext, useub;
657 useub = sem.bounds[i].upast;
658 if (A_TYPEG(ub) == A_ID || A_TYPEG(ub) == A_SUBSCR) {
659 ast = mk_assn_stmt(check_member(astparent, ub), sem.bounds[i].upast,
660 astb.bnd.dtype);
661 std = add_stmt(ast);
662 ASSNP(sym_of_ast(ub), 1);
663 if (savedelete) {
664 itemp = (ITEM *)getitem(1, sizeof(ITEM));
665 itemp->ast = mk_id(sptr);
666 itemp->t.ilm = std;
667 itemp->next = sem.p_dealloc_delete;
668 sem.p_dealloc_delete = itemp;
669 }
670 useub = ub;
671 }
672
673 /* Need to make an assignment to the extent also */
674 if (src == astb.bnd.one) {
675 extent = useub;
676 } else {
677 extent =
678 mk_extent_expr(check_member(astparent, lb), sem.bounds[i].upast);
679 }
680 ext = ADD_EXTNTAST(dt, i);
681 if (A_TYPEG(ext) == A_ID || A_TYPEG(ext) == A_SUBSCR) {
682 ast = mk_assn_stmt(check_member(astparent, ext),
683 check_member(astparent, extent), astb.bnd.dtype);
684
685 std = add_stmt(ast);
686 ASSNP(sym_of_ast(ADD_EXTNTAST(dt, i)), 1);
687 if (savedelete) {
688 itemp = (ITEM *)getitem(1, sizeof(ITEM));
689 itemp->ast = mk_id(sptr);
690 itemp->t.ilm = std;
691 itemp->next = sem.p_dealloc_delete;
692 sem.p_dealloc_delete = itemp;
693 }
694 }
695 }
696 }
697
698 for (i = 0; i < sem.arrdim.ndim; i++) {
699 if (ADD_DEFER(dt)) {
700 lb = ADD_LWBD(dt, i);
701 ub = ADD_UPBD(dt, i);
702 } else {
703 lb = ADD_LWAST(dt, i);
704 ub = ADD_UPAST(dt, i);
705 }
706 if (lb == 0)
707 lb = astb.bnd.one;
708 subs[i] =
709 mk_triple(check_member(astparent, lb), check_member(astparent, ub), 0);
710 }
711 ast = check_member(astparent, mk_id(sptr));
712 ast = mk_subscr(ast, subs, sem.arrdim.ndim, (int)DTYPEG(sptr));
713
714 return ast;
715}
716
717void
718add_p_dealloc_item(int sptr)
719{
720 int depth;
721 ITEM *itemp;
722
723 if (sem.use_etmps) {
724 /* Add allocatable temps created for an expression to the 'etmp'
725 * list; they need to deallocated at the end of processing the
726 * expression.
727 */
728 add_etmp(sptr);
729 return;
730 }
731
732 /* Don't add it twice */
733 for (itemp = sem.p_dealloc; itemp; itemp = itemp->next)
734 if (A_SPTRG(itemp->ast) == sptr)
735 return;
736
737 for (depth = sem.doif_depth; depth > 0 && DI_ID(depth) == DI_FORALL; --depth)
738 ;
739
740 itemp = (ITEM *)getitem(1, sizeof(ITEM));
741 itemp->ast = mk_id(sptr);
742 itemp->next = sem.p_dealloc;
743 itemp->t.conval = depth;
744 sem.p_dealloc = itemp;
745}
746
747
748/** \brief Generate deallocates for the temporary arrays in the sem.p_delloc
749 * list.
750 */
751void
752gen_deallocate_arrays()
753{
754 if (sem.p_dealloc) {
755 ITEM *p, *t;
756 int depth;
757 for (depth = sem.doif_depth; depth > 0 && DI_ID(depth) == DI_FORALL;
758 --depth)
759 ;
760 p = NULL; /* p points to last item on remaining list */
761 for (t = sem.p_dealloc; t; t = t->next) {
762 if (t->t.conval == depth) {
763 (void)gen_alloc_dealloc(TK_DEALLOCATE, t->ast, 0);
764 } else {
765 /* leave on the list */
766 if (p != NULL) {
767 p->next = t;
768 } else {
769 sem.p_dealloc = t;
770 }
771 p = t;
772 }
773 }
774 /* p points to last item on remaining list, if any */
775 if (p) {
776 p->next = NULL;
777 } else {
778 sem.p_dealloc = NULL;
779 }
780 }
781}
782
783/*
784 * For certain expression, such as if expressions, it's necessary to keep
785 * a list of any allocatable temps created while processing the expression.
786 * These temps, if they're deallocated at the end of the statement a memory
787 * leak may occur because the statement may actually change the control
788 * flow. These temps must be deallocated at the end of the processing
789 * the expression.
790 */
791static void
792add_etmp(int sptr)
793{
794 ITEM *x;
795
796 x = (ITEM *)getitem(0, sizeof(ITEM));
797 x->next = sem.etmp_list;
798 sem.etmp_list = x;
799 x->t.sptr = sptr;
800}
801
802void
803mk_defer_shape(SPTR sptr)
804{
805 int i;
806 int dt;
807 int numdim;
808 ADSC *ad;
809
810 dt = DTYPEG(sptr);
811 ad = AD_DPTR(dt);
812 numdim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
813
814 if (AD_LWAST(ad, 0))
815 return;
816
817 if (IN_MODULE_SPEC)
818 MDALLOCP(sptr, 1); /* mark global allocatable array */
819 else
820 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++) {
821 AD_LWAST(ad, i) = mk_bnd_ast();
822 AD_UPAST(ad, i) = mk_bnd_ast();
823 AD_EXTNTAST(ad, i) = mk_bnd_ast();
824 }
825}
826
827/*
828 * return '1' if astx is a A_ID of a compiler-created temp
829 */
830static int
831tempvar(int astx)
832{
833 if (A_TYPEG(astx) == A_ID &&
834 (CCSYMG(A_SPTRG(astx)) || HCCSYMG(A_SPTRG(astx))))
835 return 1;
836 return 0;
837} /* tempvar */
838
839void
840mk_assumed_shape(SPTR sptr)
841{
842 int i;
843 DTYPE dt = DTYPEG(sptr);
844 ADSC *ad = AD_DPTR(dt);
845 int numdim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
846
847 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++)
848 if (AD_LWBD(ad, i) == AD_LWAST(ad, i) &&
849 A_TYPEG(AD_LWBD(ad, i)) != A_CNST && tempvar(AD_LWBD(ad, i)) &&
850 !XBIT(54, 2) && !XBIT(58, 0x400000)) {
851 AD_LWBD(ad, i) = astb.bnd.one;
852 AD_LWAST(ad, i) = astb.bnd.one;
853 }
854 AD_ASSUMSHP(ad) = 1;
855 if (sem.arrdim.assumedrank) {
856 AD_ASSUMRANK(ad) = 1;
857 }
858}
859
860/** \brief Get a compiler array temporary of type dtype which is used to
861 represent array constants.
862 */
863SPTR
864get_arr_const(DTYPE dtype)
865{
866 static int iavl;
867 /* stype will get changed to ST_ARRAY when it's dinit'd */
868 SPTR sptr = getcctmp('c', iavl++, ST_UNKNOWN, dtype);
869 SCP(sptr, SC_LOCAL);
870 NODESCP(sptr, 0);
871 return sptr;
872}
873
874DTYPE
875select_kind(DTYPE dtype, int ty, INT kind_val)
876{
877 int out_dtype;
878
879 if (kind_val < 0) {
880 error(81, 3, gbl.lineno, "- KIND value must be non-negative", CNULL);
881 return dtype;
882 }
883 out_dtype = -1;
884 switch (ty) {
885 case TY_INT:
886 case TY_INT8:
887 switch (kind_val) {
888 case 8:
889 if (!XBIT(57, 0x2))
890 out_dtype = DT_INT8;
891 break;
892 case 4:
893 out_dtype = DT_INT4;
894 break;
895 case 2:
896 out_dtype = DT_SINT;
897 break;
898 case 1:
899 out_dtype = DT_BINT;
900 break;
901 }
902 break;
903 case TY_CMPLX:
904 case TY_DCMPLX:
905 switch (kind_val) {
906 case 16:
907 if (!XBIT(57, 0x8))
908 out_dtype = DT_QCMPLX;
909 if (XBIT(57, 0x10)) {
910 error(437, 2, gbl.lineno, "COMPLEX(16)", "COMPLEX(8)");
911 out_dtype = DT_CMPLX16;
912 }
913 break;
914 case 8:
915 out_dtype = DT_CMPLX16;
916 break;
917 case 4:
918 out_dtype = DT_CMPLX8;
919 break;
920 }
921 break;
922 case TY_REAL:
923 case TY_DBLE:
924 switch (kind_val) {
925 case 16:
926 if (!XBIT(57, 0x4))
927 out_dtype = DT_QUAD;
928 if (XBIT(57, 0x10)) {
929 error(437, 2, gbl.lineno, "REAL(16)", "REAL(8)");
930 out_dtype = DT_REAL8;
931 }
932 break;
933 case 8:
934 out_dtype = DT_REAL8;
935 break;
936 case 4:
937 out_dtype = DT_REAL4;
938 break;
939 }
940 break;
941 case TY_LOG:
942 case TY_LOG8:
943 switch (kind_val) {
944 case 8:
945 if (!XBIT(57, 0x2))
946 out_dtype = DT_LOG8;
947 break;
948 case 4:
949 out_dtype = DT_LOG4;
950 break;
951 case 2:
952 out_dtype = DT_SLOG;
953 break;
954 case 1:
955 out_dtype = DT_BLOG;
956 break;
957 }
958 break;
959 case TY_CHAR:
960 if (kind_val == 2)
961 out_dtype = DT_NCHAR;
962 if (kind_val == 1)
963 out_dtype = DT_CHAR;
964 break;
965 default:
966 error(81, 3, gbl.lineno, "- KIND = specified with a non-intrinsic type",
967 CNULL);
968 return dtype;
969 }
970 if (out_dtype == -1) {
971 error(81, 3, gbl.lineno, "- KIND parameter has unknown value for data type",
972 CNULL);
973 return dtype;
974 }
975 return out_dtype;
976}

978typedef struct _ido_info {
979 DOINFO *doinfo;
980 struct _ido_info *next;
981} IDO_INFO;
982
983typedef struct {
984 LOGICAL is_const;
985 INT scalar_cnt; /* # of scalar expressions */
986 int aggr_cnt; /* ast expr of # of elements in implied do or array
987 expression. */
988 int eltype; /* element dtype */
989 int zln; /* element dtype is zero length char */
990 int arrtype; /* array dtype record */
991 int tmp; /* sptr of temp array */
992 int tmpid; /* id ast of array tmp */
993 int subs[MAXDIMS]; /* current subscripts - used in _construct() */
994 int indx[MAXDIMS]; /* current subscript value */
995 INT element_cnt[MAXDIMS]; /* # of scalar expressions */
996 int indx_tmpid[MAXDIMS]; /* id ast of subscripting temporary */
997 int level; /* implied do nesting level */
998 int width;
999 LOGICAL func_in_do; /* func call found in ac-value-list */
1000 IDO_INFO *ido_list; /* track the implied-do loop encoutered */
1001 int ido_level; /* track the depth of implied-do loop encoutered */
1002 struct {
1003 DOINFO *doinfo; /* the outermost implied-do loop
1004 * on which the generated loop depends.
1005 */
1006 int start; /* start std of the generated loop */
1007 int end; /* end std of the generated loop */
1008 int level; /* the depth of the outermost implied-do loop
1009 * that has generated a loop.
1010 */
1011 int sumid; /* the temp variable used to compute
1012 * size of implied-do loop.
1013 */
1014 } loop_stmts;
1015} _ACS;
1016
1017static _ACS acs;
1018static LOGICAL _can_fold(int);
1019static void constructf90(int, ACL *);
1020static void _dinit_acl(ACL *, LOGICAL);
1021
1022static int acl_array_num = 0;
1023
1024static const char *_iexpr_op[] = {
1025 "?0?", "ADD", "SUB", "MUL", "DIV", "EXP", "NEG",
1026 "INTR_CALL", "ARRAYREF", "MEMBR_SEL", "CONV", "CAT", "EXPK", "LEQV",
1027 "LNEQV", "LOR", "LAND", "EQ", "GE", "GT", "LE",
1028 "LT", "NE", "LNOT", "EXPX", "TRIPLE",
1029};
1030
1031static const char *
1032iexpr_op(int op)
1033{
1034 if (op <= sizeof(_iexpr_op) / sizeof(char *))
1035 return _iexpr_op[op];
1036 return "?N?";
1037}
1038
1039/** \brief Given an allocatable array and an explicit shape list which has been
1040 deposited in the semant 'bounds' structure, generate assignments to
1041 the arrays bounds temporaries, and allocate the array. Save the id
1042 ast
1043 of the array for an ensuing deallocate of the array.
1044 */
1045void
1046gen_allocate_array(int arr)
1047{
1048 int alloc_obj = gen_defer_shape(arr, 0, arr);
1049 if (is_deferlenchar_dtype(acs.arrtype)) {
1050 get_static_descriptor(arr);
1051 get_all_descriptors(arr);
1052 }
1053 gen_alloc_dealloc(TK_ALLOCATE, alloc_obj, 0);
1054 add_p_dealloc_item(arr);
1055}

1057#if DEBUG
1058static void
1059_printacl(int in_array, ACL *aclp, FILE *f)
1060{
1061 SST *stkp;
1062 ACL *member_aclp;
1063 DTYPE dtype;
1064 int sptr;
1065 int save_array_num;
1066
1067 /* print a list of aclps */
1068
1069 for (; aclp != NULL; aclp = aclp->next) {
1070 switch (aclp->id) {
1071 case AC_AST:
1072 fprintf(f, "%d:", acl_array_num);
1073 fprintf(f, "ast%d", aclp->u1.ast);
1074 dtype = A_DTYPEG(aclp->u1.ast);
1075 if (!in_array)
1076 acl_array_num += compute_width_dtype(dtype);
1077 break;
1078 case AC_EXPR:
1079 fprintf(f, "%d:", acl_array_num);
1080 stkp = aclp->u1.stkp;
1081 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stkp);
1082 switch (SST_IDG(stkp)) {
1083 case S_ACONST:
1084 fprintf(f, "missed aconst");
1085 break;
1086 case S_CONST:
1087 fprintf(f, "const");
1088 break;
1089 case S_SCONST:
1090 fprintf(f, "missed sconst");
1091 break;
1092 case S_EXPR:
1093 fprintf(f, "expr");
1094 break;
1095 case S_IDENT:
1096 fprintf(f, "ident");
1097 break;
1098 default:
1099 fprintf(f, "?SST_ID%d", SST_IDG(stkp));
1100 break;
1101 }
1102 if (!in_array)
1103 acl_array_num += compute_width_dtype(dtype);
1104 break;
1105 case AC_ACONST:
1106 fprintf(f, "(/");
1107 _printacl(1, aclp->subc, f);
1108 fprintf(f, "/)");
1109 dtype = aclp->dtype;
1110 if (!in_array)
1111 acl_array_num += compute_width_dtype(dtype);
1112 break;
1113 case AC_SCONST:
1114 save_array_num = acl_array_num;
1115
1116 dtype = aclp->dtype;
1117 sptr = DTY(dtype + 3); /* tag sptr */
1118 fprintf(f, "%s(", SYMNAME(sptr));
1119 member_aclp = aclp->subc;
1120 _printacl(0, member_aclp, f);
1121 fprintf(f, ")");
1122
1123 if (in_array)
1124 acl_array_num = save_array_num;
1125 break;
1126 case AC_IDO:
1127 fprintf(f, "(");
1128 _printacl(in_array, aclp->subc, f);
1129 fprintf(f, ",i=l,u,s)");
1130 break;
1131 case AC_REPEAT:
1132 fprintf(f, "REPEAT[%d](", aclp->u1.count);
1133 _printacl(in_array, aclp->subc, f);
1134 fprintf(f, ")");
1135 break;
1136 case AC_IEXPR:
1137 dtype = aclp->dtype;
1138 fprintf(f, "AC_IEXPR(dtype %d, op %s)", dtype,
1139 iexpr_op(aclp->u1.expr->op));
1140 break;
1141 default:
1142 interr("_printacl .id", aclp->id, 3);
1143 break;
1144 }
1145 if (aclp->next)
1146 fprintf(f, ",");
1147 }
1148}
