6874 if (!A_ALIASG(ast)) {
6875 /* nothing to do right now */
6876 if (dtype == 0)
6877 dtype = A_DTYPEG(ast);
6878 aval = dinit_eval(ast);
6879 ast = mk_cval(aval, DT_INT);
6880 }
6881 if (dtype == 0)
6882 return ast;
6883 adtype = A_DTYPEG(ast);
6884 if (adtype == dtype)
6885 return ast;
6886 if (!DT_ISSCALAR(adtype) || !DT_ISSCALAR(dtype)) {
6887 return 0;
6888 }
6889 ast = A_ALIASG(ast);
6890 aval = A_SPTRG(ast);
6891 adtype = DTYPEG(aval);
6892 if (DT_ISWORD(adtype))
6893 aval = CONVAL2G(aval);
6894 val = cngcon(aval, adtype, dtype);
6895 ast = mk_cval1(val, dtype);
6896 return ast;
6897} /* dinit_getval */
6898
6899/*
6900 * Similar to dinit_getval, above, but allows types other than integer.
6901 * Part of the fix for FS2281.
6902 */
6903static int
6904dinit_getval1(int ast, DTYPE dtype)
6905{
6906 DTYPE adtype;
6907 INT aval, val;
6908 if (!A_ALIASG(ast)) {
6909 if (dtype == 0)
6910 dtype = A_DTYPEG(ast);
6911 aval = const_eval(ast);
6912 ast = mk_cval(aval, A_DTYPEG(ast));
6913 }
6914 if (dtype == 0)
6915 return ast;
6916 adtype = A_DTYPEG(ast);
6917 if (adtype == dtype)
6918 return ast;
6919 if (!DT_ISSCALAR(adtype) || !DT_ISSCALAR(dtype)) {
6920 return 0;
6921 }
6922 ast = A_ALIASG(ast);
6923 aval = A_SPTRG(ast);
6924 adtype = DTYPEG(aval);
6925 if (DT_ISWORD(adtype))
6926 aval = CONVAL2G(aval);
6927 val = cngcon(aval, adtype, dtype);
6928 ast = mk_cval1(val, dtype);
6929 return ast;
6930} /* dinit_getval1 */
6931
6932static int
6933unop_init_list(int llist, int optype)
6934{
6935 int ll, list, last, nlist;
6936 list = last = 0;
6937 if (!llist) {
6938 /* error return */
6939 interr("unop_init_list, no llist", 0, 3);
6940 return 0;
6941 }
6942 for (ll = llist; ll; ll = A_RIGHTG(ll)) {
6943 int le;
6944 le = A_LEFTG(ll);
6945 if (A_TYPEG(le) == A_INIT) {
6946 nlist = unop_init_list(le, optype);
6947 } else {
6948 /* do the operation */
6949 nlist = mk_unop(optype, le, A_DTYPEG(le));
6950 }
6951 nlist = mk_init(nlist, A_DTYPEG(nlist));
6952 if (last) {
6953 A_RIGHTP(last, nlist);
6954 } else {
6955 list = nlist;
6956 }
6957 last = nlist;
6958 }
6959 return list;
6960} /* unop_init_list */
6961
6962static int
6963binop_init_list(int llist, int rlist, int lop, int rop, int optype)
6964{
6965 int ll, rl, list, last, nlist;
6966 list = last = 0;
6967 if (lop && rop) {
6968 /* error return */
6969 interr("binop_init_list, lop&&rop", 0, 3);
6970 return 0;
6971 }
6972 if (!lop && !llist) {
6973 /* error return */
6974 interr("binop_init_list, neither lop nor llist", 0, 3);
6975 return 0;
6976 }
6977 if (!rop && !rlist) {
6978 /* error return */
6979 interr("binop_init_list, neither rop nor rlist", 0, 3);
6980 return 0;
6981 }
6982 if (!llist && !rlist) {
6983 /* error return */
6984 interr("binop_init_list, neither llist nor rlist", 0, 3);
6985 return 0;
6986 }
6987 if (llist && rlist) {
6988 for (ll = llist, rl = rlist; ll && rl;
6989 ll = A_RIGHTG(ll), rl = A_RIGHTG(rl)) {
6990 /* ll and rl are at an 'A_INIT' */
6991 int le, re;
6992 le = A_LEFTG(ll);
6993 re = A_LEFTG(rl);
6994 if (A_TYPEG(le) == A_INIT && A_TYPEG(re) == A_INIT) {
6995 nlist = binop_init_list(le, re, 0, 0, optype);
6996 } else if (A_TYPEG(le) == A_INIT) {
6997 nlist = binop_init_list(le, 0, 0, re, optype);
6998 } else if (A_TYPEG(re) == A_INIT) {
6999 nlist = binop_init_list(0, re, le, 0, optype);
7000 } else {
7001 /* do the operation */
7002 nlist = mk_binop(optype, le, re, A_DTYPEG(le));
7003 }
7004 nlist = mk_init(nlist, A_DTYPEG(nlist));
7005 if (last) {
7006 A_RIGHTP(last, nlist);
7007 } else {
7008 list = nlist;
7009 }
7010 last = nlist;
7011 }
7012 } else if (llist) {
7013 for (ll = llist; ll; ll = A_RIGHTG(ll)) {
7014 int le;
7015 le = A_LEFTG(ll);
7016 if (A_TYPEG(le) == A_INIT) {
7017 nlist = binop_init_list(le, 0, 0, rop, optype);
7018 } else {
7019 /* do the operation */
7020 nlist = mk_binop(optype, le, rop, A_DTYPEG(le));
7021 }
7022 nlist = mk_init(nlist, A_DTYPEG(nlist));
7023 if (last) {
7024 A_RIGHTP(last, nlist);
7025 } else {
7026 list = nlist;
7027 }
7028 last = nlist;
7029 }
7030 } else if (rlist) {
7031 for (rl = rlist; rl; rl = A_RIGHTG(rl)) {
7032 int re;
7033 re = A_LEFTG(rl);
7034 if (A_TYPEG(re) == A_INIT) {
7035 nlist = binop_init_list(0, re, lop, 0, optype);
7036 } else {
7037 /* do the operation */
7038 nlist = mk_binop(optype, lop, re, A_DTYPEG(re));
7039 }
7040 nlist = mk_init(nlist, A_DTYPEG(nlist));
7041 if (last) {
7042 A_RIGHTP(last, nlist);
7043 } else {
7044 list = nlist;
7045 }
7046 last = nlist;
7047 }
7048 }
7049 return list;
7050} /* binop_init_list */
7051
7052static void
7053add_subscript_list(ASTLIST *list, int ast, int arraylist, int ssval[], int ndim)
7054{
7055 /* find shape for array at 'ast', use that plus values of ssval[]
7056 * to pick a value from 'arraylist' */
7057 int a, sh, i, offset, o;
7058 a = A_LOPG(ast);
7059 sh = A_SHAPEG(a);
7060 assert(SHD_NDIM(sh) == ndim,
7061 "add_subscript_list, shape rank != subscript rank",
7062 SHD_NDIM(sh) - ndim, 3);
7063 offset = 0;
7064 for (i = 0; i < SHD_NDIM(sh); ++i) {
7065 int l, lsptr, lb, u, usptr, ub, ss, ssptr, ssv;
7066 l = SHD_LWB(sh, i);
7067 assert(A_ALIASG(l), "add_subscript_list: nonconstant array lower bound", l,
7068 3);
7069 l = A_ALIASG(l);
7070 lsptr = A_SPTRG(l);
7071 lb = CONVAL2G(lsptr);
7072 u = SHD_UPB(sh, i);
7073 assert(A_ALIASG(u), "add_subscript_list: nonconstant array upper bound", u,
7074 3);
7075 u = A_ALIASG(u);
7076 usptr = A_SPTRG(u);
7077 ub = CONVAL2G(usptr);
7078 ss = ssval[i];
7079 assert(A_ALIASG(ss), "add_subscript_list: nonconstant subscript", ss, 3);
7080 ss = A_ALIASG(ss);
7081 ssptr = A_SPTRG(ss);
7082 ssv = CONVAL2G(ssptr);
7083 if (ub >= lb)
7084 offset *= (ub - lb + 1);
7085 if (ssv >= lb)
7086 offset += ssv - lb;
7087 }
7088 /* skip 'offset' items from the arraylist, add that value to 'list' */
7089 for (o = arraylist; o && offset; o = A_RIGHTG(o), --offset)
7090 ;
7091 if (o) {
7092 DTYPE dtype = DDTG(A_DTYPEG(ast));
7093 add_init(list, A_LEFTG(o), dtype, 0);
7094 }
7095} /* add_subscript_list */
7096
7097static void
7098build_subscript_list(ASTLIST *list, int ast, int arraylist, int ssval[],
7099 int sslist[], int dim, int ndim)
7100{
7101 if (sslist[dim] == 0) {
7102 /* only one value for dimension 'dim' */
7103 if (dim > 0) {
7104 build_subscript_list(list, ast, arraylist, ssval, sslist, dim - 1, ndim);
7105 } else {
7106 add_subscript_list(list, ast, arraylist, ssval, ndim);
7107 }
7108 } else {
7109 /* step dimension 'dim' through all of its values */
7110 int l;
7111 for (l = sslist[dim]; l; l = A_RIGHTG(l)) {
7112 ssval[dim] = A_LEFTG(l);
7113 if (dim > 0) {
7114 build_subscript_list(list, ast, arraylist, ssval, sslist, dim - 1,
7115 ndim);
7116 } else {
7117 add_subscript_list(list, ast, arraylist, ssval, ndim);
7118 }
7119 }
7120 }
7121} /* build_subscript_list */
7122
7123static void
7124build_array_list(ASTLIST *list, int ast, DTYPE dtype, int sptr)
7125{
7126 int asptr, lop, rop, asd, ndim, i;
7127 int lower, upper, stride, d, ssval[MAXDIMS], sslist[MAXDIMS];
7128 ASTLIST larray;
7129 int fldsptr, past;
7130 list->head = 0;
7131 list->tail = 0;
7132 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
7133 case A_CNST:
7134 add_init(list, ast, dtype, 0);
7135 break;
7136 case A_MEM: {
7137 DTYPE dtype;
7138 int a;
7139 fldsptr = A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(ast));
7140 past = A_PARENTG(ast);
7141 asptr = A_SPTRG(past);
7142 for (a = A_LEFTG(PARAMVALG(asptr)); a; a = A_RIGHTG(a)) {
7143 if (A_SPTRG(a) == fldsptr) {
7144 break;
7145 }
7146 }
7147 if (!a) {
7148 interr("field initializer not found", 0, 3);
7149 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
7150 break;
7151 }
7152 dtype = DDTG(DTYPEG(A_SPTRG(a)));
7153 for (a = A_LEFTG(a); a; a = A_RIGHTG(a)) {
7154 add_init(list, A_LEFTG(a), dtype, 0);
7155 }
7156 } break;
7157 case A_ID:
7158 /* an array name */
7159 asptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
7160 switch (STYPEG(asptr)) {
7161 case ST_ARRAY:
7162 case ST_IDENT:
7163 case ST_VAR:
7164 if (PARAMVALG(asptr)) {
7165 DTYPE dtype = DDTG(DTYPEG(asptr));
7166 int a;
7167 for (a = A_LEFTG(PARAMVALG(asptr)); a; a = A_RIGHTG(a)) {
7168 add_init(list, A_LEFTG(a), dtype, 0);
7169 }
7170 }
7171 break;
7172
7173 default:
7174 errsev(69);
7175 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
7176 break;
7177 }
7178 break;
7179 case A_SUBSCR:
7180 /* subscripted array */
7181 build_array_list(&larray, A_LOPG(ast), dtype, sptr);
7182 /* get the subscript; take the one element, or the
7183 * sequence of elements requested */
7184 if (sem.dinit_error)
7185 break;
7186 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
7187 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
7188 assert(ndim <= 7, "build_array_list, >7 dimensions", ndim, 3);
7189 assert(A_SHAPEG(A_LOPG(ast)), "build_array_list, shapeless array", 0, 3);
7190 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
7191 int ss;
7192 ss = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
7193 if (A_SHAPEG(ss) || A_TYPEG(ss) == A_TRIPLE) {
7194 ASTLIST ssl;
7195 build_array_list(&ssl, ss, astb.bnd.dtype, 0);
7196 ssval[i] = 0;
7197 sslist[i] = ssl.head;
7198 } else {
7199 ssval[i] = dinit_getval(ss, astb.bnd.dtype);
7200 sslist[i] = 0;
7201 }
7202 }
7203 build_subscript_list(list, ast, larray.head, ssval, sslist, ndim - 1, ndim);
7204 break;
7205 case A_UNOP:
7206 /* get the right operand */
7207 build_array_list(list, A_LOPG(ast), dtype, sptr);
7208 if (sem.dinit_error)
7209 break;
7210 /* negate? */
7211 switch (A_OPTYPEG(ast)) {
7212 case OP_SUB:
7213 /* negate everything on the list */
7214 unop_init_list(list->head, A_OPTYPEG(ast));
7215 break;
7216 case OP_ADD:
7217 break;
7218 default:
7219 errsev(69);
7220 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
7221 }
7222 break;
7223 case A_BINOP:
7224 /* get right operand */
7225 lop = A_LOPG(ast);
7226 while (A_TYPEG(lop) == A_CONV)
7227 lop = A_LOPG(lop);
7228 rop = A_ROPG(ast);
7229 while (A_TYPEG(rop) == A_CONV)
7230 rop = A_LOPG(rop);
7231 if (A_SHAPEG(lop) && !A_SHAPEG(rop)) {
7232 build_array_list(list, lop, dtype, sptr);
7233 if (sem.dinit_error)
7234 break;
7235 binop_init_list(list->head, 0, 0, rop, A_OPTYPEG(ast));
7236 } else if (!A_SHAPEG(lop) && A_SHAPEG(rop)) {
7237 build_array_list(list, rop, dtype, sptr);
7238 if (sem.dinit_error)
7239 break;
7240 binop_init_list(0, list->head, lop, 0, A_OPTYPEG(ast));
7241 } else {
7242 ASTLIST list2;
7243 build_array_list(list, lop, dtype, sptr);
7244 if (sem.dinit_error)
7245 break;
7246 list2.head = list2.tail = 0;
7247 build_array_list(&list2, rop, dtype, sptr);
7248 if (sem.dinit_error)
7249 break;
7250 binop_init_list(list->head, list2.head, 0, 0, A_OPTYPEG(ast));
7251 }
7252 break;
7253 case A_CONV:
7254 case A_PAREN:
7255 build_array_list(list, A_LOPG(ast), dtype, sptr);
7256 break;
7257 case A_TRIPLE:
7258 /* build a list of items from the triplet */
7259 lower = dinit_getval(A_LBDG(ast), astb.bnd.dtype);
7260 upper = dinit_getval(A_UPBDG(ast), astb.bnd.dtype);
7261 if (A_STRIDEG(ast)) {
7262 stride = dinit_getval(A_STRIDEG(ast), astb.bnd.dtype);
7263 } else {
7264 stride = astb.bnd.one;
7265 }
7266 if (lower == 0 || upper == 0 || stride == 0) {
7267 errsev(69);
7268 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
7269 break;
7270 }
7271 lower = A_ALIASG(lower);
7272 upper = A_ALIASG(upper);
7273 stride = A_ALIASG(stride);
7274 if (lower == 0 || upper == 0 || stride == 0) {
7275 errsev(69);
7276 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
7277 break;
7278 }
7279 lower = A_SPTRG(lower);
7280 upper = A_SPTRG(upper);
7281 stride = A_SPTRG(stride);
7282 lower = CONVAL2G(lower);
7283 upper = CONVAL2G(upper);
7284 stride = CONVAL2G(stride);
7285 if (stride == 0) {
7286 errsev(69);
7287 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
7288 break;
7289 } else if (stride > 0 && lower > upper) {
7290 errsev(69);
7291 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
7292 break;
7293 } else if (stride < 0 && lower < upper) {
7294 errsev(69);
7295 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
7296 break;
7297 }
7298 if (lower <= upper) {
7299 for (d = lower; d <= upper; d += stride) {
7300 /* make a constant with value 'd'; add to A_INIT list */
7301 int a = mk_isz_cval(d, astb.bnd.dtype);
7302 add_init(list, a, astb.bnd.dtype, 0);
7303 }
7304 } else {
7305 for (d = lower; d >= upper; d += stride) {
7306 /* make a constant with value 'd'; add to A_INIT list */
7307 int a = mk_isz_cval(d, astb.bnd.dtype);
7308 add_init(list, a, astb.bnd.dtype, 0);
7309 }
7310 }
7311 break;
7312 default:
7313 errsev(69);
7314 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
7315 break;
7316 }
7317} /* build_array_list */
7318
7319static void
7320add_array_init(ASTLIST *list, int ast, DTYPE dtype, int sptr)
7321{
7322 /* given an array-shaped expression ast, add 'init' items */
7323 ASTLIST newlist;
7324 newlist.head = 0;
7325 newlist.tail = 0;
7326
7327 build_array_list(&newlist, ast, dtype, sptr);
7328 if (newlist.head) {
7329 if (list->head == 0) {
7330 list->head = newlist.head;
7331 } else {
7332 A_RIGHTP(list->tail, newlist.head);
7333 }
7334 list->tail = newlist.tail;
7335 }
7336} /* add_array_init */
7337
7338static ACL *
7339dinit_fill_struct(ASTLIST *list, ACL *aclp, int sdtype, int sptr,
7340 int memberlist, int init_single)
7341{
7342 int i, idx_sptr, aa, tmpcon;
7343 ACL *a;
7344 ACL *b;
7345 INT initval, limitval, stepval, save_conval1;
7346 INT num[2];
7347 ASTLIST newlist = {0, 0};
7348 if (aclp == NULL)
7349 return NULL;
7350#if DEBUG
7351 if (DBGBIT(3, 64))
7352 dumpacl("dinit_fill_struct", aclp, gbl.dbgfil);
7353#endif
7354 for (a = aclp; a; a = a->next) {
7355 SST *stkp;
7356 DOINFO *doinfo;
7357 int aast, dtype, ddtype, member, count;
7358 if (memberlist && sptr == 0 && !out_of_elements_message) {
7359 interr("dinit_fill_struct, out of derived type elements", 0, 0);
7360 out_of_elements_message = TRUE;
7361 }
7362 switch (a->id) {
7363 case AC_AST:
7364 dtype = A_DTYPEG(a->u1.ast);
7365 aast = a->u1.ast;
7366 if (A_TYPEG(aast) == A_ID && PARAMG(A_SPTRG(aast))) {
7367 if (PARAMVALG(A_SPTRG(aast))) {
7368 add_init(list, A_LEFTG(PARAMVALG(A_SPTRG(aast))), dtype, sptr);
7369 }
7370 } else {
7371 aast = dinit_getval(aast, sdtype);
7372 add_init(list, aast, dtype, sptr);
7373 }
7374 break;
7375 case AC_EXPR:
7376 /* get the AST */
7377 stkp = a->u1.stkp;
7378 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stkp);
7379 a->repeatc = a->size = 0;
7380 aast = SST_ASTG(stkp);
7381 if (SST_IDG(stkp) == S_ACONST) {
7382 interr("dinit_fill_struct, unexpected S_ACONST", 0, 3);
7383 aast = 0;
7384 } else if (A_TYPEG(aast) == A_INTR || A_TYPEG(aast) == A_BINOP) {
7385 ACL *iaclp = construct_acl_from_ast(aast, sdtype, 0);
7386 if (!iaclp) {
7387 return 0;
7388 }
7389 iaclp = eval_init_expr_item(iaclp);
7390 if (!iaclp) {
7391 return 0;
7392 }
7393 newlist.head = newlist.tail = 0;
7394 dinit_fill_struct(&newlist, iaclp, sdtype, sptr, memberlist,
7395 init_single);
7396 append_init_list(list, &newlist);
7397 } else {
7398 int save;
7399 aast = SST_ASTG(stkp);
7400 if (A_SHAPEG(aast) != 0 || A_TYPEG(aast) == A_SUBSCR) {
7401 save = list->tail;
7402 add_array_init(list, aast, dtype, sptr);
7403 if (save) {
7404 a->repeatc = A_RIGHTG(save);
7405 } else {
7406 a->repeatc = list->head;
7407 }
7408 a->size = list->tail;
7409 } else if (A_TYPEG(aast) == A_ID && PARAMVALG(A_SPTRG(aast))) {
7410 aa = mk_init(PARAMVALG(A_SPTRG(aast)), dtype);
7411 A_SPTRP(aa, sptr);
7412 add_init(list, aast, dtype, sptr);
7413 } else {
7414 if (DTY(sdtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
7415 aast = dinit_getval1(aast, DTY(sdtype + 1));
7416 } else
7417 aast = dinit_getval1(aast, sdtype);
7418
7419 if (A_TYPEG(SST_ASTG(stkp)) == A_CNST &&
7420 A_DTYPEG(aast) != A_DTYPEG(SST_ASTG(stkp))) {
7421 /* constant initialization value needed type conversion,
7422 * rewrite the ACL instance to use converted value */
7423 a->id = AC_AST;
7424 a->dtype = sdtype;
7425 a->u1.ast = aast;
7426 }
7427 add_init(list, aast, dtype, sptr);
7428 }
7429 }
7430 break;
7431 case AC_IEXPR:
7432 if (POINTERG(sptr)) {
7433 /* maybe this should always be done */
7434 a->sptr = sptr;
7435 }
7436 b = eval_init_expr_item(a);
7437 if (!b) {
7438 return 0;
7439 }
7440 newlist.head = newlist.tail = 0;
7441 if (POINTERG(sptr)) {
7442 /* And, MUST be ST_MEMBER */
7443 b = dinit_fill_struct(&newlist, b, b->dtype, MIDNUMG(sptr), 1,
7444 init_single);
7445 } else {
7446 if (DTY(b->dtype) == TY_ARRAY)
7447 dtype = b->dtype;
7448 else
7449 dtype = sdtype;
7450 b = dinit_fill_struct(&newlist, b, dtype, sptr, 0, init_single);
7451 }
7452 append_init_list(list, &newlist);
7453 break;
7454 case AC_ACONST:
7455 dtype = a->dtype;
7456 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_ARRAY) {
7457 interr("dinit_fill_struct, expecting ARRAY type", dtype, 1);
7458 ddtype = dtype;
7459 } else {
7460 ddtype = DDTG(sdtype);
7461 }
7462 newlist.head = newlist.tail = 0;
7463 b = dinit_fill_struct(&newlist, a->subc, ddtype, sptr, 0, FALSE);
7464 if (list && DTY(sdtype) != TY_ARRAY)
7465 append_init_list(list, &newlist);
7466 else {
7467 if (DTY(ddtype) == TY_DERIVED) {
7468 add_init(list, newlist.head, ddtype, sptr);
7469 } else
7470 add_init(list, newlist.head, dtype, sptr);
7471 }
7472 break;
7473 case AC_SCONST:
7474 dtype = a->dtype;
7475 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_DERIVED) {
7476 interr("dinit_fill_struct, expecting DERIVED type", dtype, 1);
7477 member = 0;
7478 ddtype = 0;
7479 } else {
7480 member = DTY(dtype + 1);
7481 if (member) {
7482 ddtype = DTYPEG(member);
7483 if (no_data_components(ddtype)) {
7484 member = next_member(member);
7485 if (member)
7486 ddtype = DTYPEG(member);
7487 else
7488 ddtype = 0;
7489 }
7490 } else {
7491 ddtype = 0;
7492 }
7493 }
7494 newlist.head = newlist.tail = 0;
7495 b = dinit_fill_struct(&newlist, a->subc, ddtype, member, 1, member != 0);
7496 add_init(list, newlist.head, dtype, sptr);
7497 if (sdtype && dtype != sdtype) {
7498 /* coerce */
7499 interr("initialization coercion needed", sdtype, 1);
7500 }
7501 break;
7502 case AC_IDO:
7503 if (sem.top == &sem.dostack[MAX_DOSTACK]) {
7504 /* nesting maximum exceeded. */
7505 errsev(34);
7506 return NULL;
7507 }
7508 doinfo = a->u1.doinfo;
7509 ++sem.top;
7510 newlist.head = newlist.tail = 0;
7511 idx_sptr = doinfo->index_var;
7512 initval = dinit_eval(doinfo->init_expr);
7513 limitval = dinit_eval(doinfo->limit_expr);
7514 stepval = dinit_eval(doinfo->step_expr);
7515 save_conval1 = CONVAL1G(idx_sptr);
7516 if (stepval >= 0) {
7517 for (i = initval; i <= limitval; i += stepval) {
7518 switch (DTY(DTYPEG(idx_sptr))) {
7519 case TY_INT8:
7520 case TY_LOG8:
7521 ISZ_2_INT64(i, num);
7522 tmpcon = getcon(num, DTYPEG(idx_sptr));
7523 CONVAL1P(idx_sptr, tmpcon);
7524 break;
7525 default:
7526 CONVAL1P(idx_sptr, i);
7527 break;
7528 }
7529 b = dinit_fill_struct(&newlist, a->subc, sdtype, sptr, 0, sptr != 0);
7530 }
7531 } else {
7532 for (i = initval; i >= limitval; i += stepval) {
7533 switch (DTY(DTYPEG(idx_sptr))) {
7534 case TY_INT8:
7535 case TY_LOG8:
7536 ISZ_2_INT64(i, num);
7537 tmpcon = getcon(num, DTYPEG(idx_sptr));
7538 CONVAL1P(idx_sptr, tmpcon);
7539 break;
7540 default:
7541 CONVAL1P(idx_sptr, i);
7542 break;
7543 }
7544 b = dinit_fill_struct(&newlist, a->subc, sdtype, sptr, 0, sptr != 0);
7545 }
7546 }
7547 append_init_list(list, &newlist);
7548 CONVAL1P(idx_sptr, save_conval1);
7549 --sem.top;
7550 break;
7551 case AC_REPEAT:
7552 count = a->u1.count;
7553 while (--count >= 0) {
7554 b = dinit_fill_struct(list, a->subc, sdtype, sptr, 0, sptr != 0);
7555 }
7556 break;
7557 case AC_CONVAL:
7558 if (a->conval == 0) {
7559 aast = a->u1.ast;
7560 } else if (DT_ISWORD(a->dtype)) {
7561 aast = mk_cval1(a->conval, a->dtype);
7562 } else {
7563 aast = mk_cnst(a->conval);
7564 }
7565 dtype = A_DTYPEG(aast);
7566 aast = dinit_getval(aast, sdtype);
7567 add_init(list, aast, dtype, sptr);
7568 break;
7569 }
7570 if (memberlist && sptr) {
7571 /* move 'sptr' along the member list */
7572 if (STYPEG(sptr) != ST_MEMBER) {
7573 interr("dinit_fill_struct, expecing member", sptr, 1);
7574 return a->next;
7575 }
7576 sptr = next_member(sptr);
7577 if (sptr <= NOSYM) {
7578 return a->next;
7579 }
7580 sdtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
7581 } else if (init_single) {
7582 /* initializing a single symbol */
7583 return a->next;
7584 }
7585 }
7586 return NULL;
7587} /* dinit_fill_struct */
7588
7589void
7590dinit_struct_param(SPTR sptr, ACL *sconst, DTYPE dtype)
7591{
7592 ASTLIST newlist;
7593 /* set up 'sptr' as having a parameter value */
7594 PARAMP(sptr, 1);
7595 /* put the 'parameter' value in the ASTs */
7596 out_of_elements_message = FALSE;
7597 sem.top = &sem.dostack[0];
7598 newlist.head = newlist.tail = 0;
7599 dinit_fill_struct(&newlist, sconst, dtype, sptr, 0, sptr != 0);
7600 PARAMVALP(sptr, newlist.head);
7601} /* dinit_struct_param */
7602
7603/** \brief In DATA statement, do the stuff in dinit_struct_const in two steps.
7604 */
7605ACL *
7606dinit_struct_vals(ACL *sconst, DTYPE dtype, SPTR component_sptr)
7607{
7608 SST *item_stkp;
7609 int ast;
7610 ACL *aclp;
7611 ACL *ict; /* Initializer Constant Tree */
7612 ACL *last;
7613 ACL *first;
7614 /* need to check for number of entries */
7615 /* allocate and init an Initializer Constant Tree */
7616 int count = 0;
7617 SPTR member_sptr = DTY(dtype + 1);
7618 SPTR sptr = component_sptr != NOSYM ? component_sptr : DTY(dtype + 3);
7619 last = NULL;
7620 for (aclp = sconst->subc; aclp != NULL; aclp = aclp->next) {
7621 if (aclp->id == AC_ACONST) {
7622 ict = aclp;
7623 ict->sptr = member_sptr;
7624 } else if (aclp->id == AC_SCONST) {
7625 ict = dinit_struct_vals(aclp, aclp->dtype, member_sptr);
7626 ict->sptr = member_sptr;
7627 } else if (aclp->id == AC_EXPR && SST_IDG(aclp->u1.stkp) == S_IDENT &&
7628 STYPEG(SST_SYMG(aclp->u1.stkp)) == ST_PD &&
7629 PDNUMG(SST_SYMG(aclp->u1.stkp)) == PD_null) {
7630 ict = SST_ACLG(aclp->u1.stkp);
7631 } else {
7632 item_stkp = aclp->u1.stkp;
7633 ast = item_stkp->ast;
7634 if (!ast || (!A_ALIASG(ast) &&
7635 (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_INTR && A_OPTYPEG(ast) != I_NULL))) {
7636 int errsptr;
7637 errsptr = SST_SYMG(item_stkp);
7638 if (ast == 0 && errsptr) {
7639 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno,
7640 "DATA initialization with nonconstant value -",
7641 SYMNAME(errsptr));
7642 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
7643 } else {
7644 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno,
7645 "DATA initialization with nonconstant expression", "");
7646 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
7647 return NULL;
7648 }
7649 ict = NULL;
7650 } else {
7651 ict = GET_ACL(15);
7652 ict->id = AC_AST;
7653 ict->next = NULL;
7654 ict->subc = NULL;
7655 ict->u1.ast = SST_ASTG(item_stkp); /* the data constant */
7656 ict->repeatc = 0; /* no repeat count */
7657 ict->sptr = member_sptr;
7658 ict->dtype = SST_DTYPEG(item_stkp);
7659 }
7660 }
7661 if (ict != NULL) {
7662 if (last == NULL)
7663 first = ict;
7664 else
7665 last->next = ict;
7666 last = ict;
7667 }
7668 if (member_sptr != 0)
7669 member_sptr = SYMLKG(member_sptr);
7670 }
7671 ict = GET_ACL(15);
7672 ict->id = AC_SCONST;
7673 ict->next = NULL;
7674 ict->subc = first;
7675 ict->u1.ast = count;
7676 ict->repeatc = astb.bnd.one; /* repeat count */
7677 ict->sptr = sptr;
7678 ict->dtype = dtype;
7679 return ict;
7680}
7681
7682/** \brief Create an initialization node for a variable reference in a data
7683 statement.
7684
7685 If the variable reference is an array section (tpr1652) an implied do is
7686 generated for each subscript which is a triple. For example, the array
7687 section:
7688 <pre>
7689 A(i1, L2:U2, L3:U3, i4)
7690 </pre>
7691 is transformed into:
7692 <pre>
7693 ( ( A(i1, j2, j3, i4) j2 = L2, U2 ), j3 = L3, U3 )
7694 </pre>
7695 Each triple subscript is replaced by an implied do index variable, and
7696 the expressions in the triplet becomes the bounds of the implied do.
7697 Sections are to be initialized in array element order (i.e., column major).
7698 An implied do nest is produced by a left to right scan of the subscripts
7699 (the leftmost triple represents the innermost implied do).
7700
7701 If the variable reference is a member of a whole array, turn the whole
7702 array reference into a subscripted reference where each subscript is
7703 a triple. Then, the subscripted referenced is handled as described
7704 above.
7705
7706 For other variable references, a single initialization node is created.
7707 */
7708VAR *
7709dinit_varref(SST *stkp)
7710{
7711 VAR *ivl;
7712 int ast;
7713 ITEM *mhd, *p; /* mhd = "member of the whole array" ? */
7714 int i;
7715 int ndim;
7716 int subs[MAXDIMS];
7717
7718 mhd = NULL;
7719 for (ast = SST_ASTG(stkp); A_TYPEG(ast) == A_MEM; ast = A_PARENTG(ast)) {
7720 p = (ITEM *)getitem(0, sizeof(ITEM));
7721 p->next = mhd;
7722 p->ast = ast;
7723 mhd = p;
7724 }
7725 if (mhd && A_TYPEG(ast) == A_ID && DTY(A_DTYPEG(ast)) == TY_ARRAY) {
7726 int ss;
7727 ADSC *ad;
7728 ss = A_SPTRG(ast);
7729 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(ss));
7730 ndim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
7731 i = 0;
7732 while (i < ndim) {
7733 subs[i] = mk_triple(AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_UPAST(ad, i), 0);
7734 i++;
7735 }
7736 ast = mk_subscr(ast, subs, ndim, A_DTYPEG(ast));
7737 }
7738 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSCR) {
7739 /*
7740 * the variable reference is subscripted; check if any of the subcripts
7741 * are triples.
7742 */
7743 int asd;
7744 int triple[MAXDIMS];
7745 LOGICAL any_triple;
7746 int newast;
7747
7748 any_triple = FALSE;
7749 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
7750 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
7751 for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
7752 /*
7753 * If a subscript in dimension 'i' (zero-based) is a triple:
7754 * 1. save the ast of the triple in triple[i].
7755 * 2. create an integer variable which will be the implied do
7756 * index in dimension 'i'.
7757 * 3. create the ast of the do variable which will be the
7758 * subscript in dimension 'i' and save in subs[i].
7759 *
7760 * Otherwise, triple[i] is set to 0 (subscript in the dimension
7761 * 'i' is not a triple).
7762 */
7763 subs[i] = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
7764 if (A_TYPEG(subs[i]) == A_TRIPLE) {
7765 any_triple = TRUE;
7766 triple[i] = subs[i];
7767 subs[i] = mk_id(get_temp(astb.bnd.dtype));
7768 } else
7769 triple[i] = 0;
7770 }
7771 if (any_triple) {
7772 VAR *newivl;
7773 VAR *endl;
7774 /*
7775 * Create a subscripted reference, where the triples are replaced
7776 * by their respective index variables; the other subscripts
7777 * are used as is. This subscripted reference becomes the object
7778 * in a variable reference initialization node.
7779 */
7780 newast = mk_subscr(A_LOPG(ast), subs, ndim, DTY(A_DTYPEG(ast) + 1));
7781 for (p = mhd; p != NULL; p = p->next) {
7782 newast = mk_member(newast, A_MEMG(p->ast), A_DTYPEG(p->ast));
7783 }
7784 ivl = (VAR *)getitem(15, sizeof(VAR));
7785 ivl->id = Varref;
7786 ivl->u.varref.ptr = newast;
7787 ivl->u.varref.id = S_LVALUE;
7788 ivl->u.varref.dtype = A_DTYPEG(newast);
7789 ivl->u.varref.shape = A_SHAPEG(newast);
7790 ivl->u.varref.subt = NULL;
7791 ivl->next = NULL;
7792 if (SCG(SST_LSYMG(stkp)) == SC_BASED) {
7793 error(116, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(SST_LSYMG(stkp)), "(DATA)");
7794 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
7795 }
7796 /* keep track of the 'end' (outer) init. node; note that 'ivl'
7797 * represents the current init. node
7798 */
7799 endl = ivl;
7800 for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
7801 if (triple[i]) {
7802 /* build a doend element for the dinit var list */
7803 newivl = (VAR *)getitem(15, sizeof(VAR));
7804 endl->next = newivl; /* current -> Doend */
7805 newivl->id = Doend;
7806 newivl->next = NULL;
7807 endl = newivl; /* end of this do is the Doend */
7808 /*
7809 * Create the dostart element, link it to the doend element,
7810 * and link all in the order dostart -> current node ->
7811 * doend.
7812 */
7813 newivl->u.doend.dostart = (VAR *)getitem(15, sizeof(VAR));
7814 newivl = newivl->u.doend.dostart;
7815 newivl->id = Dostart;
7816 newivl->u.dostart.indvar = subs[i];
7817 newivl->u.dostart.lowbd = A_LBDG(triple[i]);
7818 newivl->u.dostart.upbd = A_UPBDG(triple[i]);
7819 newivl->u.dostart.step = A_STRIDEG(triple[i]);
7820 newivl->next = ivl; /* Dostart -> current */
7821 ivl = newivl; /* Dostart is the new current node */
7822 }
7823 }
7824 SST_VLBEGP(stkp, ivl); /* Dostart of the outermost implied do*/
7825 SST_VLENDP(stkp, endl); /* Doend of the outermost implied do*/
7826 sem.dinit_data = TRUE;
7827 return NULL; /* tell semant that a section was initialized */
7828 }
7829 }
7830 /* build a single element for the dinit var list */
7831 ivl = (VAR *)getitem(15, sizeof(VAR));
7832 ivl->id = Varref;
7833 ivl->u.varref.ptr = SST_ASTG(stkp);
7834 ivl->u.varref.id = SST_IDG(stkp);
7835 ivl->u.varref.dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stkp);
7836 ivl->u.varref.shape = SST_SHAPEG(stkp);
7837 ivl->u.varref.subt = NULL;
7838 ivl->next = NULL;
7839 return ivl;
7840}
7841
7842/** \brief Get a compiler temporary of any scalar dtype.
7843 */
7844SPTR
7845get_temp(DTYPE dtype)
7846{
7847 SPTR sptr;
7848 DTYPE dt;
7849#if DEBUG
7850 assert(DT_ISSCALAR(dtype) || DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED,
7851 "get_temp:nonscalar dt", dtype, 3);
7852#endif
7853 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR || DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR)
7854 return get_ch_temp(dtype);
7855
7856 if (!sem.temps_reset) {
7857 BZERO(temps_ctr, char, sizeof(temps_ctr));
7858 sem.temps_reset = TRUE;
7859 }
7860
7861 do {
7862 sptr = getcctmp_sc('i', TEMPS_CTR(0), ST_VAR, dtype, sem.sc);
7863 dt = DTYPEG(sptr);
7864 } while (dt != dtype);
7865
7866 return sptr;
7867}
7868
7869DTYPE
7870get_temp_dtype(DTYPE dtype, int expr)
7871{
7872 if (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_ASSNCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR ||
7873 dtype == DT_DEFERNCHAR) {
7874 int len;
7875 if (A_TYPEG(expr) == A_INTR && A_OPTYPEG(expr) == I_TRIM)
7876 len = ast_intr(I_LEN_TRIM, astb.bnd.dtype, 1, ARGT_ARG(A_ARGSG(expr), 0));
7877 else {
7878 len = ast_intr(I_LEN, astb.bnd.dtype, 1, expr);
7879 }
7880 dtype = get_type(2, DTY(dtype), len);
7881 }
7882 return dtype;
7883}
7884
7885SPTR
7886get_itemp(DTYPE dtype)
7887{
7888 SPTR sptr = getccsym_sc('i', sem.itemps++, ST_VAR, sem.sc);
7889 DTYPEP(sptr, dtype);
7890 return sptr;
7891}
7892
7893static void
7894allocate_temp(SPTR sptr)
7895{
7896 DTYPE dtype;
7897 int subs[MAXDIMS], i, n, ast;
7898
7899 add_p_dealloc_item(sptr);
7900
7901 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
7902 ast = mk_id(sptr);
7903 /* char length variable? */
7904 if (DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR || DTYG(dtype) == TY_NCHAR) {
7905 int cvlen, len, rhs, asn, dty;
7906 dty = DDTG(dtype);
7907 cvlen = CVLENG(sptr);
7908 if (cvlen) {
7909 len = mk_id(cvlen);
7910 rhs = DTY(dty + 1);
7911 rhs = mk_convert(rhs, DTYPEG(cvlen));
7912 rhs = ast_intr(I_MAX, DTYPEG(cvlen), 2, rhs, mk_cval(0, DTYPEG(cvlen)));
7913 asn = mk_assn_stmt(len, rhs, DTYPEG(cvlen));
7914 (void)add_stmt(asn);
7915 }
7916 }
7917 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
7918 ADD_DEFER(dtype) = 1;
7919 /* insert allocate statement */
7920 n = ADD_NUMDIM(dtype);
7921 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
7922 subs[i] = mk_triple(ADD_LWBD(dtype, i), ADD_UPBD(dtype, i), 0);
7923 }
7924 ast = mk_subscr(ast, subs, n, dtype);
7925 }
7926 gen_alloc_dealloc(TK_ALLOCATE, ast, 0);
7927} /* allocate_temp */
7928
7929/** \brief Get a compiler array temporary of type dtype.
7930 */
7931SPTR
7932get_arr_temp(DTYPE dtype, LOGICAL nodesc, LOGICAL alloc_deferred,
7933 LOGICAL constructor)
7934{
7935 SPTR sptr;
7936 int needalloc;
7937 SC_KIND sc = sem.sc;
7938 DTYPE dt = DTY(dtype + 1);
7939
7940 if (DTY(dt) == TY_CHAR || DTY(dt) == TY_NCHAR)
7941 return get_ch_temp(dtype);
7942 if (!sem.temps_reset) {
7943 BZERO(temps_ctr, char, sizeof(temps_ctr));
7944 sem.temps_reset = TRUE;
7945 }
7946
7947 /*
7948 * Examine dtype to determine if an allocatable temp is needed:
7949 * o has deferred shape, or
7950 * o the size is not constant.
7951 *
7952 * If an allocatable temp is needed, its storage class is always
7953 * SC_LOCAL or SC_PRIVATE.
7954 */
7955 needalloc = 0;
7956 if (ADD_DEFER(dtype)) {
7957 needalloc = 1;
7958 } else {
7959 int d;
7960 /* if the size is not constant, mark it as adjustable */
7961 for (d = 0; d < ADD_NUMDIM(dtype); ++d) {
7962 int lb, ub;
7963 lb = ADD_LWBD(dtype, d);
7964 if (lb && A_ALIASG(lb) == 0) {
7965 needalloc = 1;
7966 break;
7967 }
7968 ub = ADD_UPBD(dtype, d);
7969 if (ub && A_ALIASG(ub) == 0) {
7970 needalloc = 1;
7971 break;
7972 }
7973 }
7974 }
7975 if (needalloc && sc != SC_PRIVATE)
7976 sc = SC_LOCAL;
7977
7978 do {
7979 int tmpc;
7980 if (!needalloc)
7981 tmpc = TEMPS_CTR(1);
7982 else
7983 tmpc = TEMPS_STK(1);
7984 if (constructor)
7985 /* Creating a temporary for an array constructor within an OpenACC region.
7986 * Mark this by using letter 'x' in the name of the temporary so that it
7987 * can be identified by the accelerator backend.
7988 * Caution: Any change to this naming scheme must also be reflected in
7989 * routine add_implicit_private in accel.c.
7990 */
7991 sptr = getcctmp_sc('x', tmpc, ST_ARRAY, dtype, sc);
7992 else
7993 sptr = getcctmp_sc('a', tmpc, ST_ARRAY, dtype, sc);
7994 dt = DTYPEG(sptr);
7995 if (DTY(dt + 1) == DTY(dtype + 1) && ADD_DEFER(dtype) == ADD_DEFER(dt) &&
7996 nodesc == NODESCG(sptr) && conformable(dt, dtype))
7997 break;
7998 } while (dt != dtype);
7999
8000 if (needalloc) {
8001 ALLOCP(sptr, 1);
8002 if (!alloc_deferred && ADD_DEFER(dtype)) {
8003 /* if deferred shape, temp will be treated as allocatable */
8004 ;
8005 } else if (ALLOCATE_ARRAYS) {
8006 int d;
8007 /* if the size is not constant, allocate it, but
8008 * first ensure that each dimension has a lower bound.
8009 */
8010 for (d = 0; d < ADD_NUMDIM(dtype); ++d) {
8011 if (ADD_LWBD(dtype, d) == 0)
8012 ADD_LWBD(dtype, d) = astb.bnd.one;
8013 }
8014 allocate_temp(sptr);
8015 }
8016 }
8017 NODESCP(sptr, nodesc);
8018 return sptr;
8019}
8020
8021/** \brief Get a compiler-created allocatable array temp to represent the
8022 result of run-time function computing the adjustl/adjustr intrinsic.
8023
8024 The result of the run-time is the length (which we don't actually use), but
8025 it's needed to effect array/forall processing in the compiler. Eventually,
8026 in outconv.c, the temp is discarded, as well as the return value of the
8027 runtime routine.
8028 */
8029SPTR
8030get_adjlr_arr_temp(DTYPE dtype)
8031{
8032 SPTR sptr;
8033 ALLOCATE_ARRAYS = 0; /* no need to generate an allocate of the temp*/
8034 sptr = get_arr_temp(dtype, TRUE, FALSE, FALSE);
8035 ALLOCATE_ARRAYS = 1;
8036 return sptr;
8037}
8038
8039/** \brief Get a compiler array temporary of from a shape of an ast.
8040 */
8041SPTR
8042get_shape_arr_temp(int arg)
8043{
8044 int shape = A_SHAPEG(arg);
8045 DTYPE dtype = get_shape_arraydtype(shape, DTY(A_DTYPEG(arg) + 1));
8046 SPTR tmp = get_arr_temp(dtype, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE);
8047 if (sem.arrdim.ndefer)
8048 gen_allocate_array(tmp);
8049 return tmp;
8050}
8051
8052/** \brief Get a character compiler temporary of type dtype.
8053 */
8054SPTR
8055get_ch_temp(DTYPE dtype)
8056{
8057 SPTR sptr;
8058 DTYPE dt;
8059 SYMTYPE stype;
8060 int len;
8061 bool needalloc = false;
8062 SC_KIND sc = sem.sc;
8063
8064 if (!sem.temps_reset) {
8065 BZERO(temps_ctr, char, sizeof(temps_ctr));
8066 sem.temps_reset = TRUE;
8067 }
8068
8069 /*
8070 * Examine dtype to determine if an allocatable temp is needed:
8071 * o the length is not a constant, or
8072 * o if array, the size is not constant.
8073 *
8074 * If an allocatable temp is needed, its storage class is always
8075 * SC_LOCAL.
8076 */
8077 dt = DDTG(dtype);
8078 /* This is pretty bogus, _INF_CLEN for temps, ugh. */
8079 if (dt == DT_ASSCHAR || dt == DT_DEFERCHAR) {
8080 dt = get_type(2, TY_CHAR, mk_cval(_INF_CLEN, DT_INT4));
8081 error(310, 2, gbl.lineno,
8082 "Unsafe fixed-length string temporary*500 being used", CNULL);
8083 } else if (dt == DT_ASSNCHAR || dt == DT_DEFERNCHAR) {
8084 dt = get_type(2, TY_NCHAR, mk_cval(_INF_CLEN, DT_INT4));
8085 error(310, 2, gbl.lineno,
8086 "Unsafe fixed-length string temporary*500 being used", CNULL);
8087 }
8088
8089 /* if the length is not a constant, make it 'adjustable' */
8090 len = DTY(dt + 1);
8091 if (A_ALIASG(len) == 0) {
8092 /* will fill in CVLEN field */
8093 needalloc = true;
8094 }
8095 stype = ST_VAR;
8096 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
8097 int d;
8098 /* if the size is not constant, mark it as adjustable */
8099 stype = ST_ARRAY;
8100 for (d = 0; d < ADD_NUMDIM(dtype); ++d) {
8101 int lb, ub;
8102 lb = ADD_LWBD(dtype, d);
8103 if (lb && A_ALIASG(lb) == 0) {
8104 needalloc = true;
8105 break;
8106 }
8107 ub = ADD_UPBD(dtype, d);
8108 if (ub && A_ALIASG(ub) == 0) {
8109 needalloc = true;
8110 break;
8111 }
8112 }
8113 }
8114 if (needalloc)
8115 sc = SC_LOCAL;
8116
8117 do {
8118 int tmpc;
8119 if (!needalloc)
8120 tmpc = TEMPS_CTR(1);
8121 else
8122 tmpc = TEMPS_STK(1);
8123 sptr = getcctmp_sc('s', tmpc, stype, dtype, sc);
8124 dt = DTYPEG(sptr);
8125 } while (dt != dtype);
8126
8127 if (needalloc) {
8128 int clen;
8129 ALLOCP(sptr, 1);
8130 /* if the length is not a constant, make it 'adjustable' */
8131 if (sem.gcvlen && is_deferlenchar_dtype(dtype)) {
8132 clen = ast_intr(I_LEN, astb.bnd.dtype, 1, mk_id(sptr));
8133 } else if (A_ALIASG(len) == 0) {
8134 /* fill in CVLEN field */
8135 ADJLENP(sptr, 1);
8136 if (CVLENG(sptr) == 0) {
8137 clen = sym_get_scalar(SYMNAME(sptr), "len", astb.bnd.dtype);
8138 CVLENP(sptr, clen);
8139 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY)
8140 CCSYMP(clen, 1);
8141 }
8142 }
8143 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
8144 if (ALLOCATE_ARRAYS) {
8145 int d;
8146 /* if the size is not constant, allocate it, but need to
8147 * first ensure that each dimension has a lower bound.
8148 */
8149 for (d = 0; d < ADD_NUMDIM(dtype); ++d) {
8150 if (ADD_LWBD(dtype, d) == 0)
8151 ADD_LWBD(dtype, d) = astb.bnd.one;
8152 }
8153 if (!sem.arrdim.ndefer || ADJLENG(sptr))
8154 allocate_temp(sptr);
8155 }
8156 } else {
8157 allocate_temp(sptr);
8158 }
8159 }
8160 return sptr;
8161}
8162
8163int
8164need_alloc_ch_temp(DTYPE dtype)
8165{
8166 if (sem.use_etmps) {
8167 /*
8168 * if the dtype warrants an allocatable temp, need to add a fake
8169 * etmp entry so that its expression context, such as a relational
8170 * expression, is fully evaluated and assigned to a temp.
8171 */
8172 if (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_ASSNCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR ||
8173 dtype == DT_DEFERNCHAR || !A_ALIASG(DTY(dtype + 1))) {
8174 add_etmp(0);
8175 return 1;
8176 }
8177 }
8178 return 0;
8179}
8180
8181/** \brief Compare \a str and \a pattern like strcmp() but ignoring the case of
8182 str.
8183 \a pattern is all lower case.
8184 */
8185int
8186sem_strcmp(const char *str, const char *pattern)
8187{
8188 const char *p1, *p2;
8189 int ch;
8190
8191 p1 = str;
8192 p2 = pattern;
8193 do {
8194 ch = *p1;
8195 if (ch >= 'A' && ch <= 'Z')
8196 ch += ('a' - 'A'); /* to lower case */
8197 if (ch != *p2)
8198 return (ch - *p2);
8199 if (ch == '\0')
8200 return 0;
8201 p1++;
8202 p2++;
8203 } while (1);
8204}
8205
8206/** \brief Return TRUE if fortran character constant is equal to pattern
8207 (pattern is always uppercase).
8208 */
8209LOGICAL
8210sem_eq_str(int con, const char *pattern)
8211{
8212 char *p1;
8213 const char *p2;
8214 int len;
8215 int c1, c2;
8216
8217 p1 = stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(con);
8218 p2 = pattern;
8219 for (len = string_length(DTYPEG(con)); len > 0; len--) {
8220 c1 = *p1;
8221 if (c1 >= 'a' && c1 <= 'z') /* convert to upper case */
8222 c1 = c1 + ('A' - 'a');
8223 c2 = *p2;
8224 if (c2 == '\0' || c1 != c2)
8225 break;
8226 p1++;
8227 p2++;
8228 }
8229
8230 if (len == 0)
8231 return TRUE;
8232
8233 /* verify that remaining characters of con are blank: */
8234 while (len--)
8235 if (*p1++ != ' ')
8236 return FALSE;
8237 return TRUE;
8238}
8239
8240/** \brief Allocate a temporary, assign it the value, and return the assignment
8241 * ast.
8242 */
8243int
8244sem_tempify(SST *stkptr)
8245{
8246 int argtyp;
8247 SST tmpsst;
8248 int tmpsym;
8249 int assn;
8250 argtyp = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
8251 argtyp = get_temp_dtype(argtyp, SST_ASTG(stkptr));
8252 if (DTY(argtyp) != TY_ARRAY) {
8253 tmpsym = get_temp(argtyp);
8254 } else {
8255 tmpsym = get_arr_temp(argtyp, FALSE, A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(stkptr)), FALSE);
8256 }
8257 mkident(&tmpsst);
8258 SST_SYMP(&tmpsst, tmpsym);
8259 SST_DTYPEP(&tmpsst, argtyp);
8260 assn = assign(&tmpsst, stkptr);
8261 return assn;
8262}
8263
8264/** \brief Update the SWEL list for a `SELECTCASE` construct represented by
8265 the \a doif structure.
8266
8267 A new SWEL item is created for a case value or a range of case
8268 values denoted by the arguments \a lc and \a uc. The order of the items in
8269 the list will correspond to the case values in ascending order.
8270
8271 Kind of case | lc | uc
8272 ---------------|--------|------
8273 case (:c) | c | -1
8274 case (c) | c | 0 (c is a sym pointer)
8275 case (c:) | c | 1
8276 case (c:d) | c | d (c and d are sym pointers)
8277 */
8278void
8279add_case_range(int doif, int lc, int uc)
8280{
8281 SWEL *swel;
8282 int ni;
8283 int bef;
8284 int i;
8285 int (*p_cmp)(int, int);
8286
8287 ni = sem.switch_avl++; /* relative ptr to new SWEL item */
8288 NEED(sem.switch_avl, switch_base, SWEL, sem.switch_size,
8289 sem.switch_size + 300);
8290
8291 /* The first SWEL item's next field locates the head of the list */
8292 bef = DI_SWEL_HD(doif);
8293 if (DT_ISLOG(DI_DTYPE(doif))) {
8294 for (i = switch_base[bef].next; i != 0; i = switch_base[i].next) {
8295 if (switch_base[i].val == lc)
8296 goto dup_error;
8297 }
8298 switch_base[ni].val = lc;
8299 switch_base[ni].next = switch_base[bef].next;
8300 switch_base[bef].next = ni;
8301 return;
8302 }
8303 if (DI_DTYPE(doif) == DT_INT8)
8304 p_cmp = _i8_cmp;
8305 else if (DT_ISINT(DI_DTYPE(doif)))
8306 p_cmp = _i4_cmp;
8307 else {
8308/* character */
8309 if (DTY(DI_DTYPE(doif)) == TY_NCHAR)
8310 p_cmp = _nchar_cmp;
8311 else
8312 p_cmp = _char_cmp;
8313 }
8314
8315 for (i = switch_base[bef].next; i != 0; i = switch_base[i].next) {
8316 swel = switch_base + i;
8317 if ((*p_cmp)(lc, swel->val) < 0) {
8318 /* lc < current case value 'val' */
8319 if (swel->uval == -1)
8320 /* (lc) in (:val) */
8321 goto range_error;
8322 if (uc == 1)
8323 /* (lc :) in (val ...) */
8324 goto range_error;
8325 if (uc > 1 && (*p_cmp)(uc, swel->val) >= 0)
8326 /* (lc:uc), lc < val, uc >= val */
8327 goto range_error;
8328 break;
8329 }
8330 if ((*p_cmp)(lc, swel->val) == 0) {
8331 /* lc == current case value */
8332 if (uc == 0 && swel->uval == 0)
8333 goto dup_error;
8334 goto range_error;
8335 }
8336
8337 /* lc > current case value */
8338 if (uc == -1)
8339 /* lc > val, (:lc) specified */
8340 goto range_error;
8341 if (swel->uval == 1)
8342 /* lc in (val:) */
8343 goto range_error;
8344 if (swel->uval > 1) {
8345 if ((*p_cmp)(lc, swel->uval) <= 0)
8346 /* lc in (val:uval) */
8347 goto range_error;
8348 }
8349 bef = i;
8350 }
8351
8352 /* insert new swel item into list */
8353 switch_base[ni].val = lc;
8354 switch_base[ni].uval = uc;
8355 switch_base[ni].next = switch_base[bef].next;
8356 switch_base[bef].next = ni;
8357 return;
8358
8359dup_error:
8360 error(310, 3, gbl.lineno, "Duplicate case value", CNULL);
8361 sem.switch_avl--;
8362 return;
8363
8364range_error:
8365 error(310, 3, gbl.lineno, "Overlapping case value", CNULL);
8366 sem.switch_avl--;
8367}
8368
8369/** \brief Compare functions whose arguments are pointers to ST_CONST
8370 symbol table entries.
8371 \return a number less than, equal to, or greater than 0, depending on the
8372 comparison
8373 */
8374int
8375_i4_cmp(int l, int r)
8376{
8377 INT v1, v2;
8378
8379 v1 = CONVAL2G(l);
8380 v2 = CONVAL2G(r);
8381 if (v1 < v2)
8382 return -1;
8383 if (v1 == v2)
8384 return 0;
8385 return 1;
8386}
8387
8388int
8389_i8_cmp(int l, int r)
8390{
8391 DBLINT64 v1, v2;
8392
8393 v1[0] = CONVAL1G(l);
8394 v1[1] = CONVAL2G(l);
8395 v2[0] = CONVAL1G(r);
8396 v2[1] = CONVAL2G(r);
8397 return cmp64(v1, v2);
8398}
8399
8400int
8401_char_cmp(int l, int r)
8402{
8403 char *v1, *v2;
8404
8405 v1 = stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(l);
8406 v2 = stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(r);
8407 return strcmp(v1, v2);
8408}
8409
8410int
8411_nchar_cmp(int l, int r)
8412{
8413#define KANJI_BLANK 0xA1A1
8414 int bytes, val1, val2;
8415 int cvlen1, cvlen2;
8416 char *p, *q;
8417
8418 cvlen1 = string_length(DTYPEG(l));
8419 cvlen2 = string_length(DTYPEG(r));
8420 p = stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(l);
8421 q = stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(r);
8422
8423 while (cvlen1 > 0 && cvlen2 > 0) {
8424 val1 = kanji_char((unsigned char *)p, cvlen1, &bytes);
8425 p += bytes, cvlen1 -= bytes;
8426 val2 = kanji_char((unsigned char *)q, cvlen2, &bytes);
8427 q += bytes, cvlen2 -= bytes;
8428 if (val1 != val2)
8429 return (val1 - val2);
8430 }
8431
8432 while (cvlen1 > 0) {
8433 val1 = kanji_char((unsigned char *)p, cvlen1, &bytes);
8434 p += bytes, cvlen1 -= bytes;
8435 if (val1 != KANJI_BLANK)
8436 return (val1 - KANJI_BLANK);
8437 }
8438
8439 while (cvlen2 > 0) {
8440 val2 = kanji_char((unsigned char *)q, cvlen2, &bytes);
8441 q += bytes, cvlen2 -= bytes;
8442 if (val2 != KANJI_BLANK)
8443 return (KANJI_BLANK - val2);
8444 }
8445 return 0;
8446}

8477static void
8478add_to_list(ACL *val, ACL **root)
8479{
8480 ACL *tail;
8481 if (*root) {
8482 for (tail = *root; tail->next; tail = tail->next)
8483 ;
8484 tail->next = val;
8485 } else {
8486 *root = val;
8487 }
8488}
8489
8490static ACL *
8491clone_init_const(ACL *original, int temp)
8492{
8493 ACL *clone;
8494
8495 if (!original)
8496 return NULL;
8497 clone = GET_ACL(15);
8498 *clone = *original;
8499 if (clone->subc) {
8500 clone_init_const_list(clone->subc, temp);
8501 }
8502 if (clone->id == AC_IEXPR) {
8503 if (clone->u1.expr->lop) {
8504 clone_init_const_list(clone->u1.expr->lop, temp);
8505 }
8506 if (clone->u1.expr->rop) {
8507 clone_init_const_list(clone->u1.expr->rop, temp);
8508 }
8509 }
8510 clone->next = NULL;
8511 return clone;
8512}
8513
8514static ACL *
8515clone_init_const_list(ACL *original, int temp)
8516{
8517 ACL *clone;
8518
8519 clone = clone_init_const(original, temp);
8520 for (original = original->next; original; original = original->next) {
8521 add_to_list(clone_init_const(original, temp), &clone);
8522 }
8523 return clone;
8524}

8526static INT
8527get_int_from_init_conval(ACL *aclp)
8528{
8529 INT ret;
8530
8531 if (DT_ISWORD(aclp->dtype)) {
8532 ret = aclp->conval;
8533 } else {
8534 ret = CONVAL2G(aclp->conval);
8535 }
8536 return ret;
8537}
8538
8539/* Intrinsic evaluation routines for data initialization
8540 * Stolen from semfunc.c and hacked to generate ACL initialization values.
8541 */
8542static ACL *
8543eval_ishft(ACL *arg, DTYPE dtype)
8544{
8545 ACL *rslt;
8546 ACL *wrkarg;
8547 ACL *arg2;
8548 INT val;
8549 INT conval;
8550 INT res[4];
8551 INT shftval;
8552
8553 arg = eval_init_expr(arg);
8554 rslt = clone_init_const(arg, TRUE);
8555 wrkarg = (rslt->id == AC_ACONST ? rslt->subc : rslt);
8556 arg2 = arg->next;
8557 shftval = get_int_from_init_conval(arg2);
8558 if (shftval > bits_in(wrkarg->dtype)) {
8559 error(4, 3, gbl.lineno, "ISHFT SHIFT argument too big for I argument\n",
8560 NULL);
8561 return 0;
8562 }
8563
8564 for (; wrkarg; wrkarg = wrkarg->next) {
8565 val = get_int_from_init_conval(wrkarg);
8566 switch (size_of(wrkarg->dtype)) {
8567 case 2:
8568 val = get_int_from_init_conval(wrkarg);
8569 if (shftval >= 0) {
8570 if (shftval >= 16)
8571 conval = 0;
8572 else {
8573 conval = ULSHIFT(val, shftval);
8574 conval = ULSHIFT(conval, 16);
8575 conval = ARSHIFT(conval, 16);
8576 }
8577 } else {
8578 if (shftval <= -16)
8579 conval = 0;
8580 else {
8581 val &= 0xffff;
8582 conval = URSHIFT(val, -shftval);
8583 }
8584 }
8585 conval = cngcon(conval, DT_WORD, DDTG(dtype));
8586 break;
8587 case 4:
8588 /*
8589 * because this ilm is used for the ISHFT intrinsic, count
8590 * is defined for values -32 to 32; some hw (i.e., n10) shifts
8591 * by cnt mod 32.
8592 */
8593 val = get_int_from_init_conval(wrkarg);
8594 if (shftval >= 0) {
8595 if (shftval >= 32)
8596 conval = 0;
8597 else
8598 conval = ULSHIFT(val, shftval);
8599 } else {
8600 if (shftval <= -32)
8601 conval = 0;
8602 else
8603 conval = URSHIFT(val, -shftval);
8604 }
8605 conval = cngcon(conval, DT_WORD, DDTG(dtype));
8606
8607 break;
8608 case 8:
8609 /* val and shftval are symbol pointers */
8610 /* get the value for shftval */
8611 res[0] = CONVAL1G(wrkarg->conval);
8612 res[1] = CONVAL2G(wrkarg->conval);
8613 if (shftval >= 0) {
8614 if (shftval >= 64) {
8615 res[0] = 0;
8616 res[1] = 0;
8617 } else if (shftval >= 32) {
8618 /* shift val by 32 bits or more */
8619 res[0] = ULSHIFT(res[1], shftval - 32);
8620 res[1] = 0;
8621 } else {
8622 /* shift by less than 32 bits; shift high-order
8623 * bits of low-order word into high-order word */
8624 res[0] = ULSHIFT(res[0], shftval) | URSHIFT(res[1], 32 - shftval);
8625 res[1] = ULSHIFT(res[1], shftval);
8626 }
8627 } else {
8628 shftval = -shftval;
8629 if (shftval >= 64) {
8630 res[0] = 0;
8631 res[1] = 0;
8632 } else if (shftval >= 32) {
8633 /* shift val by 32 bits or more */
8634 res[1] = URSHIFT(res[0], shftval - 32);
8635 res[0] = 0;
8636 } else {
8637 /* shift by less than 32 bits; shift low-order
8638 * bits of high-order word into low-order word */
8639 res[1] = URSHIFT(res[1], shftval) | ULSHIFT(res[0], 32 - shftval);
8640 res[0] = URSHIFT(res[0], shftval);
8641 }
8642 }
8643 conval = getcon(res, DT_INT8);
8644
8645 break;
8646 }
8647 wrkarg->id = AC_CONVAL;
8648 wrkarg->conval = conval;
8649 wrkarg->dtype = dtype;
8650 }
8651
8652 return rslt;
8653}
8654
8655#define INTINTRIN2(iname, ent, op) \
8656 static ACL *ent(ACL *arg, DTYPE dtype) \
8657 { \
8658 ACL *arg1 = eval_init_expr_item(arg); \
8659 ACL *arg2 = eval_init_expr_item(arg->next); \
8660 ACL *rslt = clone_init_const(arg1, TRUE); \
8661 arg1 = rslt->id == AC_ACONST ? rslt->subc : rslt; \
8662 arg2 = arg2->id == AC_ACONST ? arg2->subc : arg2; \
8663 for (; arg1; arg1 = arg1->next, arg2 = arg2->next) { \
8664 int con1 = arg1->conval; \
8665 int con2 = arg2->conval; \
8666 int num1[2], num2[2], res[2], conval; \
8667 if (DT_ISWORD(arg1->dtype)) { \
8668 num1[0] = 0, num1[1] = con1; \
8669 } else { \
8670 num1[0] = CONVAL1G(con1), num1[1] = CONVAL2G(con1); \
8671 } \
8672 if (DT_ISWORD(arg2->dtype)) { \
8673 num2[0] = 0, num2[1] = con2; \
8674 } else { \
8675 num2[0] = CONVAL1G(con2), num2[1] = CONVAL2G(con2); \
8676 } \
8677 res[0] = num1[0] op num2[0]; \
8678 res[1] = num1[1] op num2[1]; \
8679 conval = DT_ISWORD(dtype) ? res[1] : getcon(res, DT_INT8); \
8680 arg1->conval = conval; \
8681 arg1->dtype = dtype; \
8682 } \
8683 return rslt; \
8684 }
8685
8686INTINTRIN2("iand", eval_iand, &)
8687INTINTRIN2("ior", eval_ior, |)
8688INTINTRIN2("ieor", eval_ieor, ^)
8689
8690static ACL *
8691eval_ichar(ACL *arg, DTYPE dtype)
8692{
8693 ACL *rslt;
8694 ACL *wrkarg;
8695 int srcdty;
8696 int rsltdtype = DDTG(dtype);
8697 int clen;
8698 INT c;
8699 int dum;
8700
8701 rslt = arg = eval_init_expr(arg);
8702 wrkarg = (rslt->id == AC_ACONST ? rslt->subc : rslt);
8703 srcdty = DTY(wrkarg->dtype);
8704 for (; wrkarg; wrkarg = wrkarg->next) {
8705 if (srcdty == TY_NCHAR) {
8706 c = CONVAL1G(wrkarg->conval);
8707 clen = size_of(DTYPEG(c));
8708 c = kanji_char((unsigned char *)stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(c), clen, &dum);
8709 } else {
8710 c = stb.n_base[CONVAL1G(wrkarg->conval)] & 0xff;
8711 }
8712 if (DTY(rsltdtype) == TY_INT8) {
8713 INT res[4];
8714 INT conval;
8715 res[0] = 0;
8716 res[1] = c;
8717 conval = getcon(res, DT_INT8);
8718 dtype = DT_INT8;
8719 wrkarg->conval = A_SPTRG(mk_cval1(conval, dtype));
8720 } else {
8721 wrkarg->conval = c;
8722 }
8723 wrkarg->id = AC_CONVAL;
8724 wrkarg->dtype = rsltdtype;
8725 }
8726 if (rslt->id == AC_ACONST) {
8727 rslt->dtype = dup_array_dtype(arg->dtype);
8728 DTY(rslt->dtype + 1) = dtype;
8729 } else
8730 rslt->dtype = dtype;
8731 return rslt;
8732}

8734static ACL *
8735eval_char(ACL *arg, DTYPE dtype)
8736{
8737 ACL *rslt;
8738 ACL *wrkarg;
8739 char c;
8740 int sptr;
8741
8742 rslt = arg = eval_init_expr(arg);
8743 wrkarg = (rslt->id == AC_ACONST ? rslt->subc : rslt);
8744 for (; wrkarg; wrkarg = wrkarg->next) {
8745 c = get_int_from_init_conval(wrkarg);
8746 sptr = getstring(&c, 1);
8747 wrkarg->dtype = dtype;
8748 wrkarg->conval = sptr;
8749 wrkarg->u1.ast = mk_cnst(sptr);
8750 }
8751 return rslt;
8752}
