10934
10935static INT
10936get_const_from_ast(int ast)
10937{
10938 DTYPE dtype = A_DTYPEG(ast);
10939 INT c = 0;
10940
10941 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_ID) {
10942
10943 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR || DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR) {
10944 c = A_SPTRG(ast);
10945 } else {
10946 c = CONVAL1G(A_SPTRG(ast));
10947 }
10948 } else if (A_ALIASG(ast)) {
10949 if (DT_ISWORD(A_DTYPEG(ast))) {
10950 c = CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(A_ALIASG(ast)));
10951 } else {
10952 c = A_SPTRG(A_ALIASG(ast));
10953 }
10954 } else {
10955 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_BINOP || A_TYPEG(ast) == A_INTR) {
10956 return const_eval(ast);
10957 }
10958 interr("get_const_from_ast: can't get const value", 0, 3);
10959 }
10960
10961 return c;
10962}
10963
10964static struct {
10965 ACL *root;
10966 ACL *roottail;
10967 ACL *arrbase;
10968 int ndims;
10969 struct {
10970 DTYPE dtype;
10971 ISZ_T idx;
10972 ACL *subscr_base;
10973 ISZ_T lowb;
10974 ISZ_T upb;
10975 ISZ_T stride;
10976 } sub[MAXDIMS];
10977 struct {
10978 ISZ_T lowb;
10979 ISZ_T upb;
10980 ISZ_T mplyr;
10981 } dim[MAXDIMS];
10982} sb;
10983
10984static ISZ_T
10985eval_sub_index(int dim)
10986{
10987 int repeatc;
10988 ISZ_T o_lowb, elem_offset;
10989 ACL *subscr_base;
10990 ADSC *adsc = AD_DPTR(sb.sub[dim].dtype);
10991 o_lowb = ad_val_of(sym_of_ast(AD_LWAST(adsc, 0)));
10992 subscr_base = sb.sub[dim].subscr_base;
10993
10994 elem_offset = (sb.sub[dim].idx - o_lowb);
10995 while (elem_offset && subscr_base) {
10996 if (subscr_base->repeatc)
10997 repeatc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(subscr_base->repeatc));
10998 else
10999 repeatc = 1;
11000 if (repeatc > 1) {
11001 while (repeatc > 0 && elem_offset) {
11002 --repeatc;
11003 --elem_offset;
11004 }
11005 } else {
11006 subscr_base = subscr_base->next;
11007 --elem_offset;
11008 }
11009 }
11010 return get_ival(subscr_base->dtype, subscr_base->conval);
11011}
11012
11013static int
11014eval_sb(int d)
11015{
11016 int i;
11017 int t_ub = 0;
11018 ISZ_T sub_idx;
11019 ISZ_T elem_offset;
11020 ISZ_T repeat;
11021 ACL *v;
11022 ACL *c;
11023 ACL tmp;
11024
11025#define TRACE_EVAL_SB 0
11026 if (d == 0) {
11027#if TRACE_EVAL_SB
11028 printf("-----\n");
11029#endif
11030 sb.sub[0].idx = sb.sub[0].lowb;
11031 if (sb.sub[0].stride > 0)
11032 t_ub = 1;
11033 while ((t_ub ? sb.sub[0].idx <= sb.sub[0].upb
11034 : sb.sub[0].idx >= sb.sub[0].upb)) {
11035 /* compute element offset */
11036 elem_offset = 0;
11037 for (i = 0; i < sb.ndims; i++) {
11038 sub_idx = sb.sub[i].idx;
11039 if (sb.sub[i].subscr_base) {
11040 sub_idx = eval_sub_index(i);
11041 }
11042 assert(sub_idx >= sb.dim[i].lowb && sub_idx <= sb.dim[i].upb,
11043 "Subscript for array is out-of-bounds", sub_idx, 0);
11044
11045 elem_offset += (sub_idx - sb.dim[i].lowb) * sb.dim[i].mplyr;
11046#if TRACE_EVAL_SB
11047 printf("%3d ", sub_idx);
11048#endif
11049 }
11050#if TRACE_EVAL_SB
11051 printf(" elem_offset - %ld\n", elem_offset);
11052#endif
11053 /* get initialization value at element offset */
11054 v = sb.arrbase;
11055 while (v && elem_offset) {
11056 if (v->repeatc)
11057 repeat = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(v->repeatc));
11058 else
11059 repeat = 1;
11060 if (repeat > 1) {
11061 while (v && repeat > 0 && elem_offset) {
11062 --elem_offset;
11063 --repeat;
11064 }
11065 } else {
11066 v = v->next;
11067 --elem_offset;
11068 }
11069 }
11070 if (v == NULL) {
11071 interr("initialization expression: invalid array subscripts\n",
11072 elem_offset, 3);
11073 return 1;
11074 }
11075 /*
11076 * evaluate initialization value and add (repeat copies) to
11077 * initialization list
11078 */
11079 tmp = *v;
11080 tmp.next = 0;
11081 tmp.repeatc = astb.i1;
11082 c = eval_init_expr_item(clone_init_const(&tmp, TRUE));
11083 c->next = NULL;
11084
11085 add_to_list(c, &sb.root);
11086 sb.sub[0].idx += sb.sub[0].stride;
11087 }
11088#if TRACE_EVAL_SB
11089 printf("-----\n");
11090#endif
11091 return 0;
11092 }
11093 if (sb.sub[d].stride > 0) {
11094 for (sb.sub[d].idx = sb.sub[d].lowb; sb.sub[d].idx <= sb.sub[d].upb;
11095 sb.sub[d].idx += sb.sub[d].stride) {
11096 if (eval_sb(d - 1))
11097 return 1;
11098 }
11099 } else {
11100 for (sb.sub[d].idx = sb.sub[d].lowb; sb.sub[d].idx >= sb.sub[d].upb;
11101 sb.sub[d].idx += sb.sub[d].stride) {
11102 if (eval_sb(d - 1))
11103 return 1;
11104 }
11105 }
11106 return 0;
11107}
11108
11109static ACL *
11110eval_const_array_section(ACL *lop, int ldtype)
11111{
11112 ADSC *adsc = AD_DPTR(ldtype);
11113 int ndims = 0;
11114 int i;
11115
11116 sb.root = sb.roottail = NULL;
11117 if (lop->id == AC_ACONST) {
11118 sb.arrbase = eval_array_constructor(lop);
11119 } else {
11120 sb.arrbase = lop;
11121 }
11122
11123 if (sb.ndims != AD_NUMDIM(adsc)) {
11124 interr("initialization expression: subscript/dimension mis-match\n", ldtype,
11125 3);
11126 return 0;
11127 }
11128 ndims = AD_NUMDIM(adsc);
11129 for (i = 0; i < ndims; i++) {
11130 sb.dim[i].lowb = ad_val_of(sym_of_ast(AD_LWAST(adsc, i)));
11131 sb.dim[i].upb = ad_val_of(sym_of_ast(AD_UPAST(adsc, i)));
11132 sb.dim[i].mplyr = ad_val_of(sym_of_ast(AD_MLPYR(adsc, i)));
11133 }
11134
11135 sb.ndims = ndims;
11136 if (eval_sb(ndims - 1))
11137 return 0;
11138
11139 return sb.root;
11140}
11141
11142static ISZ_T
11143get_ival(DTYPE dtype, INT conval)
11144{
11145 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
11146 case TY_INT8:
11147 case TY_LOG8:
11148 return get_isz_cval(conval);
11149 default:
11150 return conval;
11151 }
11152}
11153
11154static ACL *
11155eval_const_array_triple_section(ACL *curr_e)
11156{
11157 ACL *c, *lop, *rop, *t_lop;
11158 ACL *v;
11159 int ndims = 0;
11160
11161 sb.root = sb.roottail = NULL;
11162 c = curr_e;
11163 do {
11164 rop = c->u1.expr->rop;
11165 lop = c->u1.expr->lop;
11166 sb.sub[ndims].subscr_base = 0;
11167 sb.sub[ndims].dtype = 0;
11168 if (lop) {
11169 t_lop = eval_init_expr(lop);
11170 sb.sub[ndims].dtype = t_lop->dtype;
11171 if (t_lop->id == AC_ACONST)
11172 sb.sub[ndims].subscr_base = eval_array_constructor(t_lop);
11173 else
11174 sb.sub[ndims].subscr_base = t_lop;
11175 }
11176 if (rop == 0) {
11177 interr("initialization expression: missing array section lb\n", 0, 3);
11178 return 0;
11179 }
11180 v = eval_init_expr(rop);
11181 if (!v || !v->is_const) {
11182 interr("initialization expression: non-constant lb\n", 0, 3);
11183 return 0;
11184 }
11185 sb.sub[ndims].lowb = get_ival(v->dtype, v->conval);
11186
11187 if ((rop = rop->next) == 0) {
11188 interr("initialization expression: missing array section ub\n", 0, 3);
11189 return 0;
11190 }
11191 v = eval_init_expr(rop);
11192 if (!v || !v->is_const) {
11193 interr("initialization expression: non-constant ub\n", 0, 3);
11194 return 0;
11195 }
11196
11197 sb.sub[ndims].upb = get_ival(v->dtype, v->conval);
11198
11199 if ((rop = rop->next) == 0) {
11200 interr("initialization expression: missing array section stride\n", 0, 3);
11201 return 0;
11202 }
11203 v = eval_init_expr(rop);
11204 if (!v || !v->is_const) {
11205 interr("initialization expression: non-constant stride\n", 0, 3);
11206 return 0;
11207 }
11208
11209 sb.sub[ndims].stride = get_ival(v->dtype, v->conval);
11210
11211 if (++ndims >= 7) {
11212 interr("initialization expression: too many dimensions\n", 0, 3);
11213 return 0;
11214 }
11215 c = c->next;
11216 } while (c);
11217
11218 sb.ndims = ndims;
11219 return sb.root;
11220}
11221
11222static void
11223mk_cmp(ACL *c, int op, INT l_conval, INT r_conval, int rdtype, int dt)
11224{
11225 switch (get_ast_op(op)) {
11226 case OP_EQ:
11227 case OP_GE:
11228 case OP_GT:
11229 case OP_LE:
11230 case OP_LT:
11231 case OP_NE:
11232 l_conval = const_fold(OP_CMP, l_conval, r_conval, rdtype);
11233 switch (get_ast_op(op)) {
11234 case OP_EQ:
11235 l_conval = l_conval == 0;
11236 break;
11237 case OP_GE:
11238 l_conval = l_conval >= 0;
11239 break;
11240 case OP_GT:
11241 l_conval = l_conval > 0;
11242 break;
11243 case OP_LE:
11244 l_conval = l_conval <= 0;
11245 break;
11246 case OP_LT:
11247 l_conval = l_conval < 0;
11248 break;
11249 case OP_NE:
11250 l_conval = l_conval != 0;
11251 break;
11252 }
11253 l_conval = l_conval ? SCFTN_TRUE : SCFTN_FALSE;
11254 c->conval = l_conval;
11255 break;
11256 case OP_LEQV:
11257 l_conval = const_fold(OP_CMP, l_conval, r_conval, rdtype);
11258 c->conval = l_conval == 0;
11259 break;
11260 case OP_LNEQV:
11261 l_conval = const_fold(OP_CMP, l_conval, r_conval, rdtype);
11262 c->conval = l_conval != 0;
11263 break;
11264 case OP_LOR:
11265 c->conval = l_conval | r_conval;
11266 break;
11267 case OP_LAND:
11268 c->conval = l_conval & r_conval;
11269 break;
11270 default:
11271 c->conval = const_fold(get_ast_op(op), l_conval, r_conval, dt);
11272 }
11273}
11274
11275static ACL *
11276eval_init_op(int op, ACL *lop, DTYPE ldtype, ACL *rop, DTYPE rdtype, SPTR sptr,
11277 DTYPE dtype)
11278{
11279 ACL *root = NULL;
11280 ACL *c;
11281 ACL *cur_lop;
11282 ACL *cur_rop;
11283 DTYPE dt = DDTG(dtype);
11284 DTYPE e_dtype;
11285 int l_repeatc;
11286 int r_repeatc;
11287 INT l_conval;
11288 INT r_conval;
11289 int count;
11290 int lsptr;
11291 int rsptr;
11292 char *s;
11293 int llen;
11294 int rlen;
11295
11296 if (!lop) {
11297 return 0;
11298 }
11299
11300 if (op == AC_NEG || op == AC_LNOT) {
11301 cur_lop = (lop->id == AC_ACONST ? lop->subc : lop);
11302 for (; cur_lop; cur_lop = cur_lop->next) {
11303 c = GET_ACL(15);
11304 c->id = AC_CONST;
11305 c->dtype = dt;
11306 c->repeatc = astb.i1;
11307 l_conval = cur_lop->conval;
11308 if (dt != cur_lop->dtype) {
11309 l_conval = cngcon(l_conval, DDTG(cur_lop->dtype), dt);
11310 }
11311 if (op == AC_LNOT)
11312 c->conval = ~(l_conval);
11313 else
11314 c->conval = negate_const(l_conval, dt);
11315 add_to_list(c, &root);
11316 }
11317 } else if (op == AC_ARRAYREF) {
11318 root = eval_const_array_section(lop, ldtype);
11319 } else if (op == AC_CAT) {
11320 lsptr = lop->conval;
11321 rsptr = rop->conval;
11322 llen = string_length(DTYPEG(lsptr));
11323 rlen = string_length(DTYPEG(rsptr));
11324 s = getitem(0, llen + rlen);
11325 BCOPY(s, stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(lsptr), char, llen);
11326 BCOPY(s + llen, stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(rsptr), char, rlen);
11327
11328 c = GET_ACL(15);
11329 c->id = AC_CONST;
11330 c->dtype =
11331 get_type(2, DTY(DDTG(DTYPEG(lsptr))), mk_cval(llen + rlen, DT_INT4));
11332 c->repeatc = astb.i1;
11333 c->conval = c->sptr = getstring(s, llen + rlen);
11334 c->u1.ast = mk_cnst(c->conval);
11335 add_to_list(c, &root);
11336 } else if (op == AC_CONV) {
11337 cur_lop = (lop->id == AC_ACONST ? lop->subc : lop);
11338 if (cur_lop->repeatc)
11339 l_repeatc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(cur_lop->repeatc));
11340 else
11341 l_repeatc = 1;
11342 for (; cur_lop;) {
11343 c = GET_ACL(15);
11344 c->id = AC_CONST;
11345 c->dtype = dt;
11346 c->repeatc = astb.i1;
11347 c->conval = cngcon(cur_lop->conval, cur_lop->dtype, DDTG(dtype));
11348 add_to_list(c, &root);
11349 if (--l_repeatc <= 0) {
11350 cur_lop = cur_lop->next;
11351 if (cur_lop) {
11352 if (cur_lop->repeatc)
11353 l_repeatc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(cur_lop->repeatc));
11354 else
11355 l_repeatc = 1;
11356 }
11357 }
11358 }
11359 } else if (op == AC_MEMBR_SEL) {
11360 sptr = A_SPTRG(lop->u1.ast);
11361 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) != TY_DERIVED || !PARAMG(sptr)) {
11362 error(
11363 4, 3, gbl.lineno,
11364 "Left hand side of % operator must be a named constant derived type",
11365 NULL);
11366 return 0;
11367 }
11368
11369 sptr = NMCNSTG(sptr);
11370 c = clone_init_const(get_getitem_p(CONVAL2G(sptr)), TRUE);
11371
11372 if (c->id != AC_SCONST) {
11373 interr("Malformed member select operator, lhs not a derived type "
11374 "initializaer",
11375 op, 3);
11376 return 0;
11377 }
11378
11379 for (c = c->subc, count = CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(rop->u1.ast)); c && count;
11380 c = c->next, --count)
11381 ;
11382
11383 if (!c || count != 0) {
11384 interr("Malformed member select operator, invalid member specifier", op,
11385 3);
11386 return 0;
11387 }
11388
11389 root = clone_init_const(c, TRUE);
11390 root = eval_init_expr(root);
11391 } else if (op == AC_INTR_CALL) {
11392 AC_INTRINSIC intrin = lop->u1.i;
11393 switch (intrin) {
11394 case AC_I_adjustl:
11395 root = eval_adjustl(rop);
11396 break;
11397 case AC_I_adjustr:
11398 root = eval_adjustr(rop);
11399 break;
11400 case AC_I_char:
11401 root = eval_char(rop, dtype);
11402 break;
11403 case AC_I_ichar:
11404 root = eval_ichar(rop, dtype);
11405 break;
11406 case AC_I_index:
11407 root = eval_index(rop);
11408 break;
11409 case AC_I_int:
11410 root = eval_int(rop, dtype);
11411 break;
11412 case AC_I_ishft:
11413 root = eval_ishft(rop, dtype);
11414 break;
11415 case AC_I_len_trim:
11416 root = eval_len_trim(rop);
11417 break;
11418 case AC_I_ubound:
11419 case AC_I_lbound:
11420 root = eval_ul_bound(rop);
11421 break;
11422 case AC_I_min:
11423 root = eval_min_or_max(rop, dtype, /*want_max*/ FALSE);
11424 break;
11425 case AC_I_max:
11426 root = eval_min_or_max(rop, dtype, /*want_max*/ TRUE);
11427 break;
11428 case AC_I_nint:
11429 root = eval_nint(rop, dtype);
11430 break;
11431 case AC_I_null:
11432 root = eval_null(sptr);
11433 break;
11434 case AC_I_fltconvert:
11435 root = eval_fltconvert(rop, dtype);
11436 break;
11437 case AC_I_repeat:
11438 root = eval_repeat(rop, dtype);
11439 break;
11440 case AC_I_transfer:
11441 root = eval_transfer(rop, dtype);
11442 break;
11443 case AC_I_transpose:
11444 root = eval_reshape(rop, dtype, /*transpose*/ TRUE);
11445 break;
11446 case AC_I_reshape:
11447 root = eval_reshape(rop, dtype, /*transpose*/ FALSE);
11448 break;
11449 case AC_I_selected_int_kind:
11450 root = eval_selected_int_kind(rop);
11451 break;
11452 case AC_I_selected_real_kind:
11453 root = eval_selected_real_kind(rop);
11454 break;
11455 case AC_I_selected_char_kind:
11456 root = eval_selected_char_kind(rop);
11457 break;
11458 case AC_I_scan:
11459 root = eval_scan(rop);
11460 break;
11461 case AC_I_shape:
11462 root = eval_shape(rop, dtype);
11463 break;
11464 case AC_I_size:
11465 root = eval_size(rop);
11466 break;
11467 case AC_I_trim:
11468 root = eval_trim(rop, dtype);
11469 break;
11470 case AC_I_verify:
11471 root = eval_verify(rop);
11472 break;
11473 case AC_I_floor:
11474 root = eval_floor(rop, dtype);
11475 break;
11476 case AC_I_ceiling:
11477 root = eval_ceiling(rop, dtype);
11478 break;
11479 case AC_I_mod:
11480 root = eval_mod(rop, dtype);
11481 break;
11482 case AC_I_sqrt:
11483 root = eval_sqrt(rop, dtype);
11484 break;
11485 case AC_I_exp:
11486 root = eval_exp(rop, dtype);
11487 break;
11488 case AC_I_log:
11489 root = eval_log(rop, dtype);
11490 break;
11491 case AC_I_log10:
11492 root = eval_log10(rop, dtype);
11493 break;
11494 case AC_I_sin:
11495 root = eval_sin(rop, dtype);
11496 break;
11497 case AC_I_cos:
11498 root = eval_cos(rop, dtype);
11499 break;
11500 case AC_I_tan:
11501 root = eval_tan(rop, dtype);
11502 break;
11503 case AC_I_asin:
11504 root = eval_asin(rop, dtype);
11505 break;
11506 case AC_I_acos:
11507 root = eval_acos(rop, dtype);
11508 break;
11509 case AC_I_atan:
11510 root = eval_atan(rop, dtype);
11511 break;
11512 case AC_I_atan2:
11513 root = eval_atan2(rop, dtype);
11514 break;
11515 case AC_I_abs:
11516 root = eval_abs(rop, dtype);
11517 break;
11518 case AC_I_iand:
11519 root = eval_iand(rop, dtype);
11520 break;
11521 case AC_I_ior:
11522 root = eval_ior(rop, dtype);
11523 break;
11524 case AC_I_ieor:
11525 root = eval_ieor(rop, dtype);
11526 break;
11527 case AC_I_merge:
11528 root = eval_merge(rop, dtype);
11529 break;
11530 case AC_I_scale:
11531 root = eval_scale(rop, dtype);
11532 break;
11533 case AC_I_maxloc:
11534 case AC_I_maxval:
11535 case AC_I_minloc:
11536 case AC_I_minval:
11537 root = eval_minval_or_maxval(rop, rdtype, intrin);
11538 break;
11539 default:
11540 interr("eval_init_op(semutil2.c): intrinsic not supported in "
11541 "initialization",
11542 intrin, ERR_Severe);
11543 /* Try to avoid a seg fault by returning something reasonable */
11544 root = GET_ACL(15);
11545 root->id = AC_CONST;
11546 root->repeatc = astb.i1;
11547 root->dtype = dtype;
11548 root->conval = cngcon(0, DT_INT, dtype);
11549 }
11550 } else if (DTY(ldtype) == TY_ARRAY && DTY(rdtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
11551 /* array <binop> array */
11552 cur_lop = (lop->id == AC_ACONST ? lop->subc : lop);
11553 cur_rop = (rop->id == AC_ACONST ? rop->subc : rop);
11554 if (cur_lop->repeatc)
11555 l_repeatc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(cur_lop->repeatc));
11556 else
11557 l_repeatc = 1;
11558 if (cur_rop->repeatc)
11559 r_repeatc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(cur_rop->repeatc));
11560 else
11561 r_repeatc = 1;
11562 e_dtype = DDTG(dtype);
11563 for (; cur_rop && cur_lop;) {
11564 c = GET_ACL(15);
11565 c->id = AC_CONST;
11566 c->dtype = dt;
11567 l_conval = cur_lop->conval;
11568 if (DDTG(cur_lop->dtype) != e_dtype) {
11569 l_conval = cngcon(l_conval, DDTG(cur_lop->dtype), e_dtype);
11570 }
11571 r_conval = cur_rop->conval;
11572 if (DDTG(cur_rop->dtype) != e_dtype) {
11573 r_conval = cngcon(r_conval, DDTG(cur_rop->dtype), e_dtype);
11574 }
11575 c->conval = const_fold(get_ast_op(op), l_conval, r_conval, dt);
11576 add_to_list(c, &root);
11577 if (--l_repeatc <= 0) {
11578 cur_lop = cur_lop->next;
11579 if (cur_lop) {
11580 if (cur_lop->repeatc)
11581 l_repeatc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(cur_lop->repeatc));
11582 else
11583 l_repeatc = 1;
11584 }
11585 }
11586 if (--r_repeatc <= 0) {
11587 cur_rop = cur_rop->next;
11588 if (cur_rop) {
11589 if (cur_rop->repeatc)
11590 r_repeatc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(cur_rop->repeatc));
11591 else
11592 r_repeatc = 1;
11593 }
11594 }
11595 }
11596 } else if (DTY(ldtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
11597 /* array <binop> scalar */
11598 cur_lop = (lop->id == AC_ACONST ? lop->subc : lop);
11599 if (cur_lop->repeatc)
11600 l_repeatc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(cur_lop->repeatc));
11601 else
11602 l_repeatc = 1;
11603 e_dtype = DDTG(dtype) != DT_LOG ? DDTG(dtype) : DDTG(rop->dtype);
11604 r_conval = rop->conval;
11605 if (rop->dtype != e_dtype) {
11606 r_conval = cngcon(r_conval, rop->dtype, e_dtype);
11607 }
11608 for (; cur_lop;) {
11609 c = GET_ACL(15);
11610 c->id = AC_CONST;
11611 c->dtype = dt;
11612 c->repeatc = astb.i1;
11613 l_conval = cur_lop->conval;
11614 if (DDTG(cur_lop->dtype) != e_dtype) {
11615 l_conval = cngcon(l_conval, DDTG(cur_lop->dtype), e_dtype);
11616 }
11617
11618 mk_cmp(c, op, l_conval, r_conval, rdtype, dt);
11619 add_to_list(c, &root);
11620 if (--l_repeatc <= 0) {
11621 cur_lop = cur_lop->next;
11622 if (cur_lop) {
11623 if (cur_lop->repeatc)
11624 l_repeatc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(cur_lop->repeatc));
11625 else
11626 l_repeatc = 1;
11627 }
11628 }
11629 }
11630 } else if (DTY(rdtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
11631 /* scalar <binop> array */
11632 cur_rop = (rop->id == AC_ACONST ? rop->subc : rop);
11633 if (cur_rop->repeatc)
11634 r_repeatc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(cur_rop->repeatc));
11635 else
11636 r_repeatc = 1;
11637 e_dtype = DDTG(dtype) != DT_LOG ? DDTG(dtype) : DDTG(lop->dtype);
11638 l_conval = lop->conval;
11639 if (lop->dtype != e_dtype) {
11640 l_conval = cngcon(l_conval, lop->dtype, e_dtype);
11641 }
11642 for (cur_rop = rop; cur_rop;) {
11643 c = GET_ACL(15);
11644 c->id = AC_CONST;
11645 c->dtype = dt;
11646 c->repeatc = astb.i1;
11647 r_conval = cur_rop->conval;
11648 if (DDTG(cur_rop->dtype) != e_dtype) {
11649 r_conval = cngcon(r_conval, DDTG(cur_rop->dtype), e_dtype);
11650 }
11651 mk_cmp(c, op, l_conval, r_conval, rdtype, dt);
11652 add_to_list(c, &root);
11653 if (--r_repeatc <= 0) {
11654 cur_rop = cur_rop->next;
11655 if (cur_rop) {
11656 if (cur_rop->repeatc)
11657 r_repeatc = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(cur_rop->repeatc));
11658 else
11659 r_repeatc = 1;
11660 }
11661 }
11662 }
11663 } else {
11664 /* scalar <binop> scalar */
11665 root = GET_ACL(15);
11666 root->id = AC_CONST;
11667 root->repeatc = astb.i1;
11668 root->dtype = dt;
11669 op = get_ast_op(op);
11670 switch (op) {
11671 case OP_EQ:
11672 case OP_GE:
11673 case OP_GT:
11674 case OP_LE:
11675 case OP_LT:
11676 case OP_NE:
11677 l_conval = const_fold(OP_CMP, lop->conval, rop->conval, ldtype);
11678 switch (op) {
11679 case OP_EQ:
11680 l_conval = (l_conval == 0);
11681 break;
11682 case OP_GE:
11683 l_conval = (l_conval >= 0);
11684 break;
11685 case OP_GT:
11686 l_conval = (l_conval > 0);
11687 break;
11688 case OP_LE:
11689 l_conval = (l_conval <= 0);
11690 break;
11691 case OP_LT:
11692 l_conval = (l_conval < 0);
11693 break;
11694 case OP_NE:
11695 l_conval = (l_conval != 0);
11696 break;
11697 }
11698 l_conval = l_conval ? SCFTN_TRUE : SCFTN_FALSE;
11699 root->conval = l_conval;
11700 break;
11701 case OP_LEQV:
11702 l_conval = const_fold(OP_CMP, lop->conval, rop->conval, ldtype);
11703 root->conval = (l_conval == 0);
11704 break;
11705 case OP_LNEQV:
11706 l_conval = const_fold(OP_CMP, lop->conval, rop->conval, ldtype);
11707 root->conval = (l_conval != 0);
11708 break;
11709 case OP_LOR:
11710 root->conval = lop->conval | rop->conval;
11711 break;
11712 case OP_LAND:
11713 root->conval = lop->conval & rop->conval;
11714 break;
11715 default:
11716 l_conval = lop->conval;
11717 if (lop->dtype != dt) {
11718 l_conval = cngcon(l_conval, lop->dtype, dt);
11719 }
11720 r_conval = rop->conval;
11721 if (rop->dtype != dt) {
11722 r_conval = cngcon(r_conval, rop->dtype, dt);
11723 }
11724 root->conval = const_fold(op, l_conval, r_conval, dt);
11725 break;
11726 }
11727 }
11728 return root;
11729}
11730
11731static ACL *
11732eval_array_constructor(ACL *e)
11733{
11734 ACL *root = NULL;
11735 ACL *cur_e;
11736 ACL *new_e;
11737
11738 /* collapse nested array contstructors */
11739 for (cur_e = e->subc; cur_e; cur_e = cur_e->next) {
11740 if (cur_e->id == AC_ACONST) {
11741 new_e = eval_array_constructor(cur_e);
11742 } else {
11743 new_e = eval_init_expr_item(cur_e);
11744 if (!new_e) {
11745 return 0;
11746 }
11747 if (new_e->id == AC_ACONST) {
11748 new_e = eval_array_constructor(new_e);
11749 }
11750 }
11751 add_to_list(new_e, &root);
11752 }
11753 return root;
11754}
11755
11756static ACL *
11757eval_init_expr_item(ACL *cur_e)
11758{
11759 ACL *new_e = NULL;
11760 ACL *lop = NULL;
11761 ACL *rop = NULL;
11762 ACL *temp = NULL;
11763 int sptr;
11764
11765 switch (cur_e->id) {
11766 case AC_AST:
11767 if (A_TYPEG(cur_e->u1.ast) == A_ID &&
11768 DTY(A_DTYPEG(cur_e->u1.ast)) == TY_ARRAY) {
11769 sptr = A_SPTRG(cur_e->u1.ast);
11770 if (PARAMG(sptr)) {
11771 if (STYPEG(sptr) != ST_PARAM) {
11772 sptr = NMCNSTG(sptr);
11773 }
11774 new_e = clone_init_const(get_getitem_p(CONVAL2G(sptr)), TRUE);
11775 new_e = eval_init_expr(new_e);
11776 break;
11777 } else {
11778 return 0;
11779 }
11780 }
11781 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
11782 case AC_CONST:
11783 new_e = clone_init_const(cur_e, TRUE);
11784 if (new_e->id == AC_AST) {
11785 new_e->id = AC_CONST;
11786 new_e->conval = get_const_from_ast(new_e->u1.ast);
11787 }
11788 break;
11789 case AC_ICONST:
11790 new_e = clone_init_const(cur_e, TRUE);
11791 break;
11792 case AC_IEXPR:
11793 if (cur_e->u1.expr->op != AC_INTR_CALL) {
11794 lop = eval_init_expr(cur_e->u1.expr->lop);
11795 rop = temp = cur_e->u1.expr->rop;
11796 if (temp && cur_e->u1.expr->op == AC_ARRAYREF &&
11797 temp->u1.expr->op == AC_TRIPLE) {
11798 rop = eval_const_array_triple_section(temp);
11799 } else if (temp)
11800 rop = eval_init_expr(temp);
11801 } else {
11802 lop = cur_e->u1.expr->lop;
11803 rop = cur_e->u1.expr->rop;
11804 }
11805 new_e = eval_init_op(cur_e->u1.expr->op, lop, cur_e->u1.expr->lop->dtype,
11806 rop, rop ? cur_e->u1.expr->rop->dtype : 0, cur_e->sptr,
11807 cur_e->dtype);
11808 break;
11809 case AC_ACONST:
11810 new_e = clone_init_const(cur_e, TRUE);
11811 new_e->subc = eval_array_constructor(cur_e);
11812 if (new_e->subc)
11813 new_e->subc = convert_acl_dtype(new_e->subc, DDTG(new_e->subc->dtype),
11814 DDTG(new_e->dtype));
11815 break;
11816 case AC_SCONST:
11817 new_e = clone_init_const(cur_e, TRUE);
11818 new_e->subc = eval_init_expr(new_e->subc);
11819 break;
11820 case AC_IDO:
11821 new_e = eval_do(cur_e);
11822 break;
11823 case AC_CONVAL:
11824 new_e = cur_e;
11825 break;
11826 default:
11827 /* MORE internal error */
11828 break;
11829 }
11830
11831 return new_e;
11832}
11833
11834ACL *
11835eval_init_expr(ACL *e)
11836{
11837 ACL *root = NULL;
11838 ACL *cur_e;
11839 ACL *new_e;
11840
11841 for (cur_e = e; cur_e; cur_e = cur_e->next) {
11842 switch (cur_e->id) {
11843 case AC_SCONST:
11844 new_e = clone_init_const(cur_e, TRUE);
11845 new_e->subc = eval_init_expr(new_e->subc);
11846 if (!new_e->subc) {
11847 return 0;
11848 }
11849 if (new_e->subc->dtype == cur_e->dtype) {
11850 new_e->subc = new_e->subc->subc;
11851 }
11852 break;
11853 case AC_ACONST:
11854 new_e = clone_init_const(cur_e, TRUE);
11855 new_e->subc = eval_array_constructor(cur_e);
11856 if (new_e->subc)
11857 new_e->subc = convert_acl_dtype(new_e->subc, DDTG(new_e->subc->dtype),
11858 DDTG(new_e->dtype));
11859 break;
11860 default:
11861 new_e = eval_init_expr_item(cur_e);
11862 break;
11863 }
11864 if (!new_e) {
11865 return 0;
11866 }
11867 add_to_list(new_e, &root);
11868 }
11869
11870 return root;
11871}
11872
11873static ACL *
11874eval_do(ACL *ido)
11875{
11876 INT i;
11877 DOINFO *di = ido->u1.doinfo;
11878 INT initval;
11879 INT limitval;
11880 INT stepval;
11881 int idx_sptr = di->index_var;
11882 ACL *root = NULL;
11883 ACL *ict;
11884 INT num[2];
11885 INT sav_conval1 = CONVAL1G(idx_sptr);
11886 int inflag = 0;
11887
11888 initval = dinit_eval(di->init_expr);
11889 if (sem.dinit_error) {
11890 interr("Non-constant implied DO initial value", di->init_expr, 3);
11891 return 0;
11892 }
11893
11894 limitval = dinit_eval(di->limit_expr);
11895 if (sem.dinit_error) {
11896 interr("Non-constant implied DO limit value", di->init_expr, 3);
11897 return 0;
11898 }
11899
11900 stepval = dinit_eval(di->step_expr);
11901 if (sem.dinit_error) {
11902 interr("Non-constant implied DO step value", di->init_expr, 3);
11903 return 0;
11904 }
11905
11906 if (stepval >= 0) {
11907 for (i = initval; i <= limitval; i += stepval) {
11908 switch (DTY(DTYPEG(idx_sptr))) {
11909 case TY_INT8:
11910 case TY_LOG8:
11911 ISZ_2_INT64(i, num);
11912 /* implied do loop index variable is not A_CNST,
11913 * it is A_ID, so put it in CONVAL1P, so that
11914 * get_const_from_ast get it right.
11915 */
11916 CONVAL1P(idx_sptr, getcon(num, DTYPEG(idx_sptr)));
11917 break;
11918 default:
11919 CONVAL1P(idx_sptr, i);
11920 break;
11921 }
11922
11923 ict = eval_init_expr(ido->subc);
11924 if (!ict) {
11925 return 0;
11926 }
11927 ict->u1.ast = mk_cval1(ict->conval, ict->dtype);
11928 add_to_list(ict, &root);
11929 inflag = 1;
11930 }
11931 } else {
11932 for (i = initval; i >= limitval; i += stepval) {
11933 switch (DTY(DTYPEG(idx_sptr))) {
11934 case TY_INT8:
11935 case TY_LOG8:
11936 ISZ_2_INT64(i, num);
11937 CONVAL1P(idx_sptr, getcon(num, DTYPEG(idx_sptr)));
11938 break;
11939 default:
11940 CONVAL1P(idx_sptr, i);
11941 break;
11942 }
11943 ict = eval_init_expr(ido->subc);
11944 if (!ict) {
11945 return 0;
11946 }
11947 ict->u1.ast = mk_cval1(ict->conval, ict->dtype);
11948 add_to_list(ict, &root);
11949 inflag = 1;
11950 }
11951 }
11952 if (inflag == 0 && ido->subc) {
11953 ict = eval_init_expr(ido->subc);
11954 add_to_list(ict, &root);
11955 }
11956
11957 CONVAL1P(idx_sptr, sav_conval1);
11958
11959 return root;
11960}
11961
11962static INT
11963get_default_int_val(INT r)
11964{
11965 INT tmp[2];
11966 if (DTY(stb.user.dt_int) != TY_INT8) {
11967 return r;
11968 }
11969 tmp[1] = r;
11970 if (r >= 0)
11971 tmp[0] = 0;
11972 else
11973 tmp[0] = -1;
11974 return getcon(tmp, DT_INT8);
11975}
11976
11977VAR *
11978gen_varref_var(int ast, DTYPE dtype)
11979{
11980 SST tmp_sst;
11981 VAR *ivl;
11982
11983 SST_IDP(&tmp_sst, S_IDENT);
11984 SST_ASTP(&tmp_sst, ast);
11985 SST_DTYPEP(&tmp_sst, dtype);
11986 SST_SHAPEP(&tmp_sst, A_SHAPEG(ast));
11987 ivl = dinit_varref(&tmp_sst);
11988
11989 return ivl;
11990}
11991
11992/** \brief Process an AC_TYPEINIT.
11993
11994 Look for an initialization template for this type. If one already exists
11995 then return it. Otherwise build one (and return it).
11996 */
11997SPTR
11998get_dtype_init_template(DTYPE dtype)
11999{
12000 DTYPE element_dtype =
12001 is_array_dtype(dtype) ? array_element_dtype(dtype) : dtype;
12002 SPTR tag_sptr = get_struct_tag_sptr(element_dtype);
12003 int init_ict = get_struct_initialization_tree(element_dtype);
12004 ACL *aclp, *tmpl_aclp;
12005 SPTR sptr = NOSYM;
12006 char namebuf[128];
12007 const char prefix[] = "_dtInit";
12008
12009 assert(DTY(element_dtype) == TY_DERIVED,
12010 "get_dtype_init_template: element dtype not derived", dtype,
12011 ERR_Fatal);
12012 aclp = get_getitem_p(init_ict);
12013 if (aclp) {
12014 assert(eq_dtype(DDTG(aclp->dtype), element_dtype),
12015 "get_dtype_init_template: element dtype mismatch", dtype, ERR_Fatal);
12016 }
12017
12018 if (is_unresolved_parameterized_dtype(element_dtype))
12019 return NOSYM;
12020
12021 if (tag_sptr > NOSYM) {
12022 if ((sptr = TYPDEF_INITG(tag_sptr)) > NOSYM &&
12023 (SCG(sptr) == SC_STATIC || SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK)) {
12024 /* Reuse an existing initialization template object. */
12025 return sptr;
12026 }
12027 }
12028 snprintf(namebuf, sizeof namebuf, ".%s%04d", prefix, (int)element_dtype);
12029 namebuf[sizeof namebuf - 1] = '\0'; /* Windows snprintf bug workaround */
12030
12031 /* no existing initialization template yet for this derived type; build one */
12032 if (aclp) {
12033 sptr = getccssym_sc(prefix, (int)element_dtype, ST_VAR, SC_STATIC);
12034 DTYPEP(sptr, element_dtype);
12035 DCLDP(sptr, TRUE);
12036 INITIALIZERP(sptr, TRUE);
12037
12038 tmpl_aclp = GET_ACL(15);
12039 *tmpl_aclp = *aclp;
12040 tmpl_aclp->sptr = sptr;
12041 dinit((VAR *)NULL, tmpl_aclp);
12042 if (tag_sptr > NOSYM)
12043 TYPDEF_INITP(tag_sptr, sptr);
12044 }
12045 return sptr;
12046}
12047
12048void
12049gen_derived_type_alloc_init(ITEM *itemp)
12050{
12051 int ast = itemp->ast;
12052 DTYPE dtype = A_DTYPEG(ast);
12053 ACL *aclp;
12054 SPTR prototype;
12055 int ict = get_struct_initialization_tree(dtype);
12056
12057 if (ict == 0)
12058 return;
12059
12060 if ((aclp = get_getitem_p(ict)) && aclp->dtype &&
12061 (!dtype || !has_type_parameter(aclp->dtype)))
12062 dtype = aclp->dtype;
12063
12064 /* TODO: use init_derived_type() from semfin.c here instead? */
12065 prototype = get_dtype_init_template(dtype);
12066 if (prototype > NOSYM) {
12067 int src_ast = mk_id(prototype);
12068 add_stmt(mk_assn_stmt(itemp->ast, src_ast, A_DTYPEG(itemp->ast)));
12069 }
12070}
12071
12072static int firstalloc;
12073
12074void
12075check_dealloc_clauses(ITEM *list, ITEM *spec)
12076{
12077 ITEM *itemp;
12078 int stat = 0;
12079 int errmsg = 0;
12080
12081 if (list == 0)
12082 list = ITEM_END;
12083 if (spec == 0)
12084 spec = ITEM_END;
12085 firstalloc = 1;
12086 for (itemp = spec; itemp != ITEM_END; itemp = itemp->next) {
12087 switch (itemp->t.conval) {
12088 case TK_STAT:
12089 if (stat == 1)
12090 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno, "Multiple STAT specifiers", CNULL);
12091 stat++;
12092 break;
12093 case TK_ERRMSG:
12094 if (errmsg == 1)
12095 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno, "Multiple ERRMSG specifiers", CNULL);
12096 errmsg++;
12097 break;
12098 default:
12099 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, tokname[itemp->t.conval],
12100 "specifier invalid in DEALLOCATE");
12101 }
12102 }
12103}
12104
12105void
12106check_alloc_clauses(ITEM *list, ITEM *spec, int *srcast, int *mold_or_src)
12107{
12108 ITEM *itemp;
12109 int stat = 0;
12110 int errmsg = 0;
12111 int source = 0;
12112
12113 *srcast = 0;
12114 *mold_or_src = 0;
12115
12116 if (list == 0)
12117 list = ITEM_END;
12118 if (spec == 0)
12119 spec = ITEM_END;
12120 firstalloc = 1;
12121 for (itemp = spec; itemp != ITEM_END; itemp = itemp->next) {
12122 switch (itemp->t.conval) {
12123 case TK_STAT:
12124 if (stat == 1)
12125 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno, "Multiple STAT specifiers", CNULL);
12126 stat++;
12127 break;
12128 case TK_ERRMSG:
12129 if (errmsg == 1)
12130 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno, "Multiple ERRMSG specifiers", CNULL);
12131 errmsg++;
12132 break;
12133 case TK_SOURCE:
12134 case TK_MOLD:
12135 if (source == 1)
12136 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno, "Multiple SOURCE/MOLD specifiers", CNULL);
12137 source++;
12138 *srcast = itemp->ast;
12139 *mold_or_src = itemp->t.conval;
12140 break;
12141 case TK_ALIGN:
12142 break;
12143 }
12144 }
12145}
12146
12147int
12148gen_alloc_dealloc(int stmtyp, int object, ITEM *spec)
12149{
12150 int ast;
12151 ITEM *itemp;
12152 int sptr, objectsptr;
12153 DTYPE dtype;
12154 int stmt;
12155 int store_stat = 0;
12156 int store_pinned = 0;
12157 int len_stmt;
12158
12159 if (spec == 0)
12160 spec = ITEM_END;
12161 objectsptr = sym_of_ast(object);
12162 ast = mk_stmt(A_ALLOC, 0);
12163 A_TKNP(ast, stmtyp); /* TK_ALLOCATE/TK_DEALLOCATE */
12164 A_SRCP(ast, object); /* object (ast) to be allocated/deallocated */
12165 A_FIRSTALLOCP(ast, firstalloc);
12166 firstalloc = 0;
12167 for (itemp = spec; itemp != ITEM_END; itemp = itemp->next) {
12168 switch (itemp->t.conval) {
12169 case TK_STAT:
12170 sptr = sym_of_ast(itemp->ast);
12171 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
12172 if (DTYG(dtype) == TY_INT8) {
12173 int tmp;
12174 tmp = mk_id(get_temp(DT_INT4));
12175 store_stat = mk_assn_stmt(itemp->ast, tmp, dtype);
12176 itemp->ast = tmp;
12177 }
12178 if (dtype != DT_INT && flg.standard && !XBIT(124, 0x10))
12179 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno, "Invalid type for STATUS specifier",
12180 SYMNAME(sptr));
12181 A_LOPP(ast, itemp->ast);
12182 break;
12183 case TK_ERRMSG:
12184 A_M3P(ast, itemp->ast);
12185 break;
12186 case TK_SOURCE:
12187 case TK_MOLD:
12188 A_STARTP(ast, itemp->ast);
12189 break;
12190 case TK_ALIGN:
12191 A_ALIGNP(ast, itemp->ast);
12192 break;
12193 }
12194 }
12195 stmt = add_stmt(ast);
12196
12197 sem.alloc_std = stmt; /* std of allocate */
12198
12199 /* This is for allocate statement, must set length before allocate
12200 * sem.gcvlen supposedly gets set only when it is character
12201 */
12202 if (is_deferlenchar_ast(object) &&
12203 stmtyp == TK_ALLOCATE) {
12204 if (sem.gcvlen) {
12205 len_stmt =
12206 mk_assn_stmt(get_len_of_deferchar_ast(object), sem.gcvlen, DT_INT);
12207 stmt = add_stmt_before(len_stmt, stmt);
12208 } else {
12209#if DEBUG
12210 assert(sem.gcvlen != 0, "gen_alloc_dealloc: character size missing", 3,
12211 object);
12212#endif
12213 }
12214 }
12215
12216 if (store_stat) {
12217 stmt = add_stmt_after(store_stat, stmt);
12218 }
12219 if (store_pinned) {
12220 add_stmt_after(store_pinned, stmt);
12221 }
12222
12223 return ast;
12224}
12225
12226/** \brief If temps were allocated while processing the expression, the
12227 expression
12228 needs to be assigned to a temp, the allocatable temps need to be
12229 deallocated, and the use of the expression is replaced by the temp.
12230 */
12231int
12232check_etmp(SST *stkp)
12233{
12234 int new, ast;
12235
12236 sem.use_etmps = FALSE;
12237 if (sem.etmp_list == NULL)
12238 return SST_ASTG(stkp);
12239 /*
12240 * Create a new temp, generate an assignment of the expression to
12241 * the temp.
12242 */
12243 ast = sem_tempify(stkp);
12244 (void)add_stmt(ast);
12245 new = A_DESTG(ast);
12246 gen_dealloc_etmps();
12247 return new;
12248}
12249
12250void
12251gen_dealloc_etmps(void)
12252{
12253 int sptr;
12254
12255 while (sem.etmp_list) {
12256 /* insert a deallocate for the symbol at this item */
12257 sptr = sem.etmp_list->t.sptr;
12258 if (sptr)
12259 gen_alloc_dealloc(TK_DEALLOCATE, mk_id(sptr), 0);
12260 sem.etmp_list = sem.etmp_list->next;
12261 }
12262 sem.use_etmps = FALSE;
12263}
12264
12265void
12266check_and_add_auto_dealloc_from_ast(int ast)
12267{
12268 int sptr = sym_of_ast(ast);
12269
12270 check_and_add_auto_dealloc(sptr);
12271}
12272
12273void
12274check_and_add_auto_dealloc(int sptr)
12275{
12276 if (gbl.rutype != RU_FUNC && gbl.rutype != RU_SUBR && !CONSTRUCTSYMG(sptr))
12277 return;
12278 if (SCG(sptr) != SC_BASED)
12279 return;
12280 if (!ALLOCG(sptr) || POINTERG(sptr) || SAVEG(sptr) || sem.savall)
12281 return;
12282 if (!ALLOCATTRG(sptr) && MIDNUMG(sptr) && PTRVG(MIDNUMG(sptr)))
12283 return;
12284 if (MIDNUMG(sptr))
12285 switch (SCG(MIDNUMG(sptr))) {
12286 case SC_CMBLK:
12287 case SC_PRIVATE:
12288 return;
12289 default:
12290 break;
12291 }
12292 if (sem.scope_stack &&
12293 SCOPEG(sptr) == sem.scope_stack[sem.scope_level].sptr) {
12294 add_auto_dealloc(sptr);
12295 }
12296}
12297
12298void
12299add_auto_dealloc(int sptr)
12300{
12301 ITEM *itemp;
12302 for (itemp = sem.auto_dealloc; itemp; itemp = itemp->next) {
12303 if (itemp->t.sptr == sptr) {
12304 return;
12305 }
12306 }
12307 itemp = (ITEM *)getitem(15, sizeof(ITEM));
12308 itemp->t.sptr = sptr;
12309 itemp->next = sem.auto_dealloc;
12310 sem.auto_dealloc = itemp;
12311}
12312
12313static void
12314add_alloc_mem_initialize(int sptr)
12315{
12316 ITEM *itemp;
12317
12318 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) != TY_DERIVED || ALLOCATTRG(sptr) || POINTERG(sptr) ||
12319 !allocatable_member(sptr))
12320 return;
12321
12322 for (itemp = sem.alloc_mem_initialize; itemp; itemp = itemp->next) {
12323 if (itemp->t.sptr == sptr) {
12324 return;
12325 }
12326 }
12327 itemp = (ITEM *)getitem(15, sizeof(ITEM));
12328 itemp->t.sptr = sptr;
12329 itemp->next = sem.alloc_mem_initialize;
12330 sem.alloc_mem_initialize = itemp;
12331}
12332
12333void
12334add_type_param_initialize(int sptr)
12335{
12336 ITEM *itemp;
12337 DTYPE dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
12338 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY)
12339 dtype = DTY(dtype + 1);
12340 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_DERIVED || !has_type_parameter(dtype))
12341 return;
12342 for (itemp = sem.type_initialize; itemp; itemp = itemp->next) {
12343 if (itemp->t.sptr == sptr) {
12344 return;
12345 }
12346 }
12347 itemp = (ITEM *)getitem(15, sizeof(ITEM));
12348 itemp->t.sptr = sptr;
12349 itemp->next = sem.type_initialize;
12350 sem.type_initialize = itemp;
12351}

12353void
12354add_auto_finalize(int sptr)

12356 ITEM *itemp;
12357 for (itemp = sem.auto_finalize; itemp; itemp = itemp->next) {
12358 if (itemp->t.sptr == sptr) {
12359 return;
12360 }
12361 }
12362 itemp = (ITEM *)getitem(15, sizeof(ITEM));
12363 itemp->t.sptr = sptr;
12364 itemp->next = sem.auto_finalize;
12365 sem.auto_finalize = itemp;

12367
12368int
12369gen_finalization_for_sym(int sptr, int std, int memAst)
12370{
12371 int fsptr;
12372 int argt;
12373 int ast;
12374 int desc;
12375 DTYPE dtype;
12376 int tag, st_type;
12377 FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn;
12378
12379 if (SAVEG(sptr) || sem.savall || !has_finalized_component(sptr))
12380 return std; /* no finalization needed */
12381
12382 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) == TY_ARRAY) {
12383 if (SDSCG(sptr) == 0) {
12384 get_static_descriptor(sptr);
12385 std = add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0), std);
12386 std = init_sdsc(sptr, DTYPEG(sptr), std, 0);
12387 }
12388 desc = SDSCG(sptr);
12389
12390 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
12391
12392 dtype = DTY(dtype + 1);
12393 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED) {
12394 int arg0;
12395 tag = DTY(dtype + 3);
12396 st_type = get_static_type_descriptor(tag);
12397 arg0 = check_member(memAst, mk_id(desc));
12398 std = gen_set_type(arg0, mk_id(st_type), std, FALSE, FALSE);
12399 }
12400 } else {
12401 desc = get_type_descr_arg(gbl.currsub, sptr);
12402 }
12403 rtlRtn = RTE_finalize;
12404 fsptr = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(rtlRtn), DT_NONE);
12405 argt = mk_argt(2);
12406
12407 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = check_member(memAst, mk_id(sptr));
12408 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = check_member(memAst, mk_id(desc));
12409
12410 ast = mk_id(fsptr);
12411 ast = mk_func_node(A_CALL, ast, 2, argt);
12412 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
12413 return std;
12414}
12415
12416static int
12417get_parm_ast(int parent, SPTR sptr, DTYPE dtype)
12418{
12419 int mem, rslt, ast;
12420 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY)
12421 dtype = DTY(dtype + 1);
12422 for (mem = DTY(dtype + 1); mem > NOSYM; mem = SYMLKG(mem)) {
12423 if (PARENTG(mem)) {
12424 ast = mk_member(parent, mk_id(mem), dtype);
12425 rslt = get_parm_ast(ast, sptr, DTYPEG(mem));
12426 if (rslt)
12427 return rslt;
12428 }
12429 if (strcmp(SYMNAME(sptr), SYMNAME(mem)) == 0) {
12430 ast = mk_member(parent, mk_id(mem), /*dtype*/ DTYPEG(mem));
12431 return ast;
12432 }
12433 }
12434 /* Field not found, so try again and take more recursive approach */
12435 for (mem = DTY(dtype + 1); mem > NOSYM; mem = SYMLKG(mem)) {
12436 /* Act only on the cases that were not considered before */
12437 if ((!PARENTG(mem)) && strcmp(SYMNAME(sptr), SYMNAME(mem))) {
12438 ast = mk_member(parent, mk_id(mem), dtype);
12439 rslt = get_parm_ast(ast, sptr, DTYPEG(mem)); /* recurse here */
12440 if (rslt)
12441 return rslt;
12442 }
12443 }
12444 return 0;
12445}
12446
12447static int
12448remove_parent_from_ast(int ast)
12449{
12450 int i, newast, newast2, nargs, newargs, orig_args;
12451 int asd;
12452
12453 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
12454 case A_INTR:
12455 switch (A_OPTYPEG(ast)) {
12456 case I_INT1:
12457 case I_INT2:
12458 case I_INT4:
12459 case I_INT8:
12460 case I_INT:
12461 orig_args = A_ARGSG(ast);
12462 newast = remove_parent_from_ast(ARGT_ARG(orig_args, 0));
12463 newast2 = mk_stmt(A_INTR, A_DTYPEG(ast));
12464 A_OPTYPEP(newast2, A_OPTYPEG(ast));
12465 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(ast);
12466 newargs = mk_argt(nargs);
12467 ARGT_ARG(newargs, 0) = newast;
12468 for (i = 1; i < nargs; ++i)
12469 ARGT_ARG(newargs, i) = ARGT_ARG(orig_args, i);
12470 A_ARGSP(newast2, newargs);
12471 A_ARGCNTP(newast2, nargs);
12472 ast = newast;
12473 }
12474 break;
12475 case A_MEM:
12476 ast = mk_id(memsym_of_ast(ast));
12477 break;
12478 case A_CNST:
12479 break;
12480 case A_ID:
12481 break;
12482 case A_SUBSCR:
12483 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
12484 newast = remove_parent_from_ast(A_LOPG(ast));
12485 ast = mk_subscr_copy(newast, asd, A_DTYPEG(newast));
12486 break;
12487 case A_UNOP:
12488 newast = remove_parent_from_ast(A_LOPG(ast));
12489 ast = mk_unop(A_OPTYPEG(ast), newast, A_DTYPEG(ast));
12490 break;
12491 case A_CONV:
12492 newast = remove_parent_from_ast(A_LOPG(ast));
12493 ast = mk_convert(newast, A_DTYPEG(ast));
12494 break;
12495 case A_BINOP:
12496 newast = remove_parent_from_ast(A_LOPG(ast));
12497 newast2 = remove_parent_from_ast(A_ROPG(ast));
12498 ast = mk_binop(A_OPTYPEG(ast), newast, newast2, A_DTYPEG(ast));
12499 break;
12500 default:
12501 interr("remove_parent_from_ast: unexpected ast type", A_TYPEG(ast), 3);
12502 }
12503 return ast;
12504}
12505
12506int
12507add_parent_to_bounds(int parent, int ast)
12508{
12509 int newast, i;
12510 if (parent == 0)
12511 return ast;
12512 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
12513 case A_INTR:
12514 switch (A_OPTYPEG(ast)) {
12515 case I_INT1:
12516 case I_INT2:
12517 case I_INT4:
12518 case I_INT8:
12519 case I_INT:
12520 i = A_ARGSG(ast);
12521 newast = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, ARGT_ARG(i, 0));
12522 ARGT_ARG(i, 0) = newast;
12523 }
12524 break;
12525 case A_MEM:
12526 if (A_PARENTG(ast) == parent) {
12527 break;
12528 }
12529
12530 if (!A_PARENTG(ast)) {
12531 A_PARENTP(ast, parent);
12532 break;
12533 }
12534
12535 newast = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, A_PARENTG(ast));
12536 if (newast)
12537 A_PARENTP(ast, newast);
12538
12539 break;
12540 case A_CNST:
12541 break;
12542 case A_ID:
12543 newast = get_parm_ast(parent, sym_of_ast(ast), DTYPEG(sym_of_ast(parent)));
12544 if (newast)
12545 ast = newast;
12546 break;
12547 case A_SUBSCR:
12548 case A_UNOP:
12549 case A_CONV:
12550 newast = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, A_LOPG(ast));
12551 A_LOPP(ast, newast);
12552 break;
12553 case A_BINOP:
12554 newast = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, A_LOPG(ast));
12555 A_LOPP(ast, newast);
12556 newast = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, A_ROPG(ast));
12557 A_ROPP(ast, newast);
12558 break;
12559 default:
12560 interr("add_parent_to_bounds: unexpected ast type", A_TYPEG(ast), 3);
12561 }
12562 return ast;
12563}
12564
12565int
12566fix_mem_bounds(int parent, int mem)
12567{
12568 ADSC *ad;
12569 int numdim, i, bndast;
12570 int all_cnst;
12571 int zbase;
12572
12573 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(mem));
12574 numdim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
12575 all_cnst = 1;
12576 zbase = AD_ZBASE(ad);
12577 if (zbase && A_TYPEG(zbase)) {
12578 AD_ZBASE(ad) = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, zbase);
12579 }
12580 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++) {
12581 bndast = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
12582 if (bndast) {
12583 AD_LWAST(ad, i) = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, bndast);
12584 if (A_TYPEG(AD_LWAST(ad, i)) != A_CNST)
12585 all_cnst = 0;
12586 }
12587 bndast = AD_UPAST(ad, i);
12588 if (bndast) {
12589 AD_UPAST(ad, i) = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, bndast);
12590 if (A_TYPEG(AD_UPAST(ad, i)) != A_CNST)
12591 all_cnst = 0;
12592 }
12593 bndast = AD_EXTNTAST(ad, i);
12594 if (bndast) {
12595 AD_EXTNTAST(ad, i) = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, bndast);
12596 }
12597 }
12598
12599 return all_cnst;
12600}
12601
12602int
12603fix_mem_bounds2(int parent, int mem)
12604{
12605 ADSC *ad, *bd;
12606 int numdim, i, bndast;
12607 int all_cnst;
12608 int zbase;
12609 int mem_dtype;
12610 int new_dtype;
12611
12612 /* This function is the same as fix_mem_bounds() above except we
12613 * assign a new dtype with mem that includes a new array descriptor.
12614 * Otherwise, we may overwrite a shared array descriptor with new
12615 * bounds information.
12616 */
12617
12618 mem_dtype = new_dtype = DTYPEG(mem);
12619 new_dtype = dup_array_dtype(new_dtype);
12620
12621 numdim = ADD_NUMDIM(mem_dtype);
12622 get_aux_arrdsc(new_dtype, numdim);
12623 bd = AD_DPTR(new_dtype);
12624 ad = AD_DPTR(mem_dtype);
12625
12626 /* Step 1: Construct bd w/ fields from mem_dtype minus any existing parent */
12627
12628 all_cnst = 1;
12629 zbase = ADD_ZBASE(mem_dtype);
12630 if (zbase && A_TYPEG(zbase)) {
12631 AD_ZBASE(bd) = remove_parent_from_ast(zbase);
12632 }
12633
12634 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++) {
12635 bndast = ADD_LWAST(mem_dtype, i);
12636 if (bndast) {
12637 AD_LWBD(bd, i) = AD_LWAST(bd, i) = remove_parent_from_ast(bndast);
12638 if (A_TYPEG(ADD_LWAST(mem_dtype, i)) != A_CNST)
12639 all_cnst = 0;
12640 }
12641 bndast = ADD_UPAST(mem_dtype, i);
12642 if (bndast) {
12643 AD_UPBD(bd, i) = AD_UPAST(bd, i) = remove_parent_from_ast(bndast);
12644 if (A_TYPEG(ADD_UPAST(mem_dtype, i)) != A_CNST)
12645 all_cnst = 0;
12646 }
12647 bndast = ADD_EXTNTAST(mem_dtype, i);
12648 if (bndast) {
12649 AD_EXTNTAST(bd, i) = remove_parent_from_ast(bndast);
12650 }
12651 }
12652
12653 if (all_cnst)
12654 return 1;
12655
12656 AD_DEFER(bd) = AD_DEFER(ad);
12657 /* Step 2: Fill in parent into new array descriptor */
12658 ad = bd;
12659
12660 all_cnst = 1;
12661 zbase = AD_ZBASE(ad);
12662 if (zbase && A_TYPEG(zbase)) {
12663 AD_ZBASE(ad) = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, zbase);
12664 }
12665 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++) {
12666 bndast = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
12667 if (bndast) {
12668 AD_LWAST(ad, i) = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, bndast);
12669 if (A_TYPEG(AD_LWAST(ad, i)) != A_CNST)
12670 all_cnst = 0;
12671 }
12672 bndast = AD_UPAST(ad, i);
12673 if (bndast) {
12674 AD_UPAST(ad, i) = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, bndast);
12675 if (A_TYPEG(AD_UPAST(ad, i)) != A_CNST)
12676 all_cnst = 0;
12677 }
12678 bndast = AD_EXTNTAST(ad, i);
12679 if (bndast) {
12680 AD_EXTNTAST(ad, i) = add_parent_to_bounds(parent, bndast);
12681 }
12682 }
12683
12684 DTYPEP(mem, new_dtype);
12685
12686 return all_cnst;
12687}
12688
12689/*
12690 * insert an assignment statement
12691 */
12692static int
12693insert_assign(int lhs, int rhs, int std)
12694{
12695 int newasn, newstd;
12696 if (lhs == rhs)
12697 return std;
12698 newasn = mk_assn_stmt(lhs, rhs, 0);
12699 newstd = add_stmt_after(newasn, std);
12700 return newstd;
12701} /* insert_assign */
12702
12703static int
12704get_header_member(int sdsc_ast, int info)
12705{
12706 int ast;
12707 int subs[1];
12708
12709 subs[0] = mk_isz_cval(info, astb.bnd.dtype);
12710 ast = mk_subscr(sdsc_ast, subs, 1, astb.bnd.dtype);
12711 return ast;
12712}
12713
12714static int
12715size_of_dtype(DTYPE dtype, SPTR sptr, int memberast)
12716{
12717 int sizeAst;
12718 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR) {
12719 /* assumed length character */
12720 if (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR) {
12721 sizeAst = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_lena), astb.bnd.dtype);
12722 sizeAst = begin_call(A_FUNC, sizeAst, 1);
12723 add_arg(check_member(memberast, mk_id(sptr)));
12724 } else {
12725 int clen;
12726 clen = DTY(dtype + 1);
12727 if (A_ALIASG(clen)) {
12728 sizeAst = A_ALIASG(clen);
12729 } else {
12730 sizeAst = clen;
12731 }
12732 sizeAst = mk_bnd_int(sizeAst);
12733 }
12734 } else {
12735 sizeAst = mk_isz_cval(size_of(dtype), astb.bnd.dtype);
12736 }
12737 return sizeAst;
12738}
12739
12740int
12741init_sdsc(int sptr, DTYPE dtype, int before_std, int parent_sptr)
12742{
12743 int sptrsdsc = SDSCG(sptr);
12744 ADSC *ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
12745 int ndims = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
12746 int nargs = 5 + ndims * 2;
12747 int argt = mk_argt(nargs);
12748 int fsptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_template), DT_NONE);
12749 int sptrsdsc_arg, ast, i, std;
12750
12751 assert(sptrsdsc > NOSYM, "init_sdsc: sptr has no SDSC", sptr, ERR_Fatal);
12752 sptrsdsc_arg = mk_id(sptrsdsc);
12753 if (STYPEG(sptrsdsc) == ST_MEMBER) {
12754 assert(STYPEG(sptrsdsc) != ST_MEMBER || parent_sptr > NOSYM,
12755 "init_sdsc: sptrdsc is member but no parent sptr", sptrsdsc,
12756 ERR_Fatal);
12757 sptrsdsc_arg = mk_member(mk_id(parent_sptr), sptrsdsc_arg, dtype);
12758 }
12759
12760 /* call RTE_template(desc, rank, flags, kind, len, {lb, ub}+) */
12761 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = sptrsdsc_arg;
12762 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = mk_isz_cval(ndims, astb.bnd.dtype);
12763 ARGT_ARG(argt, 2) = mk_isz_cval(0, astb.bnd.dtype);
12764 ARGT_ARG(argt, 3) = mk_isz_cval(dtype_to_arg(dtype + 1), astb.bnd.dtype);
12765 ARGT_ARG(argt, 4) = size_of_dtype(DDTG(dtype), sptr, 0);
12766
12767 for (i = 0; i < ndims; ++i) {
12768 ARGT_ARG(argt, 5 + 2 * i) = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
12769 ARGT_ARG(argt, 6 + 2 * i) = AD_UPAST(ad, i);
12770 }
12771
12772 ast =
12773 mk_func_node(A_CALL, mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_template), DT_NONE)),
12774 nargs, argt);
12775 SDSCINITP(sptr, TRUE);
12776 A_DTYPEP(ast, DT_INT);
12777 NODESCP(fsptr, TRUE);
12778 std = add_stmt_before(ast, before_std);
12779
12780 /* call pghpf_instance(dest desc, targ desc, kind,len, 0) */
12781 argt = mk_argt(nargs = 5);
12782 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = sptrsdsc_arg;
12783 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = sptrsdsc_arg;
12784 ARGT_ARG(argt, 2) = mk_isz_cval(dtype_to_arg(dtype + 1), astb.bnd.dtype);
12785 ARGT_ARG(argt, 3) = size_of_dtype(DDTG(dtype), sptr, ast);
12786 ARGT_ARG(argt, 4) = mk_isz_cval(0, astb.bnd.dtype);
12787
12788 ast =
12789 mk_func_node(A_CALL, mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_instance), DT_NONE)),
12790 nargs, argt);
12791 return add_stmt_after(ast, std);
12792}
12793
12794/** \brief Similar to init_sdsc() above, but it's also used to initialize
12795 * a descriptor's bounds from a subscript expression.
12796 *
12797 * \param sptr is the symbol table pointer of the symbol with the descriptor
12798 * to initialize.
12799 * \param dtype is the dtype used for initializing the descriptor.
12800 * \param before_std is the statement descriptor where we want to insert the
12801 * initialization code (inserted before this std).
12802 * \param parent_sptr is the symbol table pointer of the enclosing object
12803 * if sptr is an ST_MEMBER. Otherwise, it can be 0.
12804 * \param subscr is an AST representing the subscript expression that contains
12805 * the array bounds. If it's not an A_SUBSCR, then init_sdsc() is
12806 * called instead.
12807 * \param td_ast is an AST representing the descriptor that we are creating
12808 * an instance of.
12809 *
12810 * \return a statement descriptor of the generated statements.
12811 */
12812int
12813init_sdsc_bounds(SPTR sptr, DTYPE dtype, int before_std, SPTR parent_sptr,
12814 int subscr, int td_ast)
12815{
12816 SPTR sptrsdsc = SDSCG(sptr);
12817 ADSC *ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
12818 int ndims = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
12819 int nargs = 5 + ndims * 2;
12820 int argt = mk_argt(nargs);
12821 SPTR fsptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_template), DT_NONE);
12822 int sptrsdsc_arg, ast, i, std;
12823 int asd, triplet, stride;
12824
12825 if (!subscr || A_TYPEG(subscr) != A_SUBSCR) {
12826 return init_sdsc(sptr, dtype, before_std, parent_sptr);
12827 }
12828 assert(sptrsdsc > NOSYM, "init_sdsc_bounds: sptr has no SDSC", sptr,
12829 ERR_Fatal);
12830 sptrsdsc_arg = mk_id(sptrsdsc);
12831 if (STYPEG(sptrsdsc) == ST_MEMBER) {
12832 assert(STYPEG(sptrsdsc) != ST_MEMBER || parent_sptr > NOSYM,
12833 "init_sdsc_bounds: sptrdsc is member but no parent sptr", sptrsdsc,
12834 ERR_Fatal);
12835 sptrsdsc_arg = mk_member(mk_id(parent_sptr), sptrsdsc_arg, dtype);
12836 }
12837
12838 /* call RTE_template(desc, rank, flags, kind, len, {lb, ub}+) */
12839 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = sptrsdsc_arg;
12840 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = mk_isz_cval(ndims, astb.bnd.dtype);
12841 ARGT_ARG(argt, 2) = mk_isz_cval(0, astb.bnd.dtype);
12842 ARGT_ARG(argt, 3) = mk_isz_cval(dtype_to_arg(dtype + 1), astb.bnd.dtype);
12843 ARGT_ARG(argt, 4) = size_of_dtype(DDTG(dtype), sptr, 0);
12844
12845 asd = A_ASDG(subscr);
12846 for (i = 0; i < ndims; ++i) {
12847 triplet = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
12848 if ((stride = A_STRIDEG(triplet)) != 0 && A_TYPEG(stride) == A_CNST &&
12849 ad_val_of(A_SPTRG(stride)) < 0) {
12850 ARGT_ARG(argt, 5 + 2 * i) = mk_bnd_int(A_UPBDG(triplet));
12851 ARGT_ARG(argt, 6 + 2 * i) = mk_bnd_int(A_LBDG(triplet));
12852 } else {
12853 ARGT_ARG(argt, 5 + 2 * i) = mk_bnd_int(A_LBDG(triplet));
12854 ARGT_ARG(argt, 6 + 2 * i) = mk_bnd_int(A_UPBDG(triplet));
12855 }
12856 }
12857
12858 ast =
12859 mk_func_node(A_CALL, mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_template), DT_NONE)),
12860 nargs, argt);
12861 SDSCINITP(sptr, TRUE);
12862 A_DTYPEP(ast, DT_INT);
12863 NODESCP(fsptr, TRUE);
12864 std = add_stmt_before(ast, before_std);
12865
12866 /* call pghpf_instance(dest desc, targ desc, kind,len, 0) */
12867 argt = mk_argt(nargs = 5);
12868 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = td_ast != 0 ? td_ast : sptrsdsc_arg;
12869 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = sptrsdsc_arg;
12870 ARGT_ARG(argt, 2) = mk_isz_cval(dtype_to_arg(dtype + 1), astb.bnd.dtype);
12871 ARGT_ARG(argt, 3) = size_of_dtype(DDTG(dtype), sptr, ast);
12872 ARGT_ARG(argt, 4) = mk_isz_cval(0, astb.bnd.dtype);
12873
12874 ast =
12875 mk_func_node(A_CALL, mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_instance), DT_NONE)),
12876 nargs, argt);
12877 return add_stmt_after(ast, std);
12878}
12879
12880static int
12881genPolyAsn(int dest, int src, int std, int parentMem)
12882{
12883 int argt, flag_con, astdest, dest_sdsc_ast, astsrc, src_sdsc_ast, fsptr;
12884 int ast;
12885
12886 astsrc = mk_id(src);
12887
12888 if (!parentMem) {
12889 if (!SDSCG(dest))
12890 get_static_descriptor(dest);
12891
12892 dest_sdsc_ast = mk_id(SDSCG(dest));
12893
12894 astdest = mk_id(dest);
12895 } else {
12896 int sdsc_mem = get_member_descriptor(dest);
12897 if (sdsc_mem > NOSYM) {
12898 int parentDty = DTYPEG(sym_of_ast(parentMem));
12899 if (DTY(parentDty) == TY_ARRAY)
12900 parentDty = DTY(parentDty + 1);
12901 dest_sdsc_ast = check_member(parentMem, mk_id(sdsc_mem));
12902 } else {
12903 if (!SDSCG(dest)) {
12904 get_static_descriptor(dest);
12905 }
12906 dest_sdsc_ast = mk_id(SDSCG(dest));
12907 }
12908
12909 astdest = check_member(parentMem, mk_id(dest));
12910 }
12911
12912 src_sdsc_ast = mk_id(get_static_type_descriptor(src));
12913 if (dest_sdsc_ast) {
12914 std = gen_set_type(dest_sdsc_ast, src_sdsc_ast, std, FALSE, FALSE);
12915 }
12916
12917 std = add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0), std);
12918 std = init_sdsc(dest, parentMem ? A_DTYPEG(parentMem) : DTYPEG(dest), std,
12919 parentMem ? sym_of_ast(parentMem) : 0);
12920
12921 fsptr = sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_poly_asn), DT_NONE);
12922 argt = mk_argt(5);
12923 flag_con = mk_cval1(1, DT_INT);
12924 flag_con = mk_unop(OP_VAL, flag_con, DT_INT);
12925 ARGT_ARG(argt, 4) = flag_con;
12926
12927 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = astdest;
12928 ARGT_ARG(argt, 1) = dest_sdsc_ast;
12929 ARGT_ARG(argt, 2) = astsrc;
12930 ARGT_ARG(argt, 3) = src_sdsc_ast;
12931 ast = mk_id(fsptr);
12932 ast = mk_func_node(A_CALL, ast, 5, argt);
12933 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
12934
12935 return std;
12936}
12937
12938static int
12939gen_kind_parm_assignments(SPTR sptr, DTYPE dtype, int std, int flag)
12940{
12941 int mem, val, con;
12942 int ast, ast2;
12943 int sdsc_mem, i, j;
12944 int pass;
12945 int memDtype;
12946 int orig_dtype;
12947 int exit_std;
12948 static int parentMem = 0;
12949 static int firstAllocStd = 0;
12950
12951 orig_dtype = dtype;
12952 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
12953 dtype = DTY(dtype + 1);
12954 }
12955 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_DERIVED ||
12956 (!flag && (ALLOCATTRG(sptr) || POINTERG(sptr)) && SCG(sptr) != SC_DUMMY))
12957 return std;
12958 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_ARRAY || DTY(orig_dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
12959 /* This code creates an array of PDTs. It first creates a scalar PDT object.
12960 * We then recursively call gen_kind_parm_assignments() on that object to
12961 * initialize the components that use the PDT's type parameters.
12962 * The firstAllocStd static variable is set to the std of the first
12963 * init code of a component that uses one of more type parameters. If
12964 * firstAllocStd is not set (i.e., it's -1) after the call to
12965 * gen_kind_parm_assignments(), then just return std. In this case, we
12966 * have a PDT with type parameters, but no components that use those type
12967 * parameters. If firstAllocStd > -1, then we have a PDT that uses
12968 * the type parameters. We use our temporary PDT (i.e., tmp) to create an
12969 * array of these by cloning it into each element of the array. This is very
12970 * similar to sourced allocation (e.g.,allocate(pdt_array(n),source=pdt)).
12971 * In fact, we clone tmp by calling the RTE_poly_asn() rte routine.
12972 * This routine is also called when we perform sourced allocation.
12973 * Although our technique is similar to source allocation, this code also
12974 * works with non-allocatable arrays.
12975 */
12976 int tmp = getccsym_sc('d', sem.dtemps++, ST_VAR, SC_STATIC);
12977 DTYPEP(tmp, dtype);
12978 firstAllocStd = -1;
12979 gen_kind_parm_assignments(tmp, dtype, std, flag);
12980 if (firstAllocStd > -1) {
12981 std = firstAllocStd;
12982 std = genPolyAsn(sptr, tmp, std, parentMem);
12983 }
12984 firstAllocStd = std;
12985 return std;
12986 }
12987 for (pass = 0; pass <= 1; ++pass) {
12988 for (mem = DTY(dtype + 1); mem > NOSYM; mem = SYMLKG(mem)) {
12989 memDtype = DTYPEG(mem);
12990 if (pass && DTY(memDtype) == TY_ARRAY && has_type_parameter(memDtype)) {
12991 int origParentMem = parentMem;
12992 int eleDtype = DTY(memDtype + 1);
12993 parentMem = (!parentMem) ? mk_member(mk_id(sptr), mk_id(mem), eleDtype)
12994 : mk_member(parentMem, mk_id(mem), eleDtype);
12995 std = gen_kind_parm_assignments(mem, memDtype, std, flag);
12996 parentMem = origParentMem;
12997 continue;
12998 }
12999 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY && !flag) {
13000 continue;
13001 }
13002 if (PARENTG(mem)) {
13003 std = gen_kind_parm_assignments(sptr, DTYPEG(mem), std, flag);
13004 continue;
13005 }
13006 if ((!LENPARMG(mem) || A_TYPEG(LENG(mem)) == A_CNST) && SETKINDG(mem) &&
13007 !USEKINDG(mem) && (val = KINDG(mem))) {
13008 if (!pass) {
13009 con = mk_cval1(val, DT_INT);
13010 ast = add_parent_to_bounds(mk_id(sptr), mk_id(mem));
13011 ast = mk_assn_stmt(ast, con, DT_INT);
13012 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
13013 }
13014 } else if (LENPARMG(mem) && SETKINDG(mem) && !USEKINDG(mem) &&
13015 (val = KINDG(mem)) && LENG(mem)) {
13016 if (!pass) {
13017 ast = add_parent_to_bounds(mk_id(sptr), mk_id(mem));
13018 ast2 = LENG(mem);
13019 ast = mk_assn_stmt(ast, ast2, DT_INT);
13020 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
13021 }
13022 } else if (SETKINDG(mem) && !USEKINDG(mem) && KINDG(mem) &&
13023 (val = PARMINITG(mem))) {
13024 if (!pass) {
13025 con = mk_cval1(val, DT_INT);
13026 ast = add_parent_to_bounds(mk_id(sptr), mk_id(mem));
13027 ast = mk_assn_stmt(ast, con, DT_INT);
13028 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
13029 }
13030 } else if (INITKINDG(mem) && (val = PARMINITG(mem))) {
13031 if (!pass) {
13032 if (!chk_kind_parm_expr(val, dtype, 0, 1)) {
13033 char *buf;
13034 int len;
13035 len = strlen("Initialization must be a constant"
13036 " expression for component in object") +
13037 strlen(SYMNAME(mem)) + 1;
13038 buf = getitem(0, len);
13039 sprintf(buf,
13040 "Initialization must be a constant"
13041 " expression for component %s in object",
13042 SYMNAME(mem));
13043 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, buf, SYMNAME(sptr));
13044 } else {
13045 val = chk_kind_parm_set_expr(val, dtype);
13046 if (A_TYPEG(val) == A_CNST) {
13047 if (USELENG(mem)) {
13048 error(155, 4, gbl.lineno,
13049 "Length type parameters may not be "
13050 "used with type components that have default "
13051 "initialization -",
13052 SYMNAME(mem));
13053 }
13054 ast = add_parent_to_bounds(mk_id(sptr), mk_id(mem));
13055 ast = mk_assn_stmt(ast, val, DT_INT);
13056 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
13057 } else {
13058 char *buf;
13059 int len;
13060 len = strlen("Initialization must be a constant"
13061 " expression for component in object") +
13062 strlen(SYMNAME(mem)) + 1;
13063 buf = getitem(0, len);
13064 sprintf(buf,
13065 "Initialization must be a constant"
13066 " expression for component %s in object",
13067 SYMNAME(mem));
13068 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, buf, SYMNAME(sptr));
13069 }
13070 }
13071 }
13072 } else if (USELENG(mem) &&
13073 /*ALLOCG(mem) &&*/ DTY(DTYPEG(mem)) == TY_ARRAY) {
13074 if (pass) {
13075 i = mk_id(sptr);
13076 if (flag)
13077 fix_mem_bounds2(i, mem);
13078
13079 ast = mk_stmt(A_ALLOC, 0);
13080 A_TKNP(ast, TK_ALLOCATE);
13081 j = mk_member(i, mk_id(mem), dtype);
13082 A_SRCP(ast, j);
13083 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
13084 if (firstAllocStd < 0)
13085 firstAllocStd = std;
13086 std = add_stmt_before(mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0), std);
13087 std = init_sdsc(mem, DTYPEG(mem), std, sptr);
13088
13089 if (!flag && (gbl.rutype != RU_PROG || CONSTRUCTSYMG(sptr))) {
13090 exit_std = CONSTRUCTSYMG(sptr) ? STD_PREV(BLOCK_EXIT_STD(sptr)) :
13091 gbl.exitstd;
13092 i = mk_stmt(A_ALLOC, 0);
13093 A_TKNP(i, TK_DEALLOCATE);
13094 A_SRCP(i, j);
13095 A_DALLOCMEMP(i, 1);
13096 add_stmt_after(i, exit_std);
13097 }
13098 }
13099 } else if (USELENG(mem) && ALLOCG(mem) && DTY(DTYPEG(mem)) == TY_CHAR &&
13100 LENG(mem)) {
13101 if (pass) {
13102 int src_ast;
13103
13104 sdsc_mem = SDSCG(mem);
13105 sdsc_mem = mk_member(mk_id(sptr), mk_id(sdsc_mem), dtype);
13106 sdsc_mem = get_header_member(sdsc_mem, get_byte_len_indx());
13107
13108 ast = mk_stmt(A_ALLOC, 0);
13109 A_TKNP(ast, TK_ALLOCATE);
13110 src_ast = add_parent_to_bounds(mk_id(sptr), mk_id(mem));
13111 A_SRCP(ast, src_ast);
13112 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
13113 if (firstAllocStd < 0)
13114 firstAllocStd = std;
13115
13116 std = insert_assign(sdsc_mem, LENG(mem), std);
13117
13118 if (!flag && (gbl.rutype != RU_PROG || CONSTRUCTSYMG(sptr))) {
13119 exit_std = CONSTRUCTSYMG(sptr) ? STD_PREV(BLOCK_EXIT_STD(sptr)) :
13120 gbl.exitstd;
13121 i = mk_stmt(A_ALLOC, 0);
13122 A_TKNP(i, TK_DEALLOCATE);
13123 A_SRCP(i, A_SRCG(ast));
13124 A_DALLOCMEMP(i, 1);
13125 add_stmt_after(i, exit_std);
13126 }
13127 }
13128 } else if (!SETKINDG(mem) && !USEKINDG(mem) && KINDG(mem) &&
13129 !PARMINITG(mem)) {
13130 int len;
13131 char *buf;
13132 len = strlen(SYMNAME(mem)) + strlen(SYMNAME(sptr)) +
13133 strlen("Missing value for kind type parameter in") + 1;
13134 buf = getitem(0, len);
13135 sprintf(buf, "Missing value for kind type parameter %s in %s",
13136 SYMNAME(mem), SYMNAME(sptr));
13137 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, buf, CNULL);
13138 }
13139 }
13140 }
13141 return std;
13142}
13143
13144void
13145fix_type_param_members(SPTR sptr, DTYPE dtype)
13146{
13147
13148 int mem, i, ast;
13149 for (mem = DTY(dtype + 1); mem > NOSYM; mem = SYMLKG(mem)) {
13150 if (USELENG(mem) && ALLOCG(mem) && DTY(DTYPEG(mem)) == TY_ARRAY) {
13151 i = mk_id(sptr);
13152 fix_mem_bounds(i, mem);
13153 } else if (USELENG(mem) && ALLOCG(mem) && DTY(DTYPEG(mem)) == TY_CHAR &&
13154 LENG(mem)) {
13155 ast = add_parent_to_bounds(mk_id(sptr), LENG(mem));
13156 LENP(mem, ast);
13157 DTY(DTYPEG(mem) + 1) = ast;
13158 }
13159 }
13160}
13161
13162void
13163gen_type_initialize_for_sym(SPTR sptr, int std, int flag, DTYPE dtype2)
13164{
13165 DTYPE orig_dtype = dtype2 ? dtype2 : DTYPEG(sptr);
13166 DTYPE dtype = orig_dtype;
13167
13168 if (is_array_dtype(dtype))
13169 dtype = array_element_dtype(dtype);
13170 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED) {
13171 if (std < 0) {
13172 int ast = mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0);
13173 std = add_stmt(ast);
13174 }
13175 gen_kind_parm_assignments(sptr, orig_dtype, std, flag);
13176 }
13177}
13178
13179static void
13180gen_alloc_mem_initialize_for_sym2(int sptr, int std, int ast, int visit_flag)
13181{
13182 typedef struct visitDty {
13183 int dty;
13184 struct visitDty *next;
13185 } VISITDTY;
13186
13187 static VISITDTY *visit_list = 0;
13188 VISITDTY *curr, *new_visit, *prev;
13189
13190 int sptrmem, aast, mem_sptr_id, dtype, bast;
13191
13192 dtype = (sptr) ? DTYPEG(sptr) : DTYPEG(memsym_of_ast(ast));
13193
13194 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_DERIVED)
13195 return;
13196
13197 if (visit_list) {
13198 for (curr = visit_list; curr; curr = curr->next) {
13199 if (curr->dty == dtype)
13200 return;
13201 }
13202 }
13203
13204 NEW(new_visit, VISITDTY, 1);
13205 new_visit->dty = dtype;
13206 new_visit->next = visit_list;
13207 visit_list = new_visit;
13208
13209 for (sptrmem = DTY(DDTG(dtype) + 1); sptrmem > NOSYM;
13210 sptrmem = SYMLKG(sptrmem)) {
13211 if (ALLOCATTRG(sptrmem)) {
13212 aast = mk_id(sptrmem);
13213 bast = (ast) ? ast : mk_id(sptr);
13214 mem_sptr_id = mk_member(bast, aast, DTYPEG(sptrmem));
13215 add_stmt_after(add_nullify_ast(mem_sptr_id), std);
13216 } else if (allocatable_member(sptrmem)) {
13217 aast = mk_id(sptrmem);
13218 bast = (ast) ? ast : mk_id(sptr);
13219 bast = mk_member(bast, aast, DTYPEG(sptrmem));
13220 gen_alloc_mem_initialize_for_sym2(0, std, bast, 1);
13221 }
13222 }
13223
13224 if (!visit_flag && visit_list) {
13225 for (prev = curr = visit_list; curr;) {
13226 curr = curr->next;
13227 FREE(prev);
13228 prev = curr;
13229 }
13230 visit_list = 0;
13231 }
13232}
13233
13234void
13235gen_alloc_mem_initialize_for_sym(int sptr, int std)
13236{
13237 gen_alloc_mem_initialize_for_sym2(sptr, std, 0, 0);
13238}
13239
13240static void
13241__gen_conditional_dealloc(int do_cond, int dealloc_item, int after,
13242 int test_presence)
13243{
13244 int argt;
13245 int ifast;
13246 int ast;
13247 int tsptr;
13248 int std;
13249
13250 std = after;
13251 if (do_cond) {
13252 /* generate
13253 * if( allocated(itemp->t.sptr ) then
13254 * deallocate(itemp->t.sptr)
13255 * ifend
13256 */
13257 int present;
13258 if (test_presence) {
13259 present = ast_intr(I_PRESENT, stb.user.dt_log, 1, dealloc_item);
13260 ifast = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
13261 A_IFEXPRP(ifast, present);
13262 std = add_stmt_after(ifast, std);
13263 }
13264 argt = mk_argt(1);
13265 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = dealloc_item;
13266 tsptr = getsymbol("allocated");
13267 ast = mk_id(tsptr);
13268 A_DTYPEP(ast, A_DTYPEG(dealloc_item));
13269 ast = mk_func_node(A_INTR, ast, 1, argt);
13270 A_DTYPEP(ast, stb.user.dt_log);
13271 A_OPTYPEP(ast, I_ALLOCATED);
13272 ifast = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
13273 A_IFEXPRP(ifast, ast);
13274 std = add_stmt_after(ifast, std);
13275 }
13276
13277 ast = mk_stmt(A_ALLOC, 0);
13278 A_TKNP(ast, TK_DEALLOCATE);
13279 A_SRCP(ast, dealloc_item);
13280 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
13281
13282 if (do_cond) {
13283 std = add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0), std);
13284 if (test_presence)
13285 std = add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0), std);
13286 }
13287}
13288
13289void
13290gen_conditional_dealloc(int do_cond, int dealloc_item, int after)
13291{
13292 __gen_conditional_dealloc(do_cond, dealloc_item, after, 0);
13293}
13294
13295int
13296gen_conditional_alloc(int cond, int alloc_item, int after)
13297{
13298 int argt;
13299 int ifast;
13300 int ast;
13301 int tsptr;
13302
13303 /* generate
13304 * if( allocated(cond) ) then
13305 * allocate(alloc_item)
13306 * ifend
13307 */
13308 if (cond) {
13309 argt = mk_argt(1);
13310 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = cond;
13311 tsptr = getsymbol("allocated");
13312 ast = mk_id(tsptr);
13313 A_DTYPEP(ast, A_DTYPEG(cond));
13314 ast = mk_func_node(A_INTR, ast, 1, argt);
13315 A_DTYPEP(ast, stb.user.dt_log);
13316 A_OPTYPEP(ast, I_ALLOCATED);
13317 ifast = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
13318 A_IFEXPRP(ifast, ast);
13319 after = add_stmt_after(ifast, after);
13320 }
13321
13322 ast = mk_stmt(A_ALLOC, 0);
13323 A_TKNP(ast, TK_ALLOCATE);
13324 A_LOPP(ast, 0);
13325 A_SRCP(ast, alloc_item);
13326 after = add_stmt_after(ast, after);
13327
13328 if (cond)
13329 after = add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0), after);
13330 return after;
13331}
13332
13333void
13334gen_conditional_dealloc_for_sym(int sptr, int std)
13335{
13336 int idast = mk_id(sptr);
13337 if (SCG(sptr) != SC_LOCAL) {
13338 if (flg.smp && gbl.internal > 1) {
13339 int scope = SCOPEG(sptr);
13340 if (scope && scope == SCOPEG(gbl.currsub)) {
13341 return;
13342 }
13343 }
13344 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY && OPTARGG(sptr))
13345 __gen_conditional_dealloc(1, idast, std, 1);
13346 else
13347 __gen_conditional_dealloc(1, idast, std, 0);
13348 } else {
13349 /* must be derived type scalar or array which contains allocatable
13350 * components.
13351 */
13352 int ast;
13353 ast = mk_stmt(A_ALLOC, 0);
13354 A_TKNP(ast, TK_DEALLOCATE);
13355 A_SRCP(ast, idast);
13356 (void)add_stmt_after(ast, std);
13357 }
13358}
13359
13360int
13361gen_dealloc_for_sym(int sptr, int std)
13362{
13363 int idast;
13364 int ast;
13365 int ss;
13366
13367 idast = mk_id(sptr);
13368 ast = mk_stmt(A_ALLOC, 0);
13369 A_TKNP(ast, TK_DEALLOCATE);
13370 A_SRCP(ast, idast);
13371 ss = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
13372 return ss;
13373}
13374
13375/** \brief This function initializes the type in a descriptor for an object
13376 * with an intrinsic type.
13377 *
13378 * This function generates a call to set_intrin_type() before the statement
13379 * descriptor, \param std.
13380 *
13381 * \param ast is the ast of the object that has a descriptor that needs to be
13382 * initialized.
13383 * \param sptr is the symbol table pointer of the object that has a descriptor
13384 * that needs to be initialized.
13385 * \param std is the statement descriptor that indicates where to add the call
13386 * to set_intrin_type().
13387 *
13388 * \return the std after the set_intrin_type() call.
13389 */
13390static int
13391init_intrin_type_desc(int ast, SPTR sptr, int std)
13392{
13393
13394
13395 int type_ast;
13396 SPTR sdsc = STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER ? get_member_descriptor(sptr) :
13397 SDSCG(sptr);
13398 int sdsc_ast = STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER ?
13399 check_member(ast, mk_id(sdsc)) :
13400 mk_id(sdsc);
13401 DTYPE dtype = DDTG(DTYPEG(sptr));
13402 int intrin_type;
13403
13404#if DEBUG
13405 assert(DT_ISBASIC(dtype), "init_intrin_type_desc: not basic dtype for ast",
13406 ast, 4);
13407#endif
13408 intrin_type = mk_cval(dtype_to_arg(dtype), astb.bnd.dtype);
13409 intrin_type = mk_unop(OP_VAL, intrin_type, astb.bnd.dtype);
13410 type_ast = mk_set_type_call(sdsc_ast, intrin_type, TRUE);
13411 std = add_stmt_after(type_ast, std);
13412 return std;
13413}
13414
13415/** \brief Generate (re)allocation code for deferred length character objects
13416 * and traditional character objects that are allocatable scalars.
13417 *
13418 * This is typically used in generating (re)allocation code in
13419 * an assignment to an allocatable/deferred length character object.
13420 *
13421 * Reallocation code is generated for deferred length character
13422 * objects.
13423 *
13424 * For traditional character allocatable scalars, we allocate
13425 * the object if it has not already been allocated; we do not
13426 * generate reallocation code since the amount of space allocated
13427 * is fixed with traditional character allocatable objects.
13428 *
13429 * We update the character length descriptor information for
13430 * both deferred length and traditional character objects. This
13431 * is needed for proper I/O such as namelist processing.
13432 *
13433 * \param lhs is the ast of the object getting (re)allocated.
13434 * \param rhs is the ast of the object that supplies the character length.
13435 * \param std is the statement descriptor where we insert the (re)allocation
13436 * and/or length assignment code.
13437 */
13438void
13439gen_automatic_reallocation(int lhs, int rhs, int std)
13440{
13441
13442 int ast, len_stmt;
13443 int tsptr;
13444 int argt;
13445 int ifast, innerifast, binopast;
13446 int lhs_len, rhs_len;
13447 DTYPE dtypedest = A_DTYPEG(lhs);
13448
13449 /* generate the following for deferred length character objects:
13450 *
13451 * if( allocated(lhs) ) then
13452 * if(len(lhs) .ne. len(rhs)) then
13453 * deallocate(lhs)
13454 * lhs$len = rhs$len
13455 * allocate(lhs, len=lhs$len)
13456 * ifend
13457 * else
13458 * lhs$len = rhs$len
13459 * allocate(lhs, len=lhs$len)
13460 * ifend
13461 *
13462 * generate the following for traditional character allocatable objects:
13463 *
13464 * if( allocated(lhs) ) then
13465 * if(len(lhs) .ne. len(rhs)) then
13466 * lhs$len = rhs$len
13467 * ifend
13468 * else
13469 * lhs$len = rhs$len
13470 * allocate(lhs, len=the_declared_length)
13471 * ifend
13472 */
13473
13474 ifast = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
13475
13476 argt = mk_argt(1);
13477 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = lhs;
13478 tsptr = getsymbol("allocated");
13479 ast = mk_id(tsptr);
13480 A_DTYPEP(ast, A_DTYPEG(lhs));
13481 ast = mk_func_node(A_INTR, ast, 1, argt);
13482 A_DTYPEP(ast, stb.user.dt_log);
13483 A_OPTYPEP(ast, I_ALLOCATED);
13484 A_IFEXPRP(ifast, ast);
13485 std = add_stmt_before(ifast, std);
13486
13487 innerifast = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
13488 A_IFSTMTP(ifast, innerifast);
13489
13490 lhs_len = size_ast_of(lhs, DDTG(A_DTYPEG(lhs)));
13491 if (A_TYPEG(rhs) == A_FUNC) {
13492 /* need to get the interface from the A_FUNC ast. */
13493 int sym, iface = 0;
13494 sym = procsym_of_ast(A_LOPG(rhs));
13495 proc_arginfo(sym, NULL, NULL, &iface);
13496 rhs_len = string_expr_length(mk_id(iface));
13497 } else {
13498 rhs_len = string_expr_length(rhs);
13499 }
13500 binopast = mk_binop(OP_NE, lhs_len, rhs_len, DT_LOG);
13501 A_IFEXPRP(innerifast, binopast);
13502 std = add_stmt_after(innerifast, std);
13503
13504 if (dtypedest == DT_DEFERCHAR || dtypedest == DT_DEFERNCHAR) {
13505 /* reallocation is only required for deferred length character objects */
13506 ast = mk_stmt(A_ALLOC, 0);
13507 A_IFSTMTP(innerifast, ast);
13508
13509 A_TKNP(ast, TK_DEALLOCATE);
13510 A_SRCP(ast, lhs);
13511 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
13512 }
13513
13514 len_stmt = mk_assn_stmt(get_len_of_deferchar_ast(lhs), rhs_len, DT_INT);
13515 std = add_stmt_after(len_stmt, std);
13516
13517 if (dtypedest == DT_DEFERCHAR || dtypedest == DT_DEFERNCHAR) {
13518 /* reallocation is only required for deferred length character objects */
13519 ast = mk_stmt(A_ALLOC, 0);
13520 A_TKNP(ast, TK_ALLOCATE);
13521 A_SRCP(ast, lhs);
13522 A_FIRSTALLOCP(ast, 1);
13523 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
13524 }
13525
13526 std = add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0), std);
13527 std = add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_ELSE, 0), std);
13528
13529 len_stmt = mk_assn_stmt(get_len_of_deferchar_ast(lhs), rhs_len, DT_INT);
13530 std = add_stmt_after(len_stmt, std);
13531 ast = mk_stmt(A_ALLOC, 0);
13532 A_TKNP(ast, TK_ALLOCATE);
13533 A_SRCP(ast, lhs);
13534 A_FIRSTALLOCP(ast, 1);
13535 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
13536
13537 std = init_intrin_type_desc(lhs, memsym_of_ast(lhs), std);
13538
13539 add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0), std);
13540
13541 check_and_add_auto_dealloc_from_ast(lhs);
13542}
13543
13544/** \brief Check whether there is a subprogram statement; if not, create a
13545 dummy program symbol, and use that as the program.
13546 */
13547void
13548dummy_program()
13549{
13550 if (sem.scope_level == 0) {
13551 const char *tname;
13552 int sptr;
13553 /* get a symbol to be the outer scope */
13554 tname = "MAIN";
13555 sptr = declref(getsymbol(tname), ST_ENTRY, 'd');
13556 SYMLKP(sptr, NOSYM);
13557 SCP(sptr, SC_EXTERN);
13558 PARAMCTP(sptr, 0);
13559 FUNCLINEP(sptr, gbl.funcline);
13560 DTYPEP(sptr, DT_NONE);
13561 push_scope_level(sptr, SCOPE_NORMAL);
13562 push_scope_level(sptr, SCOPE_SUBPROGRAM);
13563 gbl.currsub = sptr;
13564 /* if the first statement was labelled, set the scope of the label */
13565 if (scn.currlab) {
13566 SCOPEP(scn.currlab, sptr);
13567 }
13568 }
13569} /* dummy_program */
