13571static void
13572rw_host_state(int wherefrom, int (*p_rw)(), FILE *fd)
13573{
13574 if (wherefrom & 0x1) {
13575 rw_semant_state(p_rw, fd);
13576 }
13577 if (wherefrom & 0x10) {
13578 rw_gnr_state(p_rw, fd);
13579 }
13580 if (wherefrom & 0x2) {
13581 rw_sym_state(p_rw, fd);
13582 rw_dtype_state(p_rw, fd);
13583 rw_ast_state(p_rw, fd);
13584 rw_dinit_state(p_rw, fd);
13585 rw_dpmout_state(p_rw, fd);
13586 rw_import_state(p_rw, fd);
13587 }
13588 if (wherefrom & 0x4) {
13589 rw_mod_state(p_rw, fd);
13590 }
13591 if (wherefrom & 0x20) {
13592 rw_semant_state(p_rw, fd);
13593 rw_sym_state(p_rw, fd);
13594 rw_dtype_state(p_rw, fd);
13595 rw_ast_state(p_rw, fd);
13596 rw_dinit_state(p_rw, fd);
13597 rw_dpmout_state(p_rw, fd);
13598 rw_import_state(p_rw, fd);
13599 }
13600} /* rw_host_state */
13601
13602static FILE *state_file = NULL;
13603static FILE *state_append_file = NULL;
13604static int saved_symavl = 0;
13605static int saved_astavl = 0;
13606static int saved_dtyavl = 0;
13607static LOGICAL state_still_pass_one = FALSE;
13608static LOGICAL state_append_file_full = FALSE;
13609static long state_file_position = 0;
13610static int state_last_routine = 0;
13611
13612/* labels for internal subprograms are saved in pass 1, and restored
13613 * in pass 2; they are saved as C strings in a char array;
13614 * the structure of the C array is:
13615 * s u b 1 \000 . L 0 0 1 0 0 \000 s u b 2 \000 . L 0 0 2 0 0 \000
13616 * . L 0 0 3 0 0 \000 s u b 3 \000 s u b 4 \000 . L 0 0 1 0 0 \000 ;
13617 * for four internal subprograms:
13618 * sub1 with label 100
13619 * sub2 with labels 200 and 300
13620 * sub3 with no labels
13621 * sub4 with another label 100
13622 * the semicolon at the end is used to tell when to stop for the last
13623 * subprogram's label list.
13624 */
13625static char *saved_labels = NULL;
13626static int saved_labels_size = 0, saved_labels_avail = 0, saved_labels_pos = 0;
13627
13628/** \brief Called from semant.c to save the semant, sym, dtype, ast, and other
13629 'state' information from a host routine for internal subprograms, for 'pass
13630 1'.
13631 Also, for 'pass 2', save_host_state is called to overwrite the semant state
13632 information.
13633*/
13634void
13635save_host_state(int wherefrom)
13636{
13637 /* use quick binary read/write */
13638 if (state_file) {
13639 if (wherefrom & 0x21) {
13640 /* seek to the beginning before writing first data */
13641 fseek(state_file, 0L, 0);
13642 }
13643 } else {
13644 state_file = tmpfile();
13645 if (state_file == NULL)
13646 errfatal(5);
13647 }
13648 if (wherefrom & 0x2) {
13649 /* clear the SECD field of ST_ARRDSC symbols */
13650 int sptr;
13651 for (sptr = stb.firstusym; sptr < stb.stg_avail; ++sptr) {
13652 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_ARRDSC) {
13653 /* clear SECD field */
13654 SECDP(sptr, 0);
13655 ALNDP(sptr, 0);
13656 }
13657 }
13658 }
13659 rw_host_state(wherefrom, (int (*)())fwrite, state_file);
13660 saved_symavl = stb.stg_avail;
13661 saved_astavl = astb.stg_avail;
13662 saved_dtyavl = stb.dt.stg_avail;
13663} /* save_host_state */
13664
13665#ifdef CLASSG
13666static void
13667fix_invobj(int sptr)
13668{
13669 /* Called by fix_symtab() below. Decrements INVOBJ field of type bound
13670 * procedure due to fix_symtab() removing result argument of function.
13671 */
13672 int sptr2;
13673 for (sptr2 = 1; sptr2 < stb.stg_avail; ++sptr2) {
13674 int bind_sptr;
13675 if (STYPEG(sptr2) == ST_MEMBER && CLASSG(sptr2) && VTABLEG(sptr2) == sptr &&
13676 !NOPASSG(sptr2) && (bind_sptr = BINDG(sptr2)) > NOSYM &&
13677 STYPEG(bind_sptr) == ST_PROC && INVOBJINCG(bind_sptr)) {
13678 INVOBJINCP(bind_sptr, FALSE);
13679 INVOBJP(bind_sptr, INVOBJG(bind_sptr) - 1);
13680 }
13681 }
13682}
13683#endif
13684
13685/* look through restored symbol for array-valued, pointer-valued,
13686 * or other functions that were turned into subprograms. */
13687static void
13688fix_symtab()
13689{
13690 int sptr, i;
13691 for (sptr = aux.list[ST_PROC]; sptr > NOSYM; sptr = SLNKG(sptr)) {
13692 if (!FUNCG(sptr) && FVALG(sptr) > NOSYM) {
13693 /* remake into a function */
13694 FUNCP(sptr, TRUE);
13695 /* Remove first parameter only if it is the
13696 * return value symbol.
13697 */
13698 if (aux.dpdsc_base[DPDSCG(sptr)] == FVALG(sptr)) {
13699#ifdef CLASSG
13700 fix_invobj(sptr);
13701#endif
13702 PARAMCTP(sptr, PARAMCTG(sptr) - 1);
13703 aux.dpdsc_base[DPDSCG(sptr)] = 0; /* clear the reserved fval field */
13704 DPDSCP(sptr, DPDSCG(sptr) + 1);
13705 }
13706 DTYPEP(sptr, DTYPEG(FVALG(sptr)));
13707 }
13708 }
13709#if DEBUG
13710 /* aux.list[ST_PROC] must be terminated with NOSYM, not 0 */
13711 assert(sptr == NOSYM, "fix_symtab: corrupted aux.list[ST_PROC]", sptr, 3);
13712#endif
13713 /* fixing up procedure pointers that contain interfaces and converting it
13714 * back from subroutine to functions.
13715 */
13716 for (i = sem.typroc_avail; sptr > NOSYM; i++) {
13717 int procdt, fval;
13718 procdt = sem.typroc_base[i];
13719 fval = DTY(procdt + 5);
13720 if (!fval)
13721 continue;
13722 sptr = DTY(procdt + 2);
13723 if (!FUNCG(sptr) && FVALG(sptr) > NOSYM) {
13724 FUNCP(sptr, TRUE);
13725 if (aux.dpdsc_base[DPDSCG(sptr)] == FVALG(sptr)) {
13726#ifdef CLASSG
13727 fix_invobj(sptr);
13728#endif
13729 PARAMCTP(sptr, PARAMCTG(sptr) - 1);
13730 aux.dpdsc_base[DPDSCG(sptr)] = 0; /* clear the reserved fval field */
13731 DPDSCP(sptr, DPDSCG(sptr) + 1);
13732 }
13733 DTYPEP(sptr, DTYPEG(FVALG(sptr)));
13734 }
13735 }
13736} /* fix_symtab */
13737
13738/** \brief Called at the end of an internal subprogram.
13739
13740 In pass 1:
13741 - Save the internal subprogram information, kind of like interface blocks.
13742 If there is more than 1 internal subprogram, the information is
13743 exported collectively, that is, all subprograms are exported each time.
13744 - Save any labels for internal subprograms.
13745 These labels are restored by restore_internal_subprograms() below.
13746 - Restores the host information for the next subprogram.
13747 - Reimport any internal subprograms as contained subprograms.
13748 This information will be reimported in pass 2 by
13749 restore_internal_subprograms() below.
13750
13751 In pass 2:
13752 - Restore the host information for the next subprogram,
13753 as this will have been saved by the save_host_state
13754 call for the host subprogram and will include all the contained
13755 subprograms information as imported in restore_internal_subprograms()
13756 for the host routine.
13757 */
13758void
13759restore_host_state(int whichpass)
13760{
13761 if (state_file == NULL)
13762 interr("no state file to restore", 0, 4);
13763
13764 if (whichpass == 2) {
13765 fseek(state_file, 0L, 0);
13766 rw_host_state(0x13, (int (*)())fread, state_file);
13767 /*astb.firstuast = astb.stg_avail;*/
13768 /* ### don't reset firstusym for main program */
13769 stb.firstusym = stb.stg_avail;
13770 state_still_pass_one = 0;
13771 fix_symtab();
13772 } else if (whichpass == 4) { /* for ipa import */
13773 fseek(state_file, 0L, 0);
13774 rw_host_state(0x2, (int (*)())fread, state_file);
13775 /*astb.firstuast = astb.stg_avail;*/
13776 /* ### don't reset firstusym for main program */
13777 stb.firstusym = stb.stg_avail;
13778 state_still_pass_one = 0;
13779 fix_symtab();
13780 } else {
13781 int nw, modbase, smodbase, len, lab, saved_scope;
13782 long end_of_file;
13783 char Mname[100], Sname[100], MMname[100], SSname[100];
13784 /* pass one */
13785 /* write the 'append' symbols into the 'append_file' */
13786 state_append_file_full = TRUE;
13787 if (!state_append_file) {
13788 state_append_file = tmpfile();
13789 if (state_append_file == NULL)
13790 errfatal(5);
13791 state_file_position = 0;
13792 } else {
13793 if (!state_still_pass_one) {
13794 state_file_position = 0;
13795 fseek(state_append_file, state_file_position, 0);
13796 saved_labels_avail = 0;
13797 saved_labels_pos = 0;
13798 } else {
13799 /* what is the containing subprogram;
13800 * this is the subprogram on the top of the scope stack */
13801 if (state_last_routine == sem.scope_stack[sem.scope_level].sptr) {
13802 /* rewind to the last position */
13803 fseek(state_append_file, state_file_position, 0);
13804 } else {
13805 /* leave at the end */
13806 }
13807 }
13808 }
13809 state_last_routine = sem.scope_stack[sem.scope_level].sptr;
13810 modbase = 0;
13811 strcpy(Mname, "--");
13812 strcpy(Sname, SYMNAME(state_last_routine));
13813 if (sem.mod_sym) {
13814 modbase = CMEMFG(sem.mod_sym);
13815 strcpy(Mname, SYMNAME(sem.mod_sym));
13816 }
13817 fflush(state_append_file);
13818 state_file_position = ftell(state_append_file);
13819 /* write identifier to the file */
13820 fprintf(state_append_file, "- %s %s %d %d %d %d %d\n", Mname, Sname,
13821 SCOPEG(gbl.currsub), saved_symavl, saved_astavl, saved_dtyavl,
13822 modbase);
13823 export_append_host_sym(gbl.currsub);
13824 export_host_subprogram(state_append_file, gbl.currsub, saved_symavl,
13825 saved_astavl, saved_dtyavl);
13826 end_of_file = ftell(state_append_file); /* get position */
13827
13828 /* save labels from the internal subprogram */
13829 if (saved_labels == NULL) {
13830 saved_labels_size = 512;
13831 NEW(saved_labels, char, saved_labels_size);
13832 saved_labels_avail = 0;
13833 saved_labels_pos = 0;
13834 }
13835 len = strlen(SYMNAME(gbl.currsub));
13836 /* need len+1 char positions for the null char at the end of the
13837 * string; also need one more for the 'end everything' marker */
13838 NEED(saved_labels_avail + len + 2, saved_labels, char, saved_labels_size,
13839 saved_labels_size + 512);
13840 strcpy(saved_labels + saved_labels_avail, SYMNAME(gbl.currsub));
13841 saved_labels_avail += len + 1;
13842 for (lab = sem.flabels; lab > NOSYM; lab = SYMLKG(lab)) {
13843 len = strlen(SYMNAME(lab));
13844 NEED(saved_labels_avail + len + 2, saved_labels, char, saved_labels_size,
13845 saved_labels_size + 512);
13846 strcpy(saved_labels + saved_labels_avail, SYMNAME(lab));
13847 saved_labels_avail += len + 1;
13848 }
13849 sem.flabels = 0;
13850 saved_labels[saved_labels_avail] = ';';
13851
13852 fseek(state_file, 0L, 0);
13853 rw_host_state(0x3, (int (*)())fread, state_file);
13854 /*astb.firstuast = astb.stg_avail;*/
13855
13856 fseek(state_append_file, state_file_position, 0);
13857 nw = fscanf(state_append_file, "- %s %s %d %d %d %d %d\n", MMname, SSname,
13858 &saved_scope, &saved_symavl, &saved_astavl, &saved_dtyavl,
13859 &smodbase);
13860 if (strcmp(MMname, Mname) != 0 || strcmp(SSname, Sname) != 0 || nw != 7) {
13861 interr("unknown state file error", 0, 4);
13862 }
13863 /* import the contained subprogram symbols */
13864 import_host_subprogram(state_append_file, "state file", saved_symavl,
13865 saved_astavl, saved_dtyavl, 0, 0);
13866 state_still_pass_one = 1;
13867 /* move file for read and write to end of file */
13868 fseek(state_append_file, end_of_file, 0);
13869 }
13870} /* restore_host_state */
13871
13872/** \brief Called at the beginning of a subprogram in pass 2.
13873
13874 - Checks whether there is information available for subprograms
13875 contained in this one, as saved by restore_host_state().
13876 - If so, restores that more or less like an interface block.
13877 - If the current routine is an internal subprogram, its labels are
13878 restored. This is so FORMAT labels that appear in both the inner
13879 and outer subprogram are properly resolved.
13880 */
13881void
13882restore_internal_subprograms(void)
13883{
13884 if (gbl.currsub == 0)
13885 dummy_program();
13886 if (state_append_file && state_append_file_full) {
13887 int nw, last_routine, modbase, nmodbase, moddiff;
13888 int saved_scope;
13889 char Mname[100], Sname[100], MMname[100], SSname[100];
13890 if (state_still_pass_one) {
13891 state_still_pass_one = 0;
13892 state_file_position = 0;
13893 exterf_init_host();
13894 }
13895 nw = fseek(state_append_file, state_file_position, 0);
13896 nw = fscanf(state_append_file, "- %s %s %d %d %d %d %d\n", MMname, SSname,
13897 &saved_scope, &saved_symavl, &saved_astavl, &saved_dtyavl,
13898 &modbase);
13899 /* import the contained subprogram symbols */
13900 if (sem.scope_level) {
13901 last_routine = sem.scope_stack[sem.scope_level].sptr;
13902 strcpy(Sname, SYMNAME(last_routine));
13903 } else {
13904 strcpy(Sname, "MAIN");
13905 }
13906 /* adjust symbols in case they were moved around by module importing */
13907 nmodbase = 0;
13908 strcpy(Mname, "--");
13909 if (sem.mod_sym) {
13910 nmodbase = CMEMFG(sem.mod_sym);
13911 strcpy(Mname, SYMNAME(sem.mod_sym));
13912 }
13913 if (nw == 7 && strcmp(Mname, MMname) == 0 && strcmp(Sname, SSname) == 0) {
13914 moddiff = nmodbase - modbase;
13915 /* this is the information for this routine */
13916 import_host(state_append_file, "state file", saved_symavl, saved_astavl,
13917 saved_dtyavl, modbase, moddiff, saved_scope, stb.curr_scope);
13918 state_file_position = ftell(state_append_file);
13919 }
13920 }
13921 if (gbl.internal > 1) {
13922 /* restore any labels found */
13923 /* compare subprogram name */
13924 char *cp;
13925 cp = saved_labels + saved_labels_pos;
13926 if (strcmp(cp, SYMNAME(gbl.currsub))) {
13927 interr("unknown internal subprogram state error (labels)", gbl.currsub,
13928 4);
13929 }
13930 saved_labels_pos += strlen(cp) + 1;
13931 cp = saved_labels + saved_labels_pos;
13932 while (*cp == '.') {
13933 /* have a label */
13934 int sptr = getsymbol(cp);
13935 if (STYPEG(sptr) != ST_UNKNOWN &&
13936 (STYPEG(sptr) != ST_LABEL || SCOPEG(sptr) != stb.curr_scope)) {
13937 /* this was not a label for this subprogram already */
13938 sptr = insert_sym(sptr);
13939 }
13940 STYPEP(sptr, ST_LABEL);
13941 FMTPTP(sptr, 0);
13942 REFP(sptr, 0);
13943 ADDRESSP(sptr, 0);
13944 SYMLKP(sptr, NOSYM);
13945 SCOPEP(sptr, stb.curr_scope);
13946 saved_labels_pos += strlen(cp) + 1;
13947 cp = saved_labels + saved_labels_pos;
13948 }
13949 }
13950} /* restore_internal_subprograms */
13951
13952void
13953reset_internal_subprograms()
13954{
13955 state_still_pass_one = 0;
13956 state_file_position = 0;
13957 state_append_file_full = FALSE;
13958} /* reset_internal_subprograms */
13959
13960static FILE *modstate_file = NULL;
13961static FILE *modstate_append_file = NULL;
13962static int modsaved_symavl, modsaved_astavl, modsaved_dtyavl;
13963static int modstate_append_file_full = 0;
13964static int mod_clear_init = 0;
13965static LOGICAL modsave_ieee_features;
13966
13967/** \brief Called at a CONTAINS clause
13968
13969 Writes the module information out quickly.
13970 It is split into two pieces: the first only writes out the semant
13971 information, before semfin() deallocates it, and the second appends
13972 everything else, including the module.c tables.
13973 */
13974void
13975save_module_state1()
13976{
13977 if (modstate_file) {
13978 fseek(modstate_file, 0L, 0);
13979 } else {
13980 modstate_file = tmpfile();
13981 if (modstate_file == NULL)
13982 errfatal(5);
13983 }
13984 rw_host_state(0x1, (int (*)())fwrite, modstate_file);
13985} /* save_module_state1 */
13986
13987void
13988save_module_state2()
13989{
13990 rw_host_state(0x16, (int (*)())fwrite, modstate_file);
13991 modsaved_symavl = stb.stg_avail;
13992 modsaved_astavl = astb.stg_avail;
13993 modsaved_dtyavl = stb.dt.stg_avail;
13994 modstate_append_file_full = 0;
13995 mod_clear_init = 1;
13996 modsave_ieee_features = sem.ieee_features;
13997} /* save_module_state2 */
13998
13999static FILE *modsave_file = NULL;
14000
14001void
14002save_imported_modules_state()
14003{
14004 if (modsave_file) {
14005 fseek(modsave_file, 0L, 0);
14006 } else {
14007 modsave_file = tmpfile();
14008 if (modsave_file == NULL)
14009 errfatal(5);
14010 }
14011 rw_host_state(0x20, (int (*)())fwrite, modsave_file);
14012} /* save_imported_modules_state */
14013
14014void
14015restore_imported_modules_state()
14016{
14017 fseek(modsave_file, 0L, 0);
14018 rw_host_state(0x20, (int (*)())fread, modsave_file);
14019} /* restore_imported_modules_state */
14020
14021/*
14022 * consider:
14023 * module b
14024 * public :: f << at this point, we add a variable 'f'
14025 * contains
14026 * integer function f << now here, we add function 'f', hide variable 'f'
14027 * ...
14028 * the problem is that hiding variable 'f' happens too late, we've already
14029 * got all the information for 'f' in modstate_file; so we keep
14030 * track of this situation (semsym.c:replace_variable) and when it
14031 * arises, and we restore the module state, we re-hide 'f'.
14032 * We only need to keep track of a single variable at a time.
14033 */
14034static int module_must_hide_this_symbol_sptr = 0;
14035
14036void
14037module_must_hide_this_symbol(int sptr)
14038{
14039 module_must_hide_this_symbol_sptr = sptr;
14040} /* module_must_hide_this_symbol */
14041
14042/** \brief Called at start of module-contained subprogram, restores state.
14043 If this is the first 'restore' since the last 'reset',
14044 the 'module append' file is full and needs to be imported.
14045 */
14046void
14047restore_module_state()
14048{
14049 if (modstate_file == NULL)
14050 errfatal(5);
14051 /* First, read the binary-saved information */
14052 fseek(modstate_file, 0L, 0);
14053 rw_host_state(0x17, (int (*)())fread, modstate_file);
14054 /* for TPR 1654, if we need to set NEEDMOD for internal
14055 * subprograms, this is the place to set it
14056 * NEEDMODP( stb.curr_scope, 1 );
14057 */
14058 if (modstate_append_file_full) {
14059
14060 /* Next, import the module-contained subprogram */
14061 fseek(modstate_append_file, 0L, 0);
14062 import_host(modstate_append_file, "module state file", modsaved_symavl,
14063 modsaved_astavl, modsaved_dtyavl, 0, 0, 0, 0);
14064 }
14065 if (module_must_hide_this_symbol_sptr) {
14066 HIDDENP(module_must_hide_this_symbol_sptr, 1);
14067 module_must_hide_this_symbol_sptr = 0;
14068 }
14069 if (mod_clear_init) {
14070 /* clear the data-initialized bit for any module-initialized commons */
14071 int sptr;
14072 for (sptr = gbl.cmblks; sptr > NOSYM; sptr = SYMLKG(sptr)) {
14073 DINITP(sptr, 0);
14074 }
14075 }
14076 if (mod_clear_init || modstate_append_file_full) {
14077 modstate_append_file_full = 0;
14078 mod_clear_init = 0;
14079 /* Lastly, rewrite the module state file */
14080 fseek(modstate_file, 0L, 0);
14081 rw_host_state(0x17, (int (*)())fwrite, modstate_file);
14082 modsaved_symavl = stb.stg_avail;
14083 modsaved_astavl = astb.stg_avail;
14084 modsaved_dtyavl = stb.dt.stg_avail;
14085 }
14086 sem.ieee_features = modsave_ieee_features;
14087} /* restore_module_state */
14088
14089/** \brief Called at the end of a module-contained subprogram;
14090 rearranges the data structures for the module.
14091*/
14092void
14093reset_module_state()
14094{
14095 if (modstate_file == NULL)
14096 interr("no module state file to restore", 0, 4);
14097 if (sem.which_pass == 1) {
14098 fseek(modstate_file, 0L, 0);
14099 rw_host_state(0x17, (int (*)())fread, modstate_file);
14100 } else {
14101 /* export the module-contained subprogram */
14102 if (!modstate_append_file) {
14103 modstate_append_file = tmpfile();
14104 if (modstate_append_file == NULL)
14105 errfatal(5);
14106 } else {
14107 fseek(modstate_append_file, 0L, 0);
14108 }
14109 export_module_subprogram(modstate_append_file, gbl.currsub, modsaved_symavl,
14110 modsaved_astavl, modsaved_dtyavl);
14111 modstate_append_file_full = 1;
14112 }
14113} /* reset_module_state */
14114
14115int
14116have_module_state()
14117{
14118 if (modstate_file == NULL)
14119 return 0;
14120 return 1;
14121}
14122
14123/** \brief Compilation is finished - deallocate storage, close files, etc.
14124 */
14125void
14126sem_fini(void)
14127{
14128 if (state_file)
14129 fclose(state_file);
14130 state_file = NULL;
14131 if (state_append_file)
14132 fclose(state_append_file);
14133 state_append_file = NULL;
14134 if (saved_labels) {
14135 FREE(saved_labels);
14136 saved_labels = NULL;
14137 saved_labels_size = 0;
14138 saved_labels_avail = 0;
14139 saved_labels_pos = 0;
14140 }
14141 if (sem.eqv_base) {
14142 FREE(sem.eqv_base);
14143 sem.eqv_base = NULL;
14144 }
14145 if (sem.eqv_ss_base) {
14146 FREE(sem.eqv_ss_base);
14147 sem.eqv_ss_base = NULL;
14148 }
14149 import_fini();
14150 if (sem.non_private_base) {
14151 FREE(sem.non_private_base);
14152 sem.non_private_base = NULL;
14153 }
14154} /* sem_fini */
14155
14156void
14157sem_set_storage_class(int sptr)
14158{
14159 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_ARRAY) {
14160 if (ALLOCG(sptr)) {
14161 SCP(sptr, SC_BASED);
14162 } else if (ASUMSZG(sptr)) {
14163 {
14164 error(50, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
14165 SCP(sptr, SC_DUMMY);
14166 }
14167 } else if (ASSUMLENG(sptr)) {
14168 error(452, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
14169 SCP(sptr, SC_DUMMY);
14170 } else {
14171 SCP(sptr, SC_LOCAL);
14172 if (ADJARRG(sptr) || RUNTIMEG(sptr)) {
14173 add_auto_array(sptr);
14174 if (has_allocattr(sptr)) {
14175 add_auto_dealloc(sptr);
14176 }
14177 } else if (ADJLENG(sptr))
14178 add_auto_char(sptr);
14179 }
14180 } else if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_PROC)
14181 SCP(sptr, SC_EXTERN);
14182 else if (POINTERG(sptr)) {
14183 SCP(sptr, SC_BASED);
14184 if (ADJLENG(sptr))
14185 add_auto_char(sptr);
14186 } else if (!IS_INTRINSIC(STYPEG(sptr))) {
14187/* if an intrinsic, this processing must be deferred until an
14188 * actual scalar reference confirms a nonintrinsic context.
14189 */
14190 SCP(sptr, SC_LOCAL);
14191 if (ADJLENG(sptr))
14192 add_auto_char(sptr);
14193 }
14194}
14195
14196/* ensure that the list of automatic arrays is in
14197 * the order they're declared
14198 */
14199static void
14200add_auto_array(int sptr)
14201{
14202 SCP(sptr, SC_LOCAL);
14203 add_autobj(sptr);
14204 AD_NOBOUNDS(AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptr))) = 1;
14205}
14206
14207/* ensure that the list of automatic arrays is in
14208 * the order they're declared
14209 */
14210static void
14211add_auto_char(int sptr)
14212{
14213 SCP(sptr, SC_LOCAL);
14214 add_autobj(sptr);
14215}
14216
14217static void
14218add_autobj(int sptr)
14219{
14220 static int last_autobj;
14221
14222 if (last_autobj > NOSYM && AUTOBJG(last_autobj) > NOSYM) {
14223 /* last_autobj is invalid */
14224 int next;
14225 last_autobj = 0;
14226 next = gbl.autobj;
14227 while (next > NOSYM) {
14228 last_autobj = next;
14229 next = AUTOBJG(next);
14230 }
14231 }
14232 if (gbl.autobj == NOSYM)
14233 /* first automatic array */
14234 gbl.autobj = sptr;
14235 else
14236 AUTOBJP(last_autobj, sptr);
14237 last_autobj = sptr;
14238 AUTOBJP(sptr, NOSYM);
14239}
14240
14241void
14242dmp_var(VAR *var, int indent, FILE *f)
14243{
14244 int i;
14245 if (f == NULL)
14246 f = stderr;
14247 for (i = 0; i < indent; ++i)
14248 fprintf(f, " ");
14249 switch (var->id) {
14250 case Dostart:
14251 fprintf(f, "Dostart: indvar=%d lowbd=%d upbd=%d step=%d (ASTs)\n",
14252 var->u.dostart.indvar, var->u.dostart.lowbd, var->u.dostart.upbd,
14253 var->u.dostart.step);
14254 break;
14255 case Doend:
14256 fprintf(f, "Doend for:\n");
14257 dmp_var(var->u.doend.dostart, indent + 1, f);
14258 break;
14259 case Varref: {
14260 char typebuf[300];
14261 DTYPE dtype = var->u.varref.dtype;
14262 VAR *members = var->u.varref.subt;
14263 FILE *save_dbgfil = gbl.dbgfil;
14264 getdtype(dtype, typebuf);
14265 /* id is S_* constant */
14266 fprintf(f, "Varref: id=%d ptr=AST:%d:", var->u.varref.id,
14267 var->u.varref.ptr);
14268 gbl.dbgfil = f;
14269 printast(var->u.varref.ptr);
14270 gbl.dbgfil = save_dbgfil;
14271 fprintf(f, " dtype=%d:%s shape=%d\n", dtype, typebuf, var->u.varref.shape);
14272 for (; members != 0; members = members->next) {
14273 dmp_var(members, indent + 1, f);
14274 }
14275 } break;
14276 default:
14277 interr("dmp_var: bad id", var->id, ERR_Severe);
14278 }
14279}
14280
14281void
14282dvar(VAR *var)
14283{
14284 dmp_var(var, 0, stderr);
14285}
14286
14287void
14288dmp_acl(ACL *acl, int indent)
14289{
14290 _dmp_acl(acl, indent, NULL);
14291}
14292
14293static void
14294_dmp_acl(ACL *acl, int indent, FILE *f)
14295{
14296 ACL *c_aclp;
14297 char two_spaces[3] = " ";
14298
14299 if (!acl) {
14300 return;
14301 }
14302
14303 if (f == NULL)
14304 f = stderr;
14305 for (c_aclp = acl; c_aclp; c_aclp = c_aclp->next) {
14306 switch (c_aclp->id) {
14307 case AC_IDENT:
14308 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14309 fprintf(
14310 f,
14311 "AC_IDENT: %d, repeatc=%d, is_const=%d, dtype=%d, sptr=%d, size=%d\n",
14312 c_aclp->u1.ast, c_aclp->repeatc, c_aclp->is_const, c_aclp->dtype,
14313 c_aclp->sptr, c_aclp->size);
14314 break;
14315 case AC_CONST:
14316 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14317 fprintf(
14318 f,
14319 "AC_CONST: %d, repeatc=%d, is_const=%d, dtype=%d, sptr=%d, size=%d\n",
14320 c_aclp->u1.ast, c_aclp->repeatc, c_aclp->is_const, c_aclp->dtype,
14321 c_aclp->sptr, c_aclp->size);
14322 break;
14323 case AC_AST:
14324 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14325 fprintf(
14326 f,
14327 "AC_AST: %d, repeatc=%d, is_const=%d, dtype=%d, sptr=%d, size=%d\n",
14328 c_aclp->u1.ast, c_aclp->repeatc, c_aclp->is_const, c_aclp->dtype,
14329 c_aclp->sptr, c_aclp->size);
14330 break;
14331 case AC_EXPR:
14332 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14333 fprintf(f, "**** AC_EXPR: SST id %d ***\n", SST_IDG(c_aclp->u1.stkp));
14334 break;
14335 case AC_IEXPR:
14336 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14337 fprintf(f,
14338 "AC_IEXPR: op %s, repeatc=%d, is_const=%d, dtype=%d, sptr=%d, "
14339 "size=%d\n",
14340 iexpr_op(c_aclp->u1.expr->op), c_aclp->repeatc, c_aclp->is_const,
14341 c_aclp->dtype, c_aclp->sptr, c_aclp->size);
14342 _dmp_acl(c_aclp->u1.expr->lop, indent + 1, f);
14343 _dmp_acl(c_aclp->u1.expr->rop, indent + 1, f);
14344 break;
14345 case AC_IDO:
14346 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14347 fprintf(f, "AC_IDO: , dtype=%d, sptr=%d, size=%d\n", c_aclp->dtype,
14348 c_aclp->sptr, c_aclp->size);
14349 fprintf(f,
14350 " index var sptr %d, init expr ast %d, "
14351 "limit expr ast %d, step_expr ast %d, repeatc %d\n",
14352 c_aclp->u1.doinfo->index_var, c_aclp->u1.doinfo->init_expr,
14353 c_aclp->u1.doinfo->limit_expr, c_aclp->u1.doinfo->step_expr,
14354 c_aclp->repeatc);
14355 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14356 fprintf(f, " Initialization Values:\n");
14357 _dmp_acl(c_aclp->subc, indent + 1, f);
14358 break;
14359 case AC_ACONST:
14360 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14361 fprintf(f, "AC_ACONST: repeatc %d, dtype=%d, sptr=%d\n", c_aclp->repeatc,
14362 c_aclp->dtype, c_aclp->sptr);
14363 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14364 fprintf(f, " Initialization Values:\n");
14365 _dmp_acl(c_aclp->subc, indent + 1, f);
14366 break;
14367 case AC_SCONST:
14368 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14369 fprintf(f, "AC_SCONST: repeatc %d, dtype=%d, sptr=%d\n", c_aclp->repeatc,
14370 c_aclp->dtype, c_aclp->sptr);
14371 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14372 fprintf(f, " Initialization Values:\n");
14373 _dmp_acl(c_aclp->subc, indent + 1, f);
14374 break;
14375 case AC_TYPEINIT:
14376 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14377 fprintf(f, "AC_TYPEINIT: repeatc %d, dtype=%d, sptr=%d\n",
14378 c_aclp->repeatc, c_aclp->dtype, c_aclp->sptr);
14379 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14380 fprintf(f, " Initialization Values:\n");
14381 _dmp_acl(c_aclp->subc, indent + 1, f);
14382 break;
14383 case AC_ICONST:
14384 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14385 fprintf(f, "AC_ICONST: value %d\n", c_aclp->u1.i);
14386 break;
14387 case AC_REPEAT:
14388 case AC_LIST:
14389 default:
14390 put_prefix(two_spaces, indent, f);
14391 fprintf(f, "*** UNKNOWN/UNUSED ACL ID %d\n", c_aclp->id);
14392 break;
14393 }
14394 }
14395}
14396
14397static void
14398put_prefix(char *str, int cnt, FILE *f)
14399{
14400 int i;
14401
14402 fprintf(f, " ");
14403 for (i = 0; i < cnt; i++)
14404 fprintf(f, "%s", str);
14405}
14406
14407int
14408mp_create_bscope(int reuse)
14409{
14410 int ast = 0, i;
14411 int astid;
14412 int uplevel_sptr = 0;
14413 int scope_sptr = 0;
14414 SPTR parent_sptr;
14415
14416 if (reuse) {
14417 i = sem.scope_level;
14418 scope_sptr = BLK_SCOPE_SPTR(i);
14419 while (scope_sptr == 0 && i) {
14420 scope_sptr = BLK_SCOPE_SPTR(i);
14421 --i;
14422 }
14423 if (scope_sptr == 0) {
14424 goto newscope;
14425 }
14426 ast = mk_stmt(A_MP_BMPSCOPE, 0);
14427 astid = mk_id(scope_sptr);
14428 A_STBLKP(ast, astid);
14429 (void)add_stmt(ast);
14430 return ast;
14431 }
14432newscope:
14433 scope_sptr = getccssym("uplevel", sem.blksymnum++, ST_BLOCK);
14434 PARSYMSCTP(scope_sptr, 0);
14435 PARSYMSP(scope_sptr, 0);
14436 BLK_SCOPE_SPTR(sem.scope_level) = scope_sptr;
14437
14438 /* create a new uplevel_sptr per outlined region */
14439 uplevel_sptr = getccssym("uplevel", sem.blksymnum++, ST_BLOCK);
14440 PARSYMSCTP(uplevel_sptr, 0);
14441 PARSYMSP(uplevel_sptr, 0);
14442 PARUPLEVELP(scope_sptr, uplevel_sptr);
14443 BLK_UPLEVEL_SPTR(sem.scope_level) = uplevel_sptr;
14444 i = sem.scope_level - 1;
14445 parent_sptr = BLK_UPLEVEL_SPTR(i);
14446 while (i > 0 && parent_sptr == 0) {
14447 --i;
14448 parent_sptr = BLK_UPLEVEL_SPTR(i);
14449 }
14450 (void)llmp_create_uplevel(uplevel_sptr);
14451 if (parent_sptr) {
14452 llmp_uplevel_set_parent((SPTR)uplevel_sptr, parent_sptr);
14453 }
14454 ast = mk_stmt(A_MP_BMPSCOPE, 0);
14455 astid = mk_id(scope_sptr);
14456 A_STBLKP(ast, astid);
14457 (void)add_stmt(ast);
14458 return ast;
14459}
14460
14461int
14462mp_create_escope()
14463{
14464 int ast = 0;
14465
14466 ast = mk_stmt(A_MP_EMPSCOPE, 0);
14467 (void)add_stmt(ast);
14468 BLK_UPLEVEL_SPTR(sem.scope_level) = 0;
14469
14470 return ast;
14471}
14472
14473int
14474enter_lexical_block(int gen_debug)
14475{
14476 int sptr;
14477 int sptr1;
14478 int ast, std;
14479
14480 sptr = BLK_SCOPE_SPTR(sem.scope_level - 1);
14481
14482 if (gen_debug) {
14483 if (!sptr) {
14484 sptr = getccssym("uplevel", sem.blksymnum++, ST_BLOCK);
14485 PARSYMSCTP(sptr, 0);
14486 PARSYMSP(sptr, 0);
14487 }
14488 STARTLINEP(sptr, gbl.lineno);
14489 if (sptr != BLK_SYM(sem.scope_level - 1))
14490 ENCLFUNCP(sptr, BLK_SYM(sem.scope_level - 1));
14491 sptr1 = getlab();
14492 RFCNTI(sptr1);
14493 VOLP(sptr1, 1); /* so block is never deleted */
14494 STARTLABP(sptr, sptr1);
14495 ENCLFUNCP(sptr1, sptr);
14496 ast = mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0);
14497 std = add_stmt_after(ast, (int)STD_PREV(0));
14498 STD_LABEL(std) = sptr1;
14499 }
14500 BLK_SYM(sem.scope_level) = sptr;
14501 return sptr;
14502}
14503
14504void
14505exit_lexical_block(int gen_debug)
14506{
14507 int sptr1;
14508 int blksym;
14509 int ast, std;
14510
14511 blksym = BLK_SYM(sem.scope_level);
14512 ENDLINEP(blksym, gbl.lineno);
14513 if (gen_debug) {
14514 sptr1 = getlab();
14515 RFCNTI(sptr1);
14516 VOLP(sptr1, 1); /* so block is never deleted */
14517 ENDLABP(blksym, sptr1);
14518 ENCLFUNCP(sptr1, blksym);
14519 ast = mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0);
14520 std = add_stmt_after(ast, (int)STD_PREV(0));
14521 STD_LABEL(std) = sptr1;
14522 }
14523}

14589void
14590sem_err104(int df, int lineno, const char *str)
14591{
14592 if (df) {
14593 int id;
14594 id = DI_ID(df);
14595 if (id < sizeof(di_name) / sizeof(char *)) {
14596 char buff[256];
14597 sprintf(buff, "- %s %s", str, di_name[id]);
14598 error(104, 3, lineno, buff, CNULL);
14599 return;
14600 }
14601 interr("sem_err104:unk doif->ID", DI_ID(df), 3);
14602 }
14603}
14604
14605void
14606sem_err105(int df)
14607{
14608 if (df) {
14609 int id;
14610 id = DI_ID(df);
14611 if (id < sizeof(di_name) / sizeof(char *)) {
14612 sem_err104(df, gbl.lineno, "unterminated");
14613 return;
14614 }
14615 }
14616 errsev(105);
14617}

14619#if DEBUG
14620void
14621_dmp_doif(int df, FILE *f)
14622{
14623 int id;
14624 if (f == NULL)
14625 f = stderr;
14626 id = DI_ID(df);
14627 if (id >= sizeof(di_name) / sizeof(char *)) {
14628 fprintf(f, "Unknown DI_ID(%d) == %d\n", df, id);
14629 return;
14630 }
14631 fprintf(f, "[%3d] %s - Line=%d", df, di_name[id], DI_LINENO(df));
14632 if (DI_NAME(df))
14633 fprintf(f, " ConstructName=%d", DI_NAME(df));
14634 if (id == DI_DO && DI_DOINFO(df)->collapse)
14635 fprintf(f, " Collapse=%d", DI_DOINFO(df)->collapse);
14636 fprintf(f, "\n");
14637 if (DI_NEST(df)) {
14638 int i;
14639 fprintf(f, " Nest:0x%08lx ", DI_NEST(df));
14640 for (i = 0; i <= DI_MAXID; i++) {
14641 if (DI_B(i) & DI_NEST(df))
14642 fprintf(f, "|%s", di_name[i]);
14643 }
14644 }
14645 fprintf(f, "\n");
14646}
14647
14648void
14649dmp_doif(FILE *f)
14650{

14653 f = stderr;
14654 fprintf(f, "----- DOIF (%d entries)\n", sem.doif_depth);
14655 for (df = 1; df <= sem.doif_depth; df++) {
14656 _dmp_doif(df, f);
14657 }
14658}

14702
14703/** \brief Creates an ast that represents a call to a set type runtime routine.
14704 *
14705 * \param arg0 is the ast of the descriptor that receives the type from arg1.
14706 *
14707 * \param arg1 is the ast of the source descriptor. The type of arg1 is copied
14708 * into the arg0 descriptor.
14709 *
14710 * \param intrin_type is true when you want to use the RTE_set_intrin_type()
14711 * routine instead of the RTE_set_type() routine.
14712 *
14713 * \returns the call ast
14714 */
14715int
14716mk_set_type_call(int arg0, int arg1, LOGICAL intrin_type)
14717{
14718 int newargt, func, astnew;
14719
14720 newargt = mk_argt(2);
14721 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = arg0;
14722 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = arg1;
14723
14724 func = mk_id(sym_mkfunc_nodesc(
14725 mkRteRtnNm((intrin_type) ? RTE_set_intrin_type : RTE_set_type), DT_NONE));
14726 astnew = mk_func_node(A_CALL, func, 2, newargt);
14727
14728 return astnew;
14729}
14730
14731/** \brief Generates calls to RTE_set_type() or RTE_set_intrin_type() which
14732 * set the type descriptor field of an object's descriptor.
14733 *
14734 * \param dest_ast is the descriptor expression that's getting its type
14735 * descriptor set. Note: dest_ast may be a descriptor expression or an
14736 * expression that has a descriptor.
14737 *
14738 * \param src_ast is the expression that has the type descriptor that we are
14739 * copying to dest_ast. Note: src_ast may be a descriptor expression or an
14740 * expession that has a descriptor.
14741 *
14742 * \param std is the std where we will insert the call.
14743 *
14744 * \param insert_before is true when you want to insert the call before std,
14745 * otherwise we insert it after std.
14746 *
14747 * \param intrin_type is true when you want to use the RTE_set_intrin_type()
14748 * routine instead of the RTE_set_type() routine.
14749 *
14750 * \returns the new std after inserting the call.
14751 */
14752int
14753gen_set_type(int dest_ast, int src_ast, int std, LOGICAL insert_before,
14754 LOGICAL intrin_type)
14755{
14756 int astnew, arg0, arg1, sptr, sdsc;
14757 int atype;
14758
14759 /* Walk the ast expression to find the invoking object (an A_MEM or A_ID) */
14760 for (atype = A_TYPEG(src_ast);
14761 atype == A_FUNC || atype == A_SUBSCR || atype == A_CONV ||
14762 atype == A_CALL || atype == A_MEM;
14763 atype = A_TYPEG(src_ast)) {
14764
14765 if (atype == A_MEM) {
14766 sptr = memsym_of_ast(src_ast);
14767 if (is_tbp(sptr)) {
14768 src_ast = A_PARENTG(src_ast);
14769 } else {
14770 break;
14771 }
14772 } else {
14773 src_ast = A_LOPG(src_ast);
14774 }
14775 }
14776
14777 /* get descriptor expression for dest_ast */
14778 sptr = memsym_of_ast(dest_ast);
14779 if (DESCARRAYG(sptr) || SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY) {
14780 arg0 = dest_ast;
14781 } else if (A_TYPEG(src_ast) == A_MEM) {
14782 sdsc = get_member_descriptor(sptr);
14783 arg0 = check_member(dest_ast, mk_id(sdsc));
14784 } else {
14785 sdsc = SDSCG(sptr);
14786 if (sdsc == 0) {
14787 arg0 = dest_ast;
14788 } else {
14789 arg0 = mk_id(sdsc);
14790 }
14791 }
14792
14793 /* get descriptor expression for src_ast */
14794 if (intrin_type) {
14795 arg1 = src_ast;
14796 } else {
14797 sptr = memsym_of_ast(src_ast);
14798 if (DESCARRAYG(sptr) || SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY) {
14799 arg1 = src_ast;
14800 } else if (A_TYPEG(src_ast) == A_MEM) {
14801 sdsc = get_member_descriptor(sptr);
14802 arg1 = check_member(src_ast, mk_id(sdsc));
14803 } else {
14804 sdsc = SDSCG(sptr);
14805 if (sdsc == 0) {
14806 arg1 = src_ast;
14807 } else {
14808 arg1 = mk_id(sdsc);
14809 }
14810 }
14811 }
14812
14813 astnew = mk_set_type_call(arg0, arg1, intrin_type);
14814
14815 if (insert_before) {
14816 std = add_stmt_before(astnew, std);
14817 } else {
14818 std = add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
14819 }
14820
14821 return std;
14822}
